title: baked oatmeal
directions: Boil water and salt; mix remaining ingredients and add water all at once.
Bake in shallow dish at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve at once with milk.

title: herbed garlic mashed potatoes
directions: In large pot, boil potatoes.
Drain.
In same pot, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until golden, stirring frequently.
Remove pot from heat and add potatoes, remaining 2 tablespoons butter, milk, basil, salt and pepper. Using an electric beater or potato masher, beat mixture until smooth.

title: banana split sundae pie
directions: Spoon half of the ice cream into crust. Smooth the top.
Split bananas lengthwise and in half; arrange on ice cream.
Layer ice cream over the bananas. Freeze until firm.
Decorate with whipped cream, cherries and nuts.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine zucchini, baking soda, sugar, margarine and egg.
Sift together dry ingredients and blend into zucchini mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Makes two dozen.

title: helen's meringue
directions: Set aside egg whites.
In cold water, stir in sugar and cornstarch until cornstarch is dissolved.
Cook on the stove until soft boil stage.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar. Slowly add syrup mixture; beat until fluffy.
Spread over pies, puddings or cake.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream softened butter with sugar.
Add small amount of flour, then add eggs alternately with remaining flour.
Add Eagle Brand milk, and flavorings.
Bake in large Angel food (tube) pan sprayed with Pam.
Place in pre-heated 325° oven on top rack.
Place an iron skillet filled with water on middle rack.
Do not open door for at least one hour.
This cake will take about 1 1/2 hrs. to be done.
Place pan on wire rack and allow 30 to 40 mins. to cool in pan.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook until it boils.
Reduce heat and simmer about 20 minutes.
Makes 3 pints.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and blend well. Chill overnight in a covered dish. Makes a great salad dressing.

title: squash dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook squash in water in covered saucepan until tender.
Drain and mash.
Crumble baked cornbread into milk; set aside.
Saute celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Add pepper, soup, poultry seasoning and squash.
Stir in bread mixture.
Pour ingredients into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake for 1 hour or until set.
May top with cheese.

title: curried chicken pilaf
directions: Trim green beans and cut into 1-inch lengths on the diagonal. Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Using a hot wok, toast almonds in a small amount of vegetable oil.
Set aside.
Cook chicken in same oil*, remove.
Add more oil, cook remaining ingredients, except rice.
Return chicken and almonds to pot.

title: skillet lasagna(from maude smith)
directions: Cook lasagna according to package directions.
Drain.
Brown meat, onions and garlic in skillet at 325°.
Add seasonings and mix thoroughly.
Turn off heat.

title: cinnamon pull aparts(monkey bread)
directions: Grease Bundt pan; sprinkle in a few nuts.
Cut biscuits in quarters and roll in sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Melt oleo and add brown sugar.
Alternate layers of biscuits, oleo and brown sugar and nuts.
Bake
to 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan. Serve hot or cold by "picking" apart with fingers.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and beat about 2 minutes, then add dry ingredients and milk.
Take 1 cup of your flour and mix with the orange slices and dates before putting into the batter.
Bake in stem pan.
Bake in slow oven about 350° for about an hour or until done.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all together and bake at 400° for 1 hour or until set in middle.

title: karen's turkey dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and biscuits; add herb stuffing, onions, celery, sage and poultry seasoning.
Let set overnight.
Add eggs, broth and salt.
I buy chicken broth in cans and mix with turkey broth.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: double cheese macaroni casserole
directions: Grate cheese, Mix with next 8 ingredients.
Cook macaroni in salted water and drain.
Melt margarine in hot macaroni and mix with cheese mixture.
Pour into 3 quart casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly around edges.	Bake at 350 degrees.

title: oatmeal-carrot muffins
directions: Combine wet ingredients with sugar.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Add together.
Use lined muffin pan.
Bake at 375° for 15-20 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole(recipe from mom.  serves 8.)
directions: Pour rice in pan; pour 1 cup of broth over.
Layer chicken in pan.
Mix soups and milk together and pour in pan.
Mix melted oleo, stuffing and 1 cup broth; pour over.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses.
Sift two cups flour with other dry ingredients.
Add to the first mixture with sour milk.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Roll and cut in shape.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: mexican pasta salad
directions: Cook fusilli pasta in large pot of boiling salted water until just tender, but still firm to bite.
Drain.
Rinse pasta with cold water to cool.
Drain pasta well.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add 1 1/2 tablespoons olive oil and mix thoroughly to coat.
Add shredded chicken, diced tomatoes, corn kernels, carrot strips and chopped onion.
Toss.
Mix Dijon mustard and fresh lime juice in small bowl.
Gradually mix in remaining 1/3 cup olive oil.
Mix in chilies, chili powder and ground cumin.
Add dressing and chopped cilantro to salad; mix to blend.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Salad can be prepared 4 hours ahead.
Store in refrigerator, covered.
Serves 8.

title: tomatoes and shells
directions: In a large cook pot, cook shell macaroni per package directions and drain.
Return macaroni to pan and add all other ingredients.
Simmer over very low heat for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crush cookies well.
Add melted oleo and mix.
Reserve 1 cup of the Oreo/butter mixture for topping.
Press remainder of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut ice cream into layers or blocks (1 to 1 1/2-inches thick).
Put ice cream on top of cookie base.
Pour caramel topping on ice cream.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle remaining Oreo/butter mixture on top.
Place in freezer.
Allow 10 to 20 minutes to thaw before serving.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix all but soup and water.
Make into 2-inch balls.
Place in baking dish; pour soup and water over top.
Bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: clam dip
directions: Drain minced clams; set aside clam juice.
Mix all ingredients together and flavor with clam juice.
Chill.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, oats, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
In a small bowl, stir together eggs, milk, margarine (or butter) and brown sugar.
Add flour mixture and stir until blended.
Pour batter into grids of preheated, lightly greased waffle baker.
Close lid quickly; do not open during baking.
Use fork to remove baked waffle.
Top with fruit and yogurt.
Serving Size: 12.
Preparation Time:

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt the butter and mix with the cracker crumbs.
Press into bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Layer over the crust the chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, coconut and the milk.
Pat down and top with the pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: maureen's apricot jello
directions: Bring Jell-O and pineapple to a boil and let cool.
As this cools, beat cream cheese, Cool Whip and baby food.
After mixture is cool, whip the two together and chill.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon and vanilla. Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours.
Can be topped with cherry, strawberry and/or Cool Whip.

title: mom's ketchup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Whisk until smooth. When mixture comes to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring often. Remove pan from heat and cover until cool. Chill in a covered container. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: mile high meringue
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in the cold water.
Add the boiling water. Stir and cook over heat until clear.
Cool.
Beat the egg whites until stiff.
(Egg whites beat better if warmed to room temperature.)
Do not use any plastic bowls or spoons, etc. Gradually add the sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add cooled cornstarch mixture.
Pile on pies (be sure to seal edge of pie shell).
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix remaining ingredients; simmer for 2 hours.

title: sheath cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
In saucepan, combine margarine, cocoa, shortening and water.
Bring to boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mix; stir well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease 18 x 11-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Batter is thin.
Start frosting when cake is in oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Mix chicken and mushroom soups and chicken broth together.
Mix melted butter and stuffing mix together.
Put half of mix in a 14 x 20-inch baking dish.
Lay slices of the chicken breasts on stuffing.
Spread soup on chicken. Finish with the layer of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: rabbit and dumplings
directions: Cut
up rabbits in serving pieces.
Put in a large pot. Cook until
done with some butter, salt and pepper.
Cook and debone. Clean
the	pot.
Put
meat
back
in
the	pot.
Add chicken broth,
water, butter, salt and pepper and bring to a boil. Quarter
and
pull	apart
the biscuits.
Drop into the meat mixture one at a time and cook until done.	Serve hot.

title: cranberry orange mold
directions: Add boiling water to Jell-O, salt and spices in a medium size bowl. Stir until all dissolved.
Add cranberries and orange rind. Chill until thick.
Fold in oranges and apples.
Pour into 6-cup mold.
Chill.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Cream oleo; add sugar, eggs and other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into large unbaked crust.	Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: thin-layer cake
directions: In a mixer bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and creamy. Beat in eggs, one at a time, mixing thoroughly.

Stir together cake mix and flour. With mixer on low speed, alternately add dry ingredients, milk and sour cream to butter mixture. Mix well. Use cooking spray before adding 3/4 cup mixture to an 8-inch pan. (I bought ten 8-inch throw away cake pans.) Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Cool and frost. Makes 12 to 15 layers. Frost with Iron Skillet Chocolate Icing.

title: bok choy salad
directions: Melt oleo in skillet, then add sugar, sesame seed, noodles and slivered almonds.
Cook over low heat until lightly brown.
Set aside at room temperature.
Cut up green onions, using tops and all, and 2 pound package bok choy (chopped), using leaves and stems.
Mix with first mixture and chill until ready to serve. Top with dressing when serving.

title: ground meat, macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
The last 5 minutes, sprinkle with shredded cheese.

title: grammpy's wet chocolate cake
directions: Sift in large bowl the flour, sugar and salt (if not using self-rising flour).
Melt and boil water, cocoa and margarine. (This can easily be done in microwave.)
Pour mixture over sifted flour mixture.
Stir.
Add buttermilk which has been mixed with baking soda.
Add eggs and vanilla to buttermilk mixture.
Stir and pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately 30 to 40 minutes.
While cake is still hot add Topping.

title: chessabatter zesty
directions: Beat butter and Italian dressing.
Add remaining ingredients. Make into a log and refrigerate.
This makes a good cracker spread.

title: doughnuts
directions: Cut center out of biscuits.
Fry doughnuts and doughnut holes in hot grease, first on one side and then on the other, until the doughnuts are golden brown.
(Turn over only one time.)
Takes approximately 45 to 60 seconds.
Drain until cool on cooling rack. Cover with desired glaze.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sugar, thoroughly and shape into balls the size of a walnut. Roll in confectioners sugar. Keep in an air tight container until ready to serve. Serve with punch or eggnog.

title: easy breakfast
directions: Fry sausage meat (scrambled).
Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard.
Layer bread in a slightly buttered baking dish.
Add the scrambled sausage meat.
Pour eggs and milk mixture over sausage and top with cheese.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients; add zucchini and vanilla.
Sift together remaining ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to moist ones.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Makes 2 loaves.

title: creamy fruit cup
directions: Mix yogurt, pineapple and strawberries together.
In dish, put layer of cottage cheese and layer of yogurt mixture and repeat until dish is full.

title: 9 day slaw
directions: Chop and mix cabbage, onions and green pepper.
Pour 1 cup sugar over at once and let stand 15 minutes.
Bring to boil salad oil, vinegar, celery seed, salt and 1 cup sugar.
Pour over all and mix.
Refrigerate.
Good for 9 days.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Finely chop tomatoes, cabbage, onions and red peppers. Combine with remaining ingredients in a kettle. Bring to a boil for 10 minutes. Pour into hot sterile jars; allow 1-inch from lid. Seal jars. Store in cool dark place. Makes 8 pints.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Have eggs, cream cheese and margarine at room temperature. Cream butter, eggs, cream cheese and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Sift flour and add to the creamed mixture.
Add flavoring.
Pour into 9-inch prepared tube pan, floured and greased.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool on rack.

title: date bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and baking soda; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Spread batter in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan; cut in bars. Yields approximately 2 dozen bars.

title: zucchini parmigiana
directions: Prepare Sauce:
In large pot add oil, chopped onion and about 8 sausage links and brown.
Add 2 cans tomato puree and spices, garlic, parsley, basil, salt and pepper and 3 tablespoons grated Parmesan.
Simmer on low heat, stirring regularly for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican salad
directions: Shred and save 2 tablespoons cheese.
Cut remaining cheese into cubes.
Peel, seed and cut into slices the avocado.
In a large pan, cook beef until browned.
Drain fat.
Add Sloppy Joe sauce and cook until hot.
Chop lettuce coarsely and arrange on a plate.
Top with avocado, salsa, tortilla chips, cheese cubes and cooked ground chuck.
Top all with reserved shredded cheese. Serves 4.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Unroll crescent dough and separate into triangles.
Cut each triangle into three triangles.
Place a sausage on long end of each triangle and roll up tightly.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 400 degrees for about 20 minutes.
Serve with deli mustard.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together well and form into balls.
Cook on cookie sheet (spray lightly with Pam) for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Potatoes may be
cooked
in
skins
until done.
Peel and grate. Melt 1/2 cup butter with cheese together.
Remove from heat and stir in potatoes, sour cream,
salt,
pepper and onions.
Pour into 8 x 12-inch casserole and dot
with 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle with paprika. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dog cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients into sticky dough. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Or form into rectangle and squeeze into dog biscuit shape.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes. Cool on rack and store in plastic bag or can.
Makes 30.

title: oven rice
directions: Cut up margarine in bottom of casserole dish.
Add rice, soups, Worcestershire sauce, herbs and mushrooms on top.
Cover dish; put into a 350° oven and bake 1 hour.
Do not uncover or stir.

title: catherine's cinnamon rolls
directions: Put rolls in a greased Bundt pan.
Blend together other ingredients; pour over rolls.
Cover with Saran Wrap; let raise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Scrape bowl after each minute.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350° in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Melt butter, blend in flour.
Add milk and broth; cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add parsley, lemon juice, onion and seasonings.
Let cool slightly; then add chicken. Chill.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix pineapple (drained), mandarin oranges (drained), marshmallows, bananas, grapes with peach pie filling.
Chill.

title: brownies for the crowd
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts; stir in nuts.
Pour into 11 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: famous amos cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugars, vanilla, water and eggs.
In small bowl, mix flour, soda and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: pork with smoked oysters
directions: Combine in a bowl the soy sauce, sherry and 2 teaspoons cornstarch.
Mix until cornstarch is dissolved.
Add pork and thoroughly combine.
Drain cans of oysters and finely chop. Separate lettuce leaves and wash under cold running water; pat dry with towelling.

Arrange on a serving platter and refrigerate. Dissolve 2 teaspoons cornstarch in 2 tablespoons chicken stock. Have ingredients (oil, peas, oysters, oyster sauce and cornstarch mixture) within easy reach.
Heat wok.
Add oil.
Heat oil.
Add pork mixture and stir-fry for about 2 minutes or until meat loses its pink color and all liquids evaporate.
Add peas, oysters and oyster sauce; stir-fry for a few minutes longer.
Stir to re-combine cornstarch mixture and add to wok.
Cook until ingredients are coated with a light glaze.
Place on serving platter.

title: banana split pie
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo, mix with graham cracker crumbs to make crust.

title: mystery pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in sugar and baking powder. Crush Ritz crackers and layer in 8-inch pie pan.
Add mixture and top with pecans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: green bean side dish
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° until bubbling.
Serve with main dish.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Carefully remove leaves from cabbage.
Pour boiling water over separated leaves.
Place small cabbage leaves that are too small to fill in bottom of deep kettle.
Mix together meat, rice, eggs and seasonings; mix well.
Make meatballs; wrap in cabbage leaves and place in kettle.
After kettle is 1/2 full, place sliced onion on top.
Pour in can of tomatoes.
Finish placing rest of meat in leaves.
When finished filling with cabbage rolls, pour tomato sauce over top.
Squeeze juice of 1/2 a lemon and sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Cook on top of stove slowly for few hours until well done over a low heat.

title: lemon delight
directions: Blend flour and butter.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: teddy snack mix
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place cookies, pretzels and raisins in large baking pan.
Stir together melted margarine and cinnamon. Pour over cookie mixture.
Toss to coat evenly.
Bake for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Let cool completely.
Store in container with tight fitting lid.

title: pink velvet frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Fold in Cool Whip. Line loaf pan with foil paper.
Pour mixture into pan and freeze.
Lift out of pan and wrap again for freezer. Slice and serve.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Blend sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add beaten egg and almond extract.
Mix well.
Put peaches in unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Pour sugar mixture over peaches.

title: mushroom tarts
directions: Roll the bread slices flat with a rolling pin.
Cut the bread into circles using a small bowl, and shape into tart shells in the muffin tin.
Toast in the oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes (until they are hard and browned).
Finely chop the mushrooms and mix with the other ingredients (except cheese, flour and cream).
Simmer over medium or low heat until mushrooms have been reduced to a paste (about 20 minutes), stirring regularly.
Now add the cheese, flour and cream and stir well over heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour the mixture into shells and serve!

title: bruce's enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Season with 1/2 cup hot sauce; stir well.
Dip corn tortillas in hot oil, then dip into water.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons beef mixture into center of each tortilla and roll.
Place, side by side, into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish until dish is full.
Microwave cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes in a glass bowl until melted.
Add 1/2 cup sour cream; stir well.
Pour cheese mixture over tortillas.
Bake for 20 minutes, or until bubbly, at 350°.
Top individual servings with 1 to 2 tablespoons sour cream.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cry baby cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: peanut butter no-bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and let boil 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Add oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper to cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Thoroughly blend cheeses, onion and Worcestershire sauce. Fold in pineapple.
Make into ball.
Roll in nuts and chill.

title: grandma's punch
directions: Put all ingredients in punch bowl and enjoy!

title: diet cake
directions: Cook raisins in water with sweetener and let cool.
Beat eggs and add applesauce.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in cupcake pan or cake pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cauliflower with herb butter
directions: Steam flowerets over boiling water for 10 minutes; arrange in serving dish and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Melt butter and stir in parsley, salt, basil and garlic.
Pour herb butter over all. Serves 6.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix lemonade, orange juice and water in punch bowl.
Add scoops of ice cream and sherbet.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate 1 hour.
Makes 20 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine raisins and boiling water; set aside.
In mixing bowl beat shortening, sugar, salt, spices and eggs until creamy, smooth and fluffy.
Scrape bowl often.
Blend in applesauce, then flour and walnuts.
Stir soda into undrained raisins.
Add to batter and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven 40 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: corn fritter puffs
directions: Drain the can of whole kernel corn well, reserving 1/2 cup of liquid.
Sift together the flour, cornmeal, baking powder, salt and sugar.

title: swiss onion ring
directions: Unthaw dough.
Mix ingredients together, except dough.
Cut loaf in half the long way, then into 20 or 30 pieces.
Put half in bottom of greased pan.
Put 1/2 mixture on top of dough, then rest of dough, then top off with rest of ingredients.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Very good.

title: cherry salad
directions: Blend all the ingredients.
Store in icebox.

title: ricotta puffs
directions: In a large bowl, beat Ricotta with eggs and sugar until smooth.
In another bowl, sift together dry ingredients and add to Ricotta mixture, beating until smooth.
Pour oil in a deep pan to a depth of 1 1/2-inches and heat to 360°.
For each puff, drop a rounded teaspoonful of batter in oil.
Turn occasionally until golden (about 1 1/2 minutes).
Drain and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix together; roll into small balls.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.
Don't overbake, or they will be hard.
(Preheat oven.)

title: tomato ketchup
directions: Mix all in dishpan.
Cook on medium heat until real thick. This takes awhile.
When it gets thick, pack in jars and seal.

title: micro-quick fudge
directions: You also need a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spiced oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Stir flour, baking soda, cinnamon, allspice and salt in a small bowl.
Beat butter in a large bowl until creamy.
Beat in sugar until fully mixed.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well. Beat in vanilla.
Beat flour mixture into butter mixture.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop 2 inches apart on a baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: williamsburg orange cake
directions: Grease and flour oblong pan.
Beat all ingredients on low speed for 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: swiss fondue
directions: Rub garlic clove over inside of fondue pot or earthenware pot. Pour in wine.
Heat until bubbles form.
Combine cheese and cornstarch.
Add to wine, small portion at a time, stirring until cheese melts.
Add rest of ingredients.
Serve with bite size pieces of French bread, toasted or not.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Fry bacon until crisp in large kettle.
Add cut-up cabbage and water (enough to cover).
Add salt, pepper and bouillon cube or soup base.
Cook and cover until tender.
Add corned beef, cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: confetti slaw
directions: Mix and chill well.

title: gooey
directions: Brown pork chops lightly.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle raw rice over top to cover chops.
Arrange sliced onion and green pepper over top.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour water over to cover rice.
Cover dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: moo goo gai pen(low-fat)
directions: Skin, debone and slice chicken breast.
Stir-fry snow peas in peanut oil for 2 minutes.
Remove.
Stir-fry mushrooms for 2 minutes.
Remove.
Stir-fry cabbage until slightly wilted. Remove.
Stir-fry chicken until white.
Add vegetables and chicken stock and thicken.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken for 1 hour; take off bone.
Simmer chicken, bouillon cubes, celery, carrots and onion until done.
Add cream of celery and mushroom soups, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add noodles and simmer until done.

title: corn pie
directions: Beat together the eggs, salt and pepper.
Cut up margarine in eggs.
Drain corn; add to eggs and margarine mixture.
Add gradually 2 cups milk; mix well.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: aunt mary's spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Let cool.
Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: pumpkin mousse pie
directions: Prepare pie filling mix as directed on package with milk. Blend in pumpkin, spice and 2 cups Cool Whip.
Spoon mixture into pie shell.
Chill at least 4 hours in refrigerator.
For extended period, pie holds better in freezer.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour before serving.

title: ham casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes, then mix with rest of ingredients, except Rice Krispies.
Pour into buttered 10 x 6-inch or 8 x 8-inch dish. Cover with Rice Krispies.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apricot cake
directions: Note:
Beat eggs before you put them in the mix.

title: marinated pork loin roast
directions: Pierce pork loin in several places with long tined fork. Place in shallow glass dish.
Blend water, mustard, oil and soy sauce. Brush over meat.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour. Drain meat.
Reserve the liquid.
Insert rotisserie spit rod through center of roast.
Secure with prongs.
Insert meat thermometer near center of roast, being careful not to hit the rod.
Position drip pan under roast and begin grilling. Grill over medium setting for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until meat thermometer registers 170° for well done.
Brush with sauce during last 30 minutes of grilling time.
Heat remaining sauce to serve with meat.
Makes 8 servings.

title: french style onion soup
directions: If any of the onion rings are large, cut them in half; sprinkle with the sugar.
In a large non-aluminum saucepot melt the butter; add the onion and cook gently, stirring often until a pale gold color.
Add the beef broth and the water; cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Refrigerate.
At serving time reheat and ladle into individual ovenproof casseroles.
Top with the bread and generously sprinkle with the cheese.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix the ingredients; pour into baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle 1 roll of Ritz crackers over top.

title: french bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine all other ingredients (flour last) and knead thoroughly.
(Really punch it out.)
Punch down every 10 minutes for 1 hour.
Divide in half and let rise 10 minutes to 1 hour.
Roll into jelly roll.
Use rolling pin to roll out.
Then roll like jelly roll.
Let rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours on a well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Brush with butter immediately from oven.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and eggs; pat in 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Mix cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour batter on first mix.
Bake in oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: california walnut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in 1 1/4 cups walnuts.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Mix just enough to blend.

title: italian lasagna(serving size: 8)
directions: Combine
first	3 ingredients.	Salt and pepper and add eggs and chill (can be prepared 1 day ahead).

title: caramel popcorn in bag
directions: You will also need a brown grocery sack.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain and mash.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole and top with cracker crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated salad
directions: Mix vinegar, oil and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate at least 3 to 4 hours.
The longer, the better.
Serve cold.
Preparation time:
30 minutes. Makes 16 servings.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in sifter.
Beat vegetable oil, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and beat well.
Beat in flour mixture. Stir in morsels and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until brown.

title: groton(french meat spread)
directions: Wet saucepan and pour out all water.
Add pork; cover and cook on medium-high heat.
Chop onion and add to pork; stir and cover. Cut potato in half; add to pan.
Cover with pork.
Bring to steam and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Take out potato and mash (no milk). Add potato, salt and pepper to taste and allspice to meat and stir well.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Turn off heat and let stand for 1/2 hour.
Pour in dish.
Cover and refrigerate.
Delicious spread on bread or crackers.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients in a bowl.
Pour in buttered casserole.
Top with corn flakes, mixed with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mandarin orange jello
directions: Use juices and water to make 2 cups cold liquid.
Add to jello mix.
After jello and cheese are mixed, add fruits, a pinch of salt and 1/2 cup chopped nuts (walnuts or pecans).
Pour into large mold to jell and refrigerate.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add spices and stewed tomatoes.
Simmer covered for 15 minutes.
Add brown sugar and simmer 15 more minutes.
Place chicken in casserole.
Pour sauce over chicken. Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.
Serve over hot rice.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Mix all ingredients together. Let stand 10 minutes; pour on floured board. Knead a few minutes and make into rolls; let rise for 30 minutes. Bake at 350°.

title: apple cake
directions: Pare and dice the apples.
Mix with the sugar while you are doing them.
Let stand 1 hour to soften.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift flour with salt, cinnamon and soda.
Add to apples and mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: irish cream
directions: Whisk all the above and enjoy.

title: pecan toffee cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir together flours, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Add toffee pieces and pecans.
Batter will be very stiff.
Using small scoop, place on cookie sheet lined with parchment paper.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Let cool on counter before removing from parchment paper.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in a small amount of water until almost tender. Add beaten eggs, milk, mushroom soup and onions.
Add a layer of this mixture and a layer of cheese, making 2 layers.
Cover with cracker crumbs; dot with butter or margarine.
Bake about 30 minutes at 325°.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package.
Drain.
Melt 2 chicken bouillon cubes in 1 cup hot water. Melt butter and add flour. Stir until smooth.
Add chicken bouillon to butter and flour mix gradually, stirring until mixture thickens.
Add to drained spinach and stir well. Serves 6.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Lightly brown the onion and green peppers in bacon drippings. Combine all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 375° until bubbly and browned on top.

title: cooked pork chops
directions: Salt, pepper and flour the pork chops.
Put in a large hot skillet of grease.
Brown on both sides.
Drain grease.
Add one cup of tomato catsup and one can of Coke over the chops. Turn on low heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Sauce will thicken, chops will be tender.
Very good with mashed potatoes.

title: baked hawaiian chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish (12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch).
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: percolator cranberry punch
directions: Combine in percolator the cranberry juice cocktail, water, pineapple juice and brown sugar.
Stir to mix well.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Dredge raw diced meat in flour and brown in oil, along with onion.
When meat is brown, add enough flour to absorb any extra oil.
Let this brown as for gravy.
Add soups and tomato paste.
Use milk and flour mixture to make a thick sauce if needed.
Simmer on low.
About 15 to 30 minutes before serving, stir sour cream into sauce.
(Note: French onion soup may be used to get both onion and beef bouillon at once.)
Keep heat low once sauces are in to keep from sticking. May be served over cooked noodles, or noodles may be stirred into sauce before serving.
Stir often.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Boil the raisins and water until the raisins swell.
Take off stove and cool.
Cream together the shortening, sugar, eggs, salt, soda and vanilla.
Add cooled raisins and the flour.
Mix well. Pour into greased 3 (15 ounce) cans or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Nuts may be added.

title: sausage chowder
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Dice potatoes and green pepper, add to chowder and cook for 30 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix flour, butter and sugar; pat in bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan like loose crust.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Beat eggs, then add sugar and lemon juice.
Fold in baking powder and flour.
Pour mixture on top of crust and bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
While warm, sprinkle lightly with powdered sugar.
When cool, cut in strips or squares.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Using electric mixer, mash cooked carrots (will be lumpy). Mix dry ingredients with oil or butter; add eggs and blend.
Add carrots and milk and blend with mixer.
Pour into ungreased 2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set as for custard.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° to 375° for 40 minutes.
Flour sinks to bottom, coconut rises to top for crust. Delicious!
Enough for 2 pies.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Salt, pepper and thyme the chicken pieces.
Sear in a mixture 3 parts olive oil to 1 part vegetable oil.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Remove all but 2 tablespoons oil.
Add diced onions, bell pepper and garlic.
Saute until onions are clear.
Add chicken and cover with tomato sauce.
Add mushrooms, bay leaves, parsley, 1 teaspoon basil and 1 teaspoon thyme.
Cook for about 30 minutes while moderately boiling, until chicken is done.
Serve over cooked pasta.

title: e-z chicken
directions: Place chicken in a Brown 'N Serve bag.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Pour mixes over chicken and close bag with twist tie. Place in oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: nonalcoholic moonshine(healthy)
directions: Blend all
ingredients together for a quick pick-me-up. Healthy.

title: english apple pie
directions: Grease 9-inch pie plate with butter, then slice apples and layer in bottom of pie plate.
Mix cinnamon and sugar together and sprinkle over apples.
Stir together butter, brown sugar, flour, salt, water and chopped pecans.
Mixture will be gooey.
Spread over apples with knife dipped in water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fast fruit
directions: Mix both ingredients well. Chill. That's it!

title: aunt kay's version of cabbage rolls
directions: Mix the ground beef, sausage, egg, rice and Worcestershire sauce in a large bowl or pan. Form this mixture into egg-shaped forms a little larger than an egg. Boil the head of cabbage to soften the leaves. Wrap a cabbage leaf around each piece of egg-shaped meat. Line a roasting pan with aluminum foil. Line the aluminum foil with a half jar of drained sauerkraut. Place wrapped meat on the layer of sauerkraut. Spread the remainder of the sauerkraut on top of the wrapped meat. Mix the soup with 1 can of water, then pour over the top layer of sauerkraut. Cover your pan with another piece of aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: scallops and vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in butter in large skillet for 1 minute.
Add mushrooms, carrots and celery.
Cook, stirring constantly.
Sprinkle with dill, salt and pepper.
Set aside.

title: hershey pie
directions: Heat Hershey bars, marshmallows and milk in top of double boiler until completely dissolved.
Take off stove and cool completely.
Fold whipped cream into chocolate mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill 6 hours.

title: homemade garlic bread
directions: Spread butter over inside of each bun.
Sprinkle garlic powder on top of the buttered bun.
Bake in oven at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Best served hot out of oven.

title: chocolate chip banana cookies
directions: Sift together the first 4 ingredients.
Mix together the bananas, milk and vanilla.
Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix all together.
Add 1 package chocolate chips.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: veal curry(yields 6 servings)
directions: Cut veal in bite sized pieces and brown slowly in fat.
When almost brown, add onion and continue browning.
Sprinkle with curry powder over meat, add hot water and lemon juice; cover, simmer slowly 3/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Combine cornstarch and cold water to a smooth paste, and stir slowly into the mixture. Continue cooking five minutes, stirring constantly. If too thick, add water to right consistency.
Serve with rice mixed with minced parsley, if desired.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: On low heat in saucepan warm butter and sugar together; stir in cocoa and vanilla.
Before boiling, add eggs and pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend with mixer and pour into crust.
Chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients to broccoli (except save some cheese for top).
Put in buttered dish.
Cover with cheese and crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade cream of mushroom soup
directions: Spray medium saucepan with Pam.
Saute mushrooms, onions and white cooking wine.
Stir in chicken broth.
In a small bowl, stir together 1/4 cup of the milk and cornstarch until smooth.
Combine these 2 mixtures.
Stir in remaining 3/4 cup milk.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Stir frequently.
Simmer 2 minutes.

title: clara mae's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa, milk and salt.
Cook 3 minutes. Remove from heat; add yolks and margarine.
Return to heat and cook until mixture separates when spoon is cut through it.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites and sugar and spread on top.
Bake at 350° until meringue is golden.

title: taco casserole
directions: In medium skillet, cook meat until browned, stirring to break up large pieces.
Drain excess fat.
Sprinkle with garlic.
Place crushed chips in bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon hot meat over chips.
Spread 3/4 to 1 cup of sauce over meat.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until heated and cheese is melted.
Top with lettuce and sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: coconut muffins
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and eggs together.
Blend in all other ingredients.
Divide into 12 greased muffin pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dutch santa claus cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and knead into a loaf or roll.
Set overnight in refrigerator.
Cut in slices and bake in moderate oven (350°).

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put half of the bread and half of the cheese in a greased 9 x 13 greased dish. Add sausage that has been browned and drained well. Add rest of bread and cheese. Mix milk, eggs, mustard, salt and pepper together. Pour over other ingredients. Cover and put in the refrigerator overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered with foil. Brown without foil if necessary. Serve hot.

title: banana split cake(no bake)
directions: Line 8 1/2 x 12-inch baking dish with graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick margarine.
Mix cream cheese, 1 stick margarine and 1 egg.
Beat in 10x sugar until stiff.
Spread over crust.
Slice bananas and arrange on top next.
Drain pineapple and spread over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pineapple.
Top with cherries and nuts.
Pour syrup thinly over top.
Chill 8 hours or 2 hours in freezer before serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix ingredients. Scoop inside of 1 loaf round bread out, making a bowl. Add dip to the loaf. Serve with the bite size pieces of bread that have been removed from the loaf of bread. Serves 9 to 12.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add pineapple, strawberries and sliced bananas.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture into a mold and let jell. Spread sour cream over mixture and let set for 20 minutes.
Pour rest of the mixture on top and let jell.

title: tortoni
directions: Separate eggs.
Put whites in small mixer bowl as separated. Refrigerate yolks.
Let whites warm to room temperature 1 hour. Mix 1/4 cup water with sugar in 1-quart saucepan.
Stir over low heat to dissolve.
Boil, uncovered, without stirring to 236° on candy thermometer.
(Syrup spins 2 inch thread from spoon.)

title: quick lemon pie
directions: Mix lemonade and milk well.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Cut top off cherry tomatoes.
Remove pulp.
Turn up side down on paper towel.
Let drain.
Stuff tomatoes with spinach mixture. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Yields approximately 24 cherry tomatoes.

title: old time dumplings
directions: Beat eggs, milk and oleo. Add flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Mix lightly.
Set aside 5 minutes to tighten.
Drop into hot broth by dipping tablespoon into broth each time before dipping into dough.
Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes, then cover and cook 10 minutes more or until well done.

title: lemon lush dessert
directions: Mix flour, butter and 3/4 cup chopped walnuts together.
Press onto the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan to cover the bottom as a crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until firm.
Let cool.
Mix the cream cheese with 1 container Cool Whip; spread over cooled crust.
Prepare lemon pudding according to directions; spread as next layer.
Top with 1 container Cool Whip; add nuts.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust:
Add
graham
cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup butter. Stir and press into bottom of pan.

title: veal patties
directions: Combine meat, fat, lemon juice and seasonings.
Form patties. Dip into egg mixed with water, then into bread crumbs.
Brown in hot fat.
Cook 15 minutes.
Serve with Piquant Gravy.

title: impossible pie
directions: Pie makes its own crust.
Put ingredients in blender; blend for 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Grate or shred carrots.
Add chopped onion.
Put in bowl.
Add crushed soda crackers.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in mayonnaise, a spoon at a time, until the consistency you want.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook rice until almost soft.
Brown hamburg and onion; add tomato juice.
Simmer 1/2 hour; add catsup, brown sugar and spaghetti sauce mix.
Simmer a few minutes.
If too dry, add as much water as needed.

title: plum bread
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients well and add the remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken in the blanket
directions: Melt butter in bottom of a roast pan.
Put sliced potatoes in pan with cut up chicken on top.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour or until all is tender.
Mix together flour, baking powder, lard and salt; add enough milk to stir and all is moist.
Put this mixture on top of chicken and bake until biscuit mixture is firm and light brown.
Make a brown gravy and pour over biscuits.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil in large frying pan.
Flatten out patties.
Cook until golden brown.
Turn and brown other side.

title: mint tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer and steep for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Strain and chill.

title: burnt caramel icing
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients together in heavy saucepan.

title: green and gold potato casserole(microwave)
directions: Power Level: High.
Microwave Time: 17 1/2 to 21 minutes total.

title: spring delight
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add marshmallows and cream cheese and stir with wire whisk until dissolved.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill until congealed.

title: tropical punch
directions: Combine punch, lemonade, orange juice and grape juice concentrates.
Add water.
Mix well.
Pour into large punch bowl. Resting bottle on rim, carefully pour in ginger ale.
Add ice or frozen mixture of 7-Up with orange and/or lemon slices.
Yields approximately 35 servings.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine bread crumbs and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Beat eggs in another bowl.
Dip chicken into egg, then bread crumbs.
In a large skillet over medium heat, add oil and saute chicken 5 minutes on each side.
Remove.
In a small bowl, combine spaghetti sauce, garlic and oregano until mixed.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange chicken pieces over mix.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove foil.
Top each piece of chicken with a slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Cook spiral pasta and add parsley.
Drain and toss, then serve with chicken.

title: spiced apple cider
directions: Combine in crock-pot.
Heat 2 to 5 hours until warm or hot. Serve from pot (warm).

title: marcia's peanut butter fudge(old fashioned)
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, milk and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook slow until it forms a soft ball, stirring constantly. Remove from stove and add remaining ingredients.
Beat just until peanut butter is melted.
Pour into 8-inch pan that has been buttered and let cool.
Cut in small pieces.
(I use wax paper in bottom and sides, that way it is easy to take out of pan.)
So good!

title: acorn squash supreme
directions: Halve squash lengthwise and scrape out seeds.
Place open end down in pan of water and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn over and put 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 2 to 3 tablespoons margarine in each and bake 30 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Wash the rice thoroughly and mix all the ingredients together in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 2 hours. Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: farmers market medley
directions: In a large skillet, cook green beans and carrots in hot oil for 3 or 4 minutes, or until crisp-tender, stirring constantly. Add squash, green pepper, onion, garlic and pepper.
Cook, covered, over medium heat for 5 minutes more or until squash and pepper are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir mustard into vegetable mixture; add tomatoes and dill weed.
Cook, uncovered, for 2 to 3 minutes more or until heated through.
Season to taste with salt.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Mix together mustard, flour and salt.
Add 1 cup of evaporated milk.
Put rest of evaporated milk and sugar on top of a double boiler and turn heat on.
Add mustard mixture slowly while mixing. Add egg yolks slowly while mixing.
Heat and thicken.
When thick, add heated vinegar and take all from heat.
Keep warm on top of double boiler, but don't cook anymore.
Serve in a pitcher and use on vegetables and meats.
Also good with ham.

title: miracle pie
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into a 10-inch pie plate that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
A crust will form on the bottom, pie filling is the center and a coconut topping above.

title: chewy noels
directions: Melt butter in a 9-inch pan over low heat.
Beat eggs slightly.
Combine sugar, flour, soda and nuts and stir into beaten eggs.
Add vanilla.
Pour over butter.
Cook for 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 18 bars.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.

title: hash browns and hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients together except cheese.
Pour ground beef and onions in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour remaining ingredients on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Spread Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: okra cakes
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except egg.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot grease.
Cook until brown.

title: rice with chicken and cheese
directions: Chop onion and brown in fat.
Add salt and broth.
Heat to boiling and add rice.
Cover pan and cook on low heat for 20 minutes.
Turn heat off and let stand for 10 minutes, covered. Add chicken to rice; reheat.
Sprinkle cheese on each serving. Makes 4 servings.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Heat and allow to cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm tap water.
Add to cooled first mixture and mix.
Add egg.
Gradually add flour, a little at a time.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Let rise until double in size, about 1 hour.
Roll out; cut with doughnut cutter. Lay on wax lined cookie sheets.
Let rise in warm place.
Deep fry in 365° oil until golden brown on both sides.
Drain, cool and glaze.

title: tagliarini
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; add green pepper, if desired. Drain off fat.
Cook noodles; add with olives, tomatoes and corn. Season and bake in 350° oven or can be cooked in an electric skillet.
When it is about done, add sliced or shredded sharp Cheddar cheese.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and press firmly over bottom and about 2 1/2-inches up sides of heavily buttered 9-inch spring-form pan. Chill.

title: herby vegetable pizza
directions: Spread roll dough on jellyroll pan, pinching together edges and perforations and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Beat together cream cheese, mayonnaise and herbs.
Spread on cooled crust.
Chop raw vegetables (your choice) and press on cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Cut in squares and serve cold.

title: sardine fritters(4 to 5 persons)
directions: Leave the sardines to drain from the oil.
Put the flour in a basin with the salt and pepper.
Put the yolk of the egg in a well in the centre and add enough milk to form a smooth batter.
Beat up the white of egg and stir in lightly.
Place a sardine on a tablespoon and dip the spoon in the batter to coat the fish.
Dry fry in a lightly greased frying pan, turning the fritters once. Drain on paper and decorate with parsley and slices of lemon. (WCB)

title: dilly asparagus
directions: Cook asparagus according to package directions, omitting salt; drain.
Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients in a jar; cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Place asparagus in a shallow container.
Pour marinade over asparagus; cover and chill 8 hours. To serve, drain asparagus and arrange on serving platter.
Drain pimiento mixture, using a slotted spoon, and spoon over asparagus. Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: microwave stuffed green peppers
directions: Combine meat, fish, chicken and cheese mixtures with your favorite seasoning.
Heap in on crackers, toast, chips, lettuce cups or eclair shells.

title: pepperoni breadsticks
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix baking mix, cold water, and pepperoni until dough forms.
Beat 20 strokes.
Turn dough onto surface dusted with baking mix; gently roll in baking mix
to coat.
Knead 5 times.
Roll dough into 10-inch square.
Cut into strips.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sausage corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Grease 10-1/2 inch iron skillet or 2 qt. baking dish. Brown sausage and onion. Drain well. Combine eggs, cornmeal, corn, milk, and oil. Pour half of cornmeal mix in prepared dish. Sprinkle with sausage mixture and cheese. Pour remaining batter on top. Bake 30-40 minutes.

title: no cook peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased dish.
Cut in squares when firm.

title: light fudge(this makes about 5 pounds)
directions: Cook on high heat until boils, then on low heat until soft ball stage.
Do not stir a lot while cooking.
Beat a lot while cooling.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and coarsely chop. Drain pimento and reserve 2 teaspoons.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Sprinkle pecans and coconut in buttered cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Prepare cake mix according to package.
Spoon into pan. Combine remaining ingredients in mixer bowl.
Beat until smooth. Spoon evenly over cake, leaving 1-inch edge.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.
Invert squares on plates.
Cream cheese will sink to bottom during baking to form frosting.

title: crispy pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and cover with a solution of pickling lime and water.
Let soak for 24 hours.
Rinse well and cover with cold, clear water.
Soak for 3 hours.
Drain and cover with remaining mixture.
Soak overnight.
The next morning, boil pickles in the mixture for 35 minutes.
Put in jars; these pickles will be nice and crisp.

title: calabacitas
directions: Saute zucchini and onion until just done.
Add 1 can whole kernel corn, drained.
Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add 1 clove garlic.
Simmer.
Just before serving, sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese over and chopped tomato for color and garnish.

title: canned slaw
directions: Grate onions, peppers, carrots and cabbage.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup salt over mixture and let stand for 2 hours.
Wash off real good.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Place in 12-quart saucepan and cover with water.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until tender. Sample beans while cooking and add water as needed.

title: curried liver and onions
directions: Tip:
The liver will cut into strips easier if you plate the slices on waxed paper-lined cookie sheet and put in freezer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, evaporated milk and syrup over medium heat until it forms a soft ball in cold water; remove from heat. Add butter, vanilla and peanut butter. Beat until thick. Pour into butter-greased pan. Cool and cut into pieces.

title: eggplant caviar
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut eggplants in half lengthwise and place on a baking sheet with their cut-sides facing down.
Bake for 20 minutes or until they are fork-tender.
Take eggplants out of oven and remove the pulp from the skin.
Puree pulp in a blender. Spoon into a medium bowl.
Combine eggplant pulp with remaining ingredients.
Serve at room temperature or chill for 1 hour. Yield:
4 servings.
Preparation Time:
15 minutes.
Cooking Time: 20 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt the butter in a large frying pan.
Add the brown sugar; spread evenly over bottom of pan.
Lay complete wheel of pineapple in center.
Put cherry in center; place half wheels around.

title: all-purpose barbecue sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a large kettle and bring to a boil. Turn down and simmer for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 gallon.
Good on anything.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix soup, milk, mustard and pepper.
Stir cooked macaroni and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle rest of cheese and onions.
Bake 5 minutes more to melt cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: microwave glazed carrot coins
directions: Add all ingredients in microwave-safe bowl.
Heat on High 2 to 3 minutes in the microwave.
Stir and serve.
Serves 4.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except chips in a large bowl; mix well. Pour into a buttered dish, cover with chips. Bake at 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: rich beef stew with rice
directions: Dredge meat in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in fat.
Add bones, if any; add water and tomato sauce.
Simmer 2 1/2 hours, covered.
Add vegetables and cook until tender.
Remove meat and vegetables; stir flour-water paste into liquid.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Serve over meat and vegetables with hot rice.

title: creamed new potatoes
directions: Scrape or brush skin from new potatoes.
Place in pot and add enough water to cover potatoes about halfway.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add milk.

title: cheddar-zucchini puff
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook zucchini, covered, in a small amount of boiling water for 3 to 5 minutes or until tender.
Drain well. Spread evenly into an 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking dish.
In a bowl, combine sour cream, egg yolk, flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir in cheese.
In a bowl, beat egg white until stiff peaks form (tips stand straight).
Fold beaten egg white into sour cream mixture. Spoon atop zucchini.
In a small bowl, combine bread crumbs and melted margarine.
Sprinkle over egg mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.
Makes 6 servings.

title: freezer sweet corn
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large kettle.
Simmer for 5 to 7 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into large, shallow containers to cool.
Stir occasionally.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy; add eggs and beat one minute.
Put cocoa and food coloring in a cup and make a paste; add to shortening mixture.
Add salt to buttermilk and add with flour to the other mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Fold in vinegar and soda; mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in 9-inch pans.

title: coconut delight(in a blender)
directions: Put all ingredients except coconut in a blender.
Grease 9-inch deep pie pan and preheat oven to 350°.
Blend for 3 minutes.
Pour into pie pan and let set for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups coconut on top and bake for 40 minutes.

title: salsa marinara(marinara sauce)
directions: In a 3 to 4-quart saucepan, set over medium heat, warm the oil for one minute.
Add the onion, garlic and parsley.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Add the tomatoes and crush them with the back of a wooden spoon.
Add the oregano and the basil; stir well to combine.

title: microwave fruit upside-down cake
directions: Use 1/2 box cake mix and 1/2 of required ingredients on box (but use only 1 egg).
Pour over the already mixed crushed pineapple and brown sugar.
I use the juice also.
Microwave for 4 to 4 1/2 minutes.
Rotate and bake 4 1/2 minutes more.
Use 8-inch square dish, uncovered.
May look undone, but will finish cooking while resting.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let set overnight in refrigerator. Drain well before serving.

title: jo ann's cheese pie with self crust
directions: Beat softened cream cheese until light and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until thick, smooth and lemon colored.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan (greased 1/2 inch short of top).
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Wash carrots and cut into 3 x 1/2-inch strips. Place in saucepan. Add salt and hot water to cover carrots. Cook until tender; drain and add butter, vinegar and sugar. Cook slowly until transparent. Serve hot. Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: norma's potato salad
directions: Boil peeled and diced potatoes in water with a little salt. While the potatoes are still hot, mix salad oil and red wine vinegar and pour over.
Add salt and pepper and mix together.
Put mixture in refrigerator overnight.
The next morning, add diced onion, pickles, celery and chopped boiled eggs.
Then mix together some mayonnaise, mustard and pickle juice according to your own tastes and mix that in with the potatoes until they are as moist as desired.

title: lazy pigs in the blanket
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in saucepan in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add ground beef and brown lightly.
Drain off fat. Season to taste.
Place half the shredded cabbage in a casserole. Add the meat mixture and cover with remaining cabbage.
Pour sauce on top and spread evenly.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: golden punch(breakfast drink)
directions: Prepare orange juice and lemonade according to directions on can.
Add apricot nectar and pineapple juice.
Chill well.
To serve, stir in Sprite and pour over ice.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown and drain ground beef, sausage and onion.
Add spaghetti sauce and mushrooms.
Let simmer on low for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: corn casserole ii
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion in butter.
Mix in corn, rice, pimento and sugar.
Place in a 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: fruit cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, pineapples and pudding.
Mix well. Make into a ball.
Roll in finely chopped nuts.
Serve with cinnamon graham crackers.

title: squash pickles
directions: Sprinkle squash and onions with salt and set aside for 1 hour. Bring all other ingredients to full boil.
Drain salt from squash and onions.
Add squash and onions to vinegar mixture and bring to full boil.
Pack in sterile jars and seal.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in baking dish. Bake at 350°, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: "breakfast the morning after" quiche
directions: Brown sausage.
Cube or break bread in an oblong baking dish. Place sausage on top of bread.
Mix eggs, salt and milk in a bowl. Pour mixture over the bread and sausage.
Top with cheese. Mixture will be soupy.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes the following morning.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cut cherries and pineapple in half.
Mix fruit and flour. Cream butter and sugar; add beaten eggs and flavorings.
Combine with fruit and nuts.
Line greased 9-inch tube pan with brown paper.
Grease paper also.
Pour mixture in pan.
Bake at 300° until done (2 to 2 1/2 hours).
Cool on rack for 1/2 hour.
Remove paper.
Cool completely and store.

title: stir-fry
directions: Chop cabbage, peppers, onion and vegetables.
Cook in wok or big skillet.
Slice smoked sausage and add to mixture.
Pour over cooked rice or Oriental noodles.
Top with soy sauce.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pistachio pudding with undrained pineapple.
Add Cool Whip, nuts and marshmallows.

title: potato "shape-up" soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Put with chicken broth in saucepan. Bring to a boil; simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Add cucumber; cook 3 to 5 minutes more.
Pour 1/2 soup into a blender.
On low speed, blend smooth.
Pour into 2-quart container.
Blend remaining soup with seasoning and yogurt.
Add to the first half. Mix well.
Chill.

title: puppy chow (snack)
directions: Melt together chocolate chips, butter and peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Coat Rice Chex with mixture.
In paper bag, place cereal and powdered sugar and shake.

title: graham cracker crust pie
directions: Mix all together; put in pie crust.
Makes two pies.

title: tangy spaghetti pizza pie
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to package directions using salt and
boiling
water;
drain.
Stir	in
margarine
until melted; stir in eggs and package of
grated
Parmesan cheese. Transfer mixture to a greased 9 1/2-inch deep
dish pie plate; use a spoon to	form
mixture
into
a	pie
shell.
Carefully spread bottom with Ricotta cheese.

title: lemon-orange beverage
directions: Reconstitute beverage as directed on can.
Combine the soft drink mix, sugar, orange beverage and water in a pitcher.
Stir until the sugar dissolves.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: bessie's white fruit cake
directions: Use 1/3 of the flour to coat fruit and nuts.
Cream butter and sugar.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add eggs, one at a time, with 3 tablespoons flour, to creamed mixture.
Add 1/2 cup pineapple juice and the rest of flour.
Add fruit and nuts; mix well.
Bake in prepared tube pan for 3 hours at 275°.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Chop stems in small pieces and saute in butter.
Saute sausage and drain well.
Mix cream cheese and dressing mix; add sausage and stems.
Stuff mushroom caps with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: 5-minute fudge
directions: Add butter, milk, sugar and salt in saucepan over medium heat.
Cook 4 or 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Start timing when it begins to bubble.
Remove from heat, stir in chocolate, marshmallows, vanilla and nuts.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute. Pour in buttered pan and let cool.
Then cut in squares.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: cake squares
directions: Mix and bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight or at least 8 to 10 hours.

title: irish potato cake
directions: Using mixer, combine the first 6 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans at 325° until done (toothpick inserted in center of cake should come out clean).
Remove from oven and let set 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool.
Frost.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Mix together the peaches, sugar, flour and nutmeg; pour into pie shell.
Pour heavy cream over top.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: 15 minute spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onions and green peppers.
Cook until tender.
Stir in barbecue sauce and soup.
Simmer 5 minutes or heated through.
Prepare spaghetti as directed on box.
Serve meat sauce over spaghetti.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Peel and mash avocados.
Add salt and lemon juice.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: In a 2-quart baking dish, dump pie filling, next pineapple (drained) onto pie filling.
Next, dump box of cake mix on top, then pour stick of melted margarine on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Add nuts, if desired.

title: spanish tortilla
directions: Pour 1/4 cup of olive oil and garlic cloves, minced, into frypan.
Cook over medium heat for about a minute.
Place thinly sliced potatoes and chopped onions in frypan and cook for 4 to 5m minutes until soft.
Beat 6 eggs in separate bowl; pour cooked potatoes and onions into eggs.
Let mixture sit for 20 minutes to cool.
Put remaining 1/4 cup of olive oil in cool pan at medium heat for about a minute.
Pour in mixture and cook until edges are cooked.
When you are able to lift the edge of the tortilla, it is time to flip the mixture onto the other side.
Cook for another 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove to a serving dish and keep warm.
Tortilla can be eaten hot, warm or cold.
Serves 4.

title: spinach salad
directions: Tear spinach in bite size pieces.
Mix all together and serve.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In a large bowl, mash enough berries to equal 3 cups.
In a saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in the mashed berries and water; mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; pour into a large bowl and chill for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until mixture is just slightly warm.
Fold in the remaining berries.
Pile into pie shell; chill for 2 to 3 hours. In small mixing bowl, whip cream until soft peaks form.
Sprinkle pudding mix over cream and whip until stiff.
Pipe around edge of pie.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown ground beef in bacon drippings.
Mix in garlic powder and onion; saute.
When beef is browned, add bell pepper and tomatoes or sauce.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Then add beans, juice, salt and pepper.
Cook about 20 minutes. Add chili powder and Chili-O mix.
Simmer to blend flavors.

title: stuffing
directions: Place bread in mixing bowl.
Add milk, the bread should absorb all the milk, so there is none left in the bowl.
Mix lightly and spoon into aluminum bread tin; do not pack.
Wrap in 2 thicknesses of aluminum foil.
Place in center of oven, preheated to 325°. Bake 2 1/2 hours.
Then open foil and bake until top is lightly browned, about 15 minutes.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender until very well mixed. Store in refrigerator (covered) or in jar for up to 1 week.

title: garlic spaghetti
directions: Boil a large pot of water, containing a few shakes of salt and a drop of olive oil.
Crush the garlic cloves or slice them paper thin into a skillet containing the olive oil.

title: black bottom cups
directions: Combine cream cheese, unbeaten egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt and mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips into the cream cheese mixture.
In another bowl, sift the following together: flour, 1 cup sugar, cocoa, baking soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add the remaining ingredients to the flour mixture.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: In double boiler, melt chocolate, butter, salt and sugar.
Stir in milk; cook until thick.
Add vanilla.
Heat before serving. Makes 4 cups.
Will keep in fridge several weeks.
Serve over any ice cream; especially good over peppermint ice cream.

title: mixed vegetable fry
directions: Combine all ingredients in skillet.
Cook until all vegetables are cooked.

title: currant or raisin tea biscuits
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add to mixture the Crisco, milk and egg.
Stir until well mixed batter. Add currants or raisins.
Mix by hand.
Drop by tablespoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake approximately 12 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: better butter
directions: Equally divide the whipping cream into 2 (2 1/2 pint) jars with screw on lids.
Shake the jars as hard as you can until butter forms.
Use a spoon to dip the butter into a bowl.
Stir in a dash of salt.
Spread on hot bread.
Extra good with a little honey.

title: chocolate covered cherry cookies
directions: Mix margarine, egg, vanilla and sugar.
Add flour, cocoa, soda and powder.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Press center with thumb.
Place cherry in center.
Melt chocolate chips, sweetened condensed milk and cherry juice (from maraschino cherries).
Spoon 1 teaspoon frosting over each cherry. Spread to cover.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: m&m crispie treats
directions: Melt together marshmallows, margarine, peanut butter and salt in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally, until smooth.
Pour over combined cereal and candies, tossing lightly until thoroughly coated.
With greased fingers, gently shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Insert popsicle stick.
Place on waxed paper. Cool at room temperature until set.
(Use same recipe, to make square treats also!)

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour half of batter into hot skillet.
Top with cheese.
Add remaining batter.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: party mix
directions: Combine the first six ingredients.
Melt remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Pour over and mix well.
Put in oven at 200° in flat pan for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: rice krispie caramel bars
directions: Melt 1/4 cup margarine, 1 bag caramels and milk.
Keep warm. Prepare Rice Krispie treats by melting 1 cup margarine and marshmallows.
Pour marshmallow mixture over rice cereal.
Place 1 layer of cereal mixture in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour caramel mixture over this and put another layer of cereal mixture over this.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: aunt nene's butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs and vanilla and add to mixture.
Gradually add flour with baking powder.
Add milk gradually as mixture gets too hard.
Bake until brown at 375°.

title: election night stew
directions: Brown meat, onion and rice in a skillet or saucepan.
Stir in water, tomatoes, salt, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and pepper.
Simmer about 1 hour or until rice is done.
Add beans. Heat through and serve.
Serves 4 or can be doubled for 8.

title: easy pumpkin pies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 2 pie crusts in oven and brown for about 7 minutes.
Melt margarine, then mix in eggs and sugar, then add milk, pudding, spice and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together mixing pudding mix last.
Drop onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes and no longer.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients in square cake pan.
Make 3 holes and in each hole, put vanilla, vinegar and salad oil.
Pour 1 cup cold water over entire pan.
Mix together with fork.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until well blended.
Slice apples and serve.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice enough cucumbers fairly thick to fill gallon jar; add salt and cover with water.
Put in refrigerator; next morning, drain but don't wash.
Mix together jar of vinegar (finish filling with water); add sugar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Bring to boil; add cucumbers and bring back to boil.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam. Thaw potatoes 1/2 hour before putting together. In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together. Put into sprayed pan and sprinkle with smashed potato chips. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: uncooked relish
directions: Grind tomatoes, onions and green peppers.
Add 1 cup salt and let set overnight.
Next morning, drain out all liquid through a cloth bag.
To the pulp, add the vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Pack in jars of any size you like.
Close tight but you can't seal since it is cold.
This will keep indefinitely.

title: bean salad
directions: Garnish with hot peppers over bed of lettuce.
Set overnight for best results.

title: beans a'la brenda
directions: Wash beans; trim ends and remove strings.
Cut in half crosswise.
Saute garlic and onion in oil; remove garlic and discard.
Add beans and remaining ingredients; cover and cook, over medium heat, 25 minutes, or until beans are tender.
Add 1 tablespoon additional water, if necessary.
Yields 6 servings.

title: ground beef quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Let pie shell stand at room temperature for 10 minutes, then prick bottom and sides of crust with fork. Bake just until crust begins to brown, about 5 minutes. Let cool.

title: chicken breast almondine
directions: In skillet, saute almonds in melted margarine until golden brown (5 minutes).
Remove almonds from margarine and set aside. Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dust chicken with mixture and shake off excess.
Stir rosemary into margarine left in skillet. Over medium heat, brown chicken on both sides.
Stir in wine and cover.
Cover over low heat for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove chicken to platter and sprinkle with almonds.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together, then add flours and fruit cocktail.
Pour into floured pan.
Bake at 425° until done.
Then cook nuts, butter, sugar and cream for about 10 minutes after it comes to a rolling boil; pour this mixture over hot cake.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: dirt
directions: Blend cookies in blender to a powder or dirt like state.
Set aside in separate bowl.

title: pineapple bread pudding(stuffing)
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add the beaten eggs, crushed pineapple (after draining) and bread (crusts removed and cut into cubes).
Bake in a casserole bowl at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 8 to 10.
Great with ham dinner.

title: bean pot
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Cook bacon and crumble.
Drain 1/2 liquid from each can beans.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy oriental spaghetti
directions: Boil noodles until just tender; drain and serve accompanied by soy sauce and bowls of chopped eggs, veggies and meats to be sprinkled on top of each person's portion of noodles according to their taste.
Can be made in any quantity.

title: tidewater poppy seed slaw(12 servings)
directions: In large bowl, toss together the cabbage, onion, peppers and sugar.
In small saucepan, whisk together the oil, vinegar, dry mustard, poppy seed, salt, dry mustard and cream.
Bring to boil over medium-high heat, stirring constantly.
Simmer for 2 minutes. Pour hot dressing over cabbage mixture, tossing well. Refrigerate salad at least 12 hours to let flavors mellow.
Serve chilled on a bed of red cabbage leaves for contrast, if desired.

title: mushroom burgers
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter and place in bowl.
Add all ingredients.
Stir very well.
Make patties and fry in oil.

title: "black cookies"(chocolate peanut butter chip cookies)
directions: In large bowl, cream shortening, sugar (can use 1/2 white and 1/2 brown sugar), eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients; add alternately with milk, mixing well.
Chill dough.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry brulee
