directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sour cream and sugar; blend thoroughly.
Slice berries and sweeten to taste.
Arrange in shallow overproof serving dish.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over berries and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Place on lowest broiler rack and broil until sugar bubbles and browns lightly.
Serve at once.

title: pork with mushrooms
directions: Salt the meat slices and turn them in the flour.
Heat the oil. Add the meat and fry until pink on both sides.
Clean the mushrooms; cut into slices and add to the meat.
Cook, covered, on a medium flame until the meat is done (approximately 15 minutes). Take out the meat and continue cooking the mushrooms until the liquid evaporates.
Add the heavy cream and half of the sour cream and mix thoroughly.
(If the sauce is too thin, add a bit of cornstarch.)
Put the meat back in the pan and cook with the mushrooms for a minute or two.
Serve with rice or potatoes with leftover sour cream in a separate bowl.

title: mom's brownies
directions: In small pan over low heat, melt butter.
Add cocoa, stirring, until well blended.
In mixing bowl, beat together eggs and sugar. Add flour, mixing well.
Add butter/cocoa mixture.
Pour into standard cake pan.
Bake at 350° until brownies pull away from sides of pan.

title: shrimp cheese english muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Spread on halved English muffins.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until browned.
Can be frozen for later use.

title: snicker or caramel cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Melt caramels, oleo and milk.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour 1/2 of cake batter.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°, then pour caramel mix over the baked part of cake.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour rest of cake batter over caramel mix.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350° or until cake tests done.
Can save out a little caramel and spread a thin glaze over top of hot cake, if desired.

title: quick and easy breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread and place pieces in greased baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Brown and drain bulk sausage; drain off fat.
Spoon over bread.
Sprinkle with grated sharp cheese.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips.
Stir in Rice Krispies until coated.
Press in bottom and sides of buttered pie pan. Chill 30 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in 9x13 inch cake pan.
Mix 1 yellow cake mix and 2 eggs (this will be stiff); pat into butter.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as directed on package, adding extra cup of sugar.
Freeze mixture until slushy.
Pour into punch bowl and add juice and ginger ale.
Serves 32 people.

title: low-fat yogurt creamy dressing
directions: May add 2 tablespoons of pectin to make more creamy.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix first four ingredients in small mixing bowl.
Pull stems off of mushrooms and fill caps with mixture.
Broil about 6 inches from heat for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased black iron skillet. Batter will be real thick.
Bake at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line bottom of a large ovenware pan (disposable aluminum deep-sided cake pan) with crust up the sides also.
Lightly brown crust in oven and set aside.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift together first five ingredients.
Mix together by hand, eggs, Crisco and sliced strawberries.
Pour liquid ingredients into dry.
Stir only until moistened.
Add nuts.
Stir gently until mixed.
Pour into 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans or 4 small, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.
(Can be frozen.)

title: smash cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in pecans. Pour over the mixture in pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; cool and debone and tear into small pieces. Cook broccoli as package directs; drain.
Layer broccoli on the bottom of lightly oiled casserole dish.
Layer chicken on broccoli.

Melt cheese, soup and sour cream over low heat, stirring frequently and pour over broccoli and chicken layers. Cover with bread crumbs that can or cannot be lightly toasted. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: toll house raisin sauce
directions: Mix well and bring to a boil.
Add cornstarch in small amount of cold water.
Stir until slightly thick.
Serve hot on ham, etc.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Break noodles in bite-size pieces and boil until tender. Brown hamburger meat and drain. Layer following in casserole dish: noodles, meat, spaghetti sauce, Mozzarella cheese, Cheddar cheese, Swiss cheese and pepperoni. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Put sugar in Wesson oil; beat, then add a little vinegar at a time and continue to beat.
Add the rest of the ingredients slowly.

title: tree-mendous chicken soup(april, 1995)
directions: It is a good idea to cook with a glass of wine in one hand however, that is not essential to the soup.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add flour, vanilla and milk; beat well.
Pour into crusts.
Bake until golden brown in 350° oven.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix tomatoes, soup, broth, onion and spices and cook 10 minutes.
Add chicken.
In a large dish, layer chicken mixture, Doritos and cheese.
Repeat until all is used.
Bake at 325° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: country style chicken kiev
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In heavy 2-quart saucepan, melt butter. Meanwhile, on piece of wax paper combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, basil, oregano, garlic salt and salt.
Dip chicken breasts in melted butter, then roll in crumbs to coat.
Place skin side up in greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake in 375° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until golden brown and chicken is tender. Meanwhile, add wine, green onion and parsley to remaining melted butter (about 1/2 cup).
When chicken is golden brown, pour butter sauce mixture around and over.
Return to oven for 3 to 5 minutes more or until sauce is hot.
Serve with sauce spooned over.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook prepared squash (or use canned squash) and onion in enough water to cover for 8 to 15 minutes.
When tender, drain and mash.
Add other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake in a long, buttered casserole dish for 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 8.

title: waldorf salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Toss lightly to coat.
Spoon into large lettuce-lined bowl.

title: kentucky blackberry jam cake
directions: Cook raisins in pint of water with 2 teaspoons of sugar.
Add soda to juice.
Put raisins in mixing bowl with rest of ingredients.
Add juice and stir well.
Add flour gradually until mixture is thick.
Add jam.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Be sure to flour the bottom of the pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until done.

title: whaddayacallits
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil in a saucepan.
Add peanut butter, and stir.
Stir in cereal, and spread in a 13x9-inch pan. Combine morsels, and sprinkle over top.
Cut into bars.

title: strawberry glaze
directions: Cook until clear (first 3 ingredients).
Add jello.
Cool. Add fresh strawberries.
Can pour over pound cake or angel food or ice cream.
Can also top with whipped cream if you wish.

title: potato swiss bake
directions: Mix together.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn up to brown top.

title: coffee punch
directions: Combine coffee, rum and salt.
Add ice cream and whipping cream; stir gently.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Yields 9 cups.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: About 4 hours before serving or the day ahead:
Into a large bowl, measure flour, margarine, cream of tartar, baking soda, salt, vanilla extract, eggs and 1 1/4 cups sugar.
With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until well blended, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Shape dough into a ball.
Wrap with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate dough 2 hours or until easy to handle.

title: cheese n wiener crescents
directions: Cut cheese into 6 strips each.
Slit hot dogs down center top to within 1/2 inch of ends (don't cut through).
Stuff cheese into slit and wrap crescent triangle around each.
Bake, topped with another cheese strip, 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar.
Beat until smooth. Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda and add alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and nuts. Fold in egg whites that have been beaten until stiff.
Grease and flour 3 cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pineapple icebox surprise
directions: Save enough crackers for 6 layers.
Crush remaining crackers. Cook oleo, sugar and pineapple until sugar dissolves.
Add nuts and the crushed crackers to mixture.
Let mixture cool before making layers.
Alternate layer of crackers and layer of mixture until you have used the 6 layers of crackers.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate.
Can be frozen.
Slice and serve.

title: lemonade dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Pat mixture into cake pan. (Reserve a few crumbs for top.)
Gently combine remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into cake pan covering cracker crust. Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: italian hazelnut delights
directions: Cream butter, sugar and honey.
Add wine and blend well.
Add nuts and flour.
Knead dough until smooth.
Pinch off pieces of dough the size of a walnut and roll into balls.
Place on a greased cookie sheet, 1 inch apart, and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and roll in confectioners sugar while still hot.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: sweet and sour kraut
directions: Brown bacon in skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon.
Add onion and red pepper to bacon grease and saute.
Mix kraut, brown sugar browned onion, bacon, etc.
Cook in moderate oven or on top of stove 30 to 40 minutes.
It keeps 6 weeks or longer.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Thaw spinach.
Mix spinach and all other ingredients in mixing bowl and stir until well mixed.
Bake in oven at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pita chips with zaatar "thyme"
directions: Cut pita into small squares and place on baking sheet.
Mix zaatar and olive oil with your hands and spread on each piece of bread.
Back in oven at 400° F for 15 minutes or until brown and crispy.

title: christmas date nut loaf
directions: Leave dates and nuts whole.
Sift flour, sugar and baking powder together.
Sprinkle on dates and nuts.
Mix with hands to cover dates and nuts.
Add water to egg whites and beat until very stiff.
Add egg yolks to dry mixture.
Add vanilla and fold in egg whites and mix well.
Line loaf pan with brown paper.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Test for doneness after 45 minutes.
Serve plain or with vanilla ice cream.
Will keep for weeks.

title: raisin pie
directions: Wash raisins and soak in cold water for 3 hours.
Drain; combine 2 cups water, raisins, sugar and flour.
Also mix together with salt, lemon juice and rind and egg.
Mix thoroughly and cook over hot water for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Let cool. Pour into empty pie shell; cover with dough strips, crisscrossed. Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 more minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In a bowl, mix sugar, flour, soda and cinnamon.
Then add 1/2 cup buttermilk and eggs.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil 2 sticks butter or margarine, cold water and 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Pour mixture in saucepan into mixture in bowl; mix well.
Pour into greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: mississippi caviar
directions: Drain peas and add other ingredients.
This will keep in the refrigerator for a couple of weeks.
Serve with scoop fritos.

title: holiday turkey dressing
directions: Mix well and put dressing in turkey loosely.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in baking dish.
Mix all ingredients except pineapple together in a bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, covered (with aluminum foil), for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil and continue baking, uncovered, 1/2 hour.
Drained pineapple may be added during the last 1/2 hour.

title: "brett's approved" potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes, onion and celery.
Cook in salt water, 15 to 20 minutes.
You may drain part of water off if you like.
With hand potato masher, mash part of potatoes, leaving some whole or small pieces.
Add milk to desired thickness.
Salt and pepper to taste. Add margarine; sprinkle with dried parsley.
Vary the amount of ingredients according to people to serve.

title: taste-a-cake (easy gobs)(very good)
directions: Bake in two jelly roll pans. Line one pan with wax paper. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Makes about 45 squares.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O in hot water.
Add juice from pineapple. Let cool and add pineapple.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend the margarine and grated cheese.
Work in the dry ingredients.
Press the cheese dough around the olives so you have many small balls.
Freeze.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove to paper towels.
Serve warm.

title: puffed ball doughnuts
directions: Mix ingredients and spoon off teaspoon into hot oil. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: parmesan cheese sauce
directions: Melt margarine over
low
heat	in heavy saucepan.
Add flour, stirring constantly
until	smooth.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk while stirring.
Cook until thickened and bubbly.
Stir
in cheese, mustard and salt until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat.

title: peach delight
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir peanut butter, sugar and eggs in a bowl until blended (it will be sticky).
With floured hands, roll level measuring tablespoonfuls into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes until cookies look dry and tops are crackled.

title: sticky buns
directions: Melt together butter, syrup and sugar.
Put it in bottom of baking dish.
Roll out dough.
Spread butter, cinnamon and sugar on dough.
Cut into slices.
Put slices in pan and let rise, then bake at 375° until brown.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat oil in large Dutch oven of frying pan.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook slowly until onion is clear.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer gently over very low heat for 30 minutes.
Serve with or without meatballs over cooked pasta.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Cream cocoa, butter and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch greased pan for 20 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: apple burritoesnederland, texas
directions: Heat ingredients until melted.
Put apple pie filling in flour tortilla.
Roll and place in pan.
Put boiled mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: low calorie turkey divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Place in an 8-inch square baking pan (spray with Pam).
Place turkey slices on top of broccoli.
Preheat oven to 400°.

title: easy beef casserole
directions: Mix beef, seasoned salt and catsup.
Shape into 16 balls. Brown in greased ovenproof skillet.
Add peas and onions; dot with butter.
Mix soup and pimento together; pour over meat mixture. Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve over buttered noodles or rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Make patties; put potatoes, onion and cheese on top or bottom of hamburger patties.
Put in aluminum foil.
Fold foil over the patties; bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes about 6 large patties.

title: sesame street potatoes
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese, soups, green pepper, onion, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add thawed potatoes; mix.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with sesame seed and paprika.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop the corn to make 1 1/2 gallons.
Combine brown sugar, margarine and corn syrup; cook until well blended.
Add cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
(This mixture becomes foamy and increases in volume.)
Pour hot mixture over popcorn; stir well.

title: coconut nut puffs
directions: Place the coconut under the oven broiler and brown delicately.
Melt marshmallows in the top of a double boiler, stirring frequently.
This will take about 15 minutes.
Dip each nut in melted marshmallow and then roll in the browned coconut. These are best the day they are made.
Makes about 30 small puffs.

title: hamburger cabbage fry
directions: Peel and fry potatoes in large skillet.
Crumble and fry hamburger.
Season potatoes and hamburger to taste.
When the potatoes are almost done, cut up the cabbage in pieces, about an inch wide and 2 to 3 inches long.
Fry in butter until tender.
Add the hamburger and cabbage to the potatoes and mix.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Saute green peppers and garlic in oil in a large skillet over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Remove pepper and garlic to plate. Add chicken to skillet; cook until brown on all sides, about 8 minutes.
Drain and discard fat.
Add cooking sauce, basil, salt and ground pepper to skillet; stir in green peppers and garlic. Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, until chicken is tender 45 to 50 minutes.

title: stir-fry beef
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
Coat with Kitchen Bouquet and let stand 30 minutes.
Brown strips in oil.
Add chopped onion, pepper, tomatoes, salt and cook slow until tender, covered, approximately 40 minutes.

title: decorator icing
directions: Mix water, crisco, and flavorings in a large mixing bowl. Gradually add sugar a little at a time, folding until all is mixed in. Add the other 1/4 c (*water as needed). You want this to be thick. When all is folded in, now is time to use an electric mixer. Whip thoroughly. If making flowers, divide out a portion and add more sugar to it. This really needs to be thick.

title: tennessee chess pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add butter and cream well. Add eggs and beat, then add evaporated milk and vanilla. Stir until well blended. Pour into shell and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Pie will be slightly less than firm but will set as it cools. Cool completely before cutting.

title: deer stroganoff
directions: Dredge meat in flour and garlic mixture.
Saute in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Set aside.
Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Mix gravy according to package directions; mix with meat, mushrooms and sour cream on low until hot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and onion; add teaspoon of salt.
Cook about 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add butter, sour cream, soup, pepper and crushed crackers.
Pour in buttered casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Sprinkle dressing on cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie(from king's arms tavern, williamsburg, virginia)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare pie shell.
Beat eggs lightly. Add sugar, salt, corn syrup, cooled butter and vanilla; stir until mixed well.
Spread pecan halves on crust.
Cover with filling. Place in oven and immediately reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes, or until firm in the center.
Cool before serving.

title: fluffy sauce
directions: Combine mandarin juice, mandarin peel, lemon juice, sugar and beaten egg yolks in a saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, over a low flame until thick.
Remove sauce from the burner, let cool a little.
Whip the egg whites until stiff, add salt.
Fold egg whites into the sauce, add vanilla.
Serve over pound cake or fresh fruit.
This sauce can be served warm or cold.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle with parsley. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until top is golden.
Serve with crackers or as a side dish.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients until fluffy.
Add eggs.
Beat well. Add flour and baking soda at low speed.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool on cookie sheet.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: crispix mix
directions: Melt chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter.
Pour over Crispix and mix well but gently.
Dump this mixture into a large bag with 2 cups powdered sugar.
Toss around gently to mix.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and beat until creamy. Add raisins; mix in well. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Melt marshmallows on top, if desired.

title: apple sour cream ring
directions: In small bowl combine nuts, cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar; set aside.
Thinly
slice apples; set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°. Grease
a
9-inch tube pan.
Beat oleo with 1 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour and remaining ingredients. Beat
at low
speed	until
blended.
Constantly scrape bowl. Increase speed
to
medium;	beat
3 minutes.
Spread half of batter in pan.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of nut mixture, then sliced apples. Sprinkle
apples
with
of
nut mixture.
Spread evenly
with remaining	batter.
Sprinkle
with remaining nut mixture.	Bake for
to
minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: gina's popcorn cake
directions: Grease angel food cake pan with butter or margarine.
Mix popped popcorn, candy and peanuts in a large bowl.
Melt butter, oil and marshmallows in pan.
Pour over popcorn mixture, then mix quickly and pour into angel food pan.
Remove from pan when cool! Slice!

title: green peas and sauteed jicama
directions: Cut jicama into small cubes and blanch in boiling water for 1 1/2 minutes.
Drain.
In a saucepan, melt butter and add green peas, stirring until all are coated with butter.
Add jicama and seasonings; simmer over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until jicama and peas are tender.
Jicama remains slightly crisp. Serves 4 to 6.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together except the crackers and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix the crackers and margarine, spread over casserole and bake 15 minutes more.

title: brown and serve rolls
directions: Put 2 cups warm water in bowl; add yeast, sugar and salt.
Beat well.
Add shortening and egg and beat.
Add 2 cups flour and beat. Then add rest of flour.
Use spoon to mix in the last 4 cups of flour because it it too heavy to beat with eggbeater.

title: quickie
directions: Drain mushrooms.
Mix and put in casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies with kisses
directions: Mix all the ingredients except the candy Kisses.
Shape into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Put a Kiss in the middle of each cookie.
Press firmly.
Bake a minute or so more.

title: stacy's chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: alabama slammers
directions: Mix in shaker. Serve in shot glasses.

title: honey ambrosia
directions: Mix orange juice, honey and lemon juice in a medium bowl. Gently stir in oranges, banana and coconut.

title: aunt nan's drunkin dogs
directions: Mix brown sugar, catsup and bourbon in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Parboil wieners for 2 minutes, then simmer in sauce.
Serve in a chafing dish.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Mix oats, brown sugar, flour, salt and melted butter. Spread half of mix in 8 x 8 greased dish. Spread cranberry sauce as a second layer, then spread other half of mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp scallop primavera
directions: Chop pepper and onion into medium size chunks.
Slice mushrooms.
Mince garlic; peel shrimp.
Rinse both shrimp and scallops and remove excess water.
Heat large frying pan (medium heat for range) and add olive oil.
Once the pan has heated, add garlic, pepper, onion and mushrooms.
Stir the vegetables while cooking for approximately 2 minutes.
Using a slotted spoon, remove the vegetables (to prevent overcooking), then add shrimp, scallops, black pepper, lemon pepper, Old Bay seasoning and sherry (optional).
Cook for approximately 5 minutes, or until shrimp and scallops are tender to the touch of the fork.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place all ingredients, except chocolate chips, in bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Add chocolate chips and turn into a well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake for 50 minutes to 1 hour. Let cool for 20 minutes and turn out of pan.

title: tender barbecue ribs
directions: Place sectioned ribs in a very large pot or boiler and cover ribs with water.
Add vinegar.
Bake ribs on high (400° to 450°) for 1 1/2 hours; turn ribs every 30 minutes.
When water has boiled down to 1 to 2 cups, pour 3/4 of bottle of barbecue sauce over ribs.
Bake another 1/2 hour.
Turn ribs every 10 minutes.
Take out and serve.

title: mini white castles(yield: 60)
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pack into a flat cookie sheet, prick entire surface with a fork.
Preheat oven to 400° and bake for 10 minutes.
Cool and cut into 60 squares.
Fit onto buns and put on a dill pickle slice on
each one and replace top of bun.
Place back in containers.
Sprinkle with water and cover with foil. Store in refrigerator until ready, then bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Can also be frozen.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium mixing bowl, beat egg yolks. Stir in sweetened condensed milk, ReaLemon and food coloring, if desired.
Pour into crust. Bake 8 minutes. Cool. Chill thoroughly. Top with whipped topping.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare stuffing, but cut down on the water so it's dry.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cook chicken.
Pick meat from bones. Place over stuffing.
Pour soup (undiluted) over stuffing and chicken.
Put frozen broccoli over soup. Add 3/4 of the cheese over the broccoli. Cover with onions. Add balance of cheese.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage and cheese appetizer
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix in Cheez Whiz.
Spread mixture onto bread and broil in oven until brown.

title: sharon's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, celery leaves, water and salt until chicken is tender.
Let cool.
Debone and cut into bite size pieces.
Discard all fat and skin.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs and pinch of salt.
Add oleo and sugar.
Stir well. Add vanilla, vinegar, pecans, coconut and raisins.
Bake at 350° until nice and brown and set.
Makes one 8-inch pie.

title: grandmoma hopson's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten egg, then peanut butter.
Add sifted flour and soda.
Add vanilla.
Pinch off small pieces.
Place on greased sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream the sugar, salt, butter and Crisco. Add eggs and beat well. Add flour and milk alternately. Stir in walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Start in cold oven. Set to 325°. Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes. Remove immediately to cool.

title: concoction
directions: *Garlic powder may be used.

title: meatza pie
directions: Mix together meat, milk, crumbs and garlic.
Press to bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Put 1/2 of tomato sauce over meat. On top of sauce, arrange mushrooms and Mozzarella cheese.
Pour the rest of sauce over cheese.
Sprinkle with oregano and grated cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: slush punch
directions: Steep tea bags in 2 cups boiling water. Boil sugar in 6 cups of water and cool. Combine tea, sugar water, lemonade, and orange juice. Add bourbon. Mix and freeze 24 hours or serve with ice.

title: grace's layered mexican dip
directions: There are no specific amounts for this dip.
Use any amount to make it as large or small as you wish.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Great for marinating chicken for barbecue.
Can also brush on chicken while cooking.

title: grandmother's barbecue chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly. Dip chicken pieces into barbecue sauce. Pour remaining sauce over chicken, then cook, covered, about 350° for an hour and a half.

title: goop
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Serve with corn chips or nacho chips.

title: snow-peak frosting
directions: Heat syrup to boiling in a small saucepan.
With electric mixer at high speed (or with egg beater) beat egg whites until they form soft peaks when beater is raised; add salt.
Slowly pour in syrup continuing to beat until frosting is fluffy and hangs in peaks from beater; fold in vanilla.
For spoon designs, beat until very stiff.
Stays soft at least 2 days.

title: pea 'n' cheese salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss lightly.
Serve on salad greens.
Yields 6 servings.

title: lemon delight
directions: Melt the margarine and mix in 1 cup pecans and flour; place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Cool for
about 15 minutes.

title: sweet pea salad
directions: Drain liquid off peas; empty into mixing bowl.
Add cubed cheese and celery.
Mix mayonnaise, drained pickles, onions and mustard.
Toss peas, cheese and celery lightly with mayonnaise mixture.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce cups.
Serves 6.

title: v. i. p. meal
directions: In a big skillet, heat oil and garlic over medium-high heat. Brown meat quickly, about 5 minutes.
Take meat out of skillet. Turn heat down to medium.
Cook onions, green pepper and mushrooms until tender.
Stir in flour, wine, tomato sauce and spices.
Heat to boil; keep stirring.
Boil and stir for a minute.
Reduce heat. Put meat back in.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice with green salad, bread and wine.

title: polish stew
directions: Dice all vegetables and then add the canned ingredients.
Cook approximately 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Soup can be thickened by adding 1/2 cup flour and water stirred in while cooking.

title: garden pie
directions: In a lightly greased 8 x 10-inch baking dish, layer vegetables. Sprinkle cheese and pepper over vegetables.
Combine milk, Bisquick and eggs.
Beat until smooth and pour over vegetables.
Bake for 30 minutes in 400° oven.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: grandma stacey's plum pudding
directions: Mix suet, flour, raisins, currants, 1/2 cup sugar, bread crumbs, eggs and flavorings together well.
Add a little milk to moisten if needed.
Place on floured cloth.
Tie securely, leaving room for expansion.
Boil gently for 5 hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in oven at 350°, about 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: easy dip
directions: Brown beef; add salt and drain. Melt cheese; add beef and Ro-Tel tomatoes.

title: lo-cal coffee jello
directions: Mix together the gelatin, sweetener and instant coffee.
Add 2 cups of the boiling water.
Stir and mix well to be sure that gelatin is softened.
Add remaining hot water.
Cool in refrigerator until firm.
Serve with reduced calorie Cool Whip.

title: bran muffins
directions: In a very
large
bowl	combine
bran
and cereal.
Add boiling water; stir
to moisten and let stand 10 minutes.
Add buttermilk.
Cream shortening
and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add	to
bran
mixture; stir until well blended.
Mix together flour, soda
and salt.
Add raisins to flour mixture. Stir into bran mixture.
Cover tightly with foil.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Fill
muffin tins lined with baking cups, 3/4 full. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: 4 in one casserole
directions: Form 6 patties of pork sausage and brown and cook thoroughly in skillet.
Reserve about 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Place apple slices on plate, covered with Saran Wrap.
In microwave, cook until just soft.
Save any juice.
Prepare mashed potatoes (I use Betty Crocker Potato Buds.)
Place the 6 sausage patties in casserole.
Top with apple rings.
Spread the undrained kraut over top.
Add a little of sausage drippings and apple juice to the top of the kraut.
Top with the mashed potatoes with a dab of butter over each patty section.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Bake in tube pan at 325° to 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Add one egg at a time, blending well.
Add 3 cups flour, a little at a time, and beat well.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix
peas, chestnuts, onion, pimento and cream of mushroom soup in a casserole dish.
Place grated cheese over pea mixture. Mix remaining ingredients and put on top of cheese. Bake in 400 degree oven for 20 minutes.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in buttered casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be topped with crushed potato chips and baked another 5 to 10 minutes.

title: snappy meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with honey mustard.

title: kentucky cole slaw
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate before serving.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut chicken, potatoes, carrots, celery, onion and broccoli into bite size pieces.
Put potatoes, carrots and celery in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Add onion and broccoli.
Cook an additional 5 minutes.
Drain vegies; set aside with peas until needed.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix carrots and melted margarine in a medium size bowl; set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder, sugar and cinnamon.
Add to carrot mixture.
Add eggs and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish (1 1/2-quart).
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 45 minutes.

title: double coconut cream pie
directions: Filling:
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in milk and cream of coconut.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick. Cook 2 more minutes.
Gradually stir in about 1 cup milk mixture into egg mixture.
Stir constantly.
Return to saucepan.
Cook and stir until bubbly and cook 2 more minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in butter, coconut and vanilla.

title: fruitcake cupcakes
directions: Combine fruit and nuts and dredge with flour.
In a bowl, add the cake mix, 1 egg, orange juice, lemon extract and salt.
Mix 2 minutes.
Add remaining eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Blend batter into fruit.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes as standard size cupcakes (use paper liners).
Yields 40.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Place all ingredients in a slow cooker or electric skillet and heat thoroughly.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch cake pan (ungreased), dump all above ingredients and mix together thoroughly with a fork; make sure the liquid is combined well with the dry ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs. Beat mixture. Add jam and mix well. Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk; add soda in water. Mix well and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: halibut
directions: Season halibut with salt and pepper to taste.
Grease a baking dish and put the onion and green onions on the bottom. Place the seasoned halibut over the onions. Spread the mayonnaise on the halibut.
Sprinkle the bread crumbs over the top.
Sprinkle with dill weed.
Bake at 350° for 20-30 minutes, or until halibut is flaky and crumbs are light brown.

title: german potato salad
directions: Mix the onion and bacon with cooked potatoes and set aside. Cook the water, sugar, cornstarch, vinegar and oil until thicken. Pour over potatoes and mix.
Serve.

title: broiled chicken casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish (about 8 x 10-inch). Mix vegetables and cream of chicken soup.
Spread bread crumbs over mixture. Sprinkle cheese on top of bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: sweet and sour broccoli
directions: Trim the leaves and coarse stem ends from the broccoli and cut the stems and florets into bite size pieces.
Bring about 1-inch of lightly salted water to a boil in a 3-quart saucepan.
Add the broccoli and cook, covered, for 5 minutes, or until crisp-tender. Drain well.

title: baked custard for two
directions: In a bowl, lightly beat the egg.
Add milk, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Pour into two ungreased custard cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Set in a pan containing 1/2 to 1-inch of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until set.

title: potluck casserole
directions: Brown onions and ground beef in skillet until onions are soft and beef is thoroughly cooked.
Stir in 3/4 cup cheese and add all remaining ingredients.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix together and let marinate.
You may add bacon bits or chopped, hard-boiled eggs or croutons.
If so, go a little lighter on the Good Seasons, maybe a half package might be plenty.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: pasta salad *
directions: Chop tomatoes (approximately 6 cups) in large bowl.
Add seasonings and oil.
Let stand several hours or overnight; return to room temperature.
Cook pasta.
Add 1/4 cup oil from tomatoes and Parmesan to hot pasta and toss.
Add 1/2 tomatoes; toss. Grate white cheese; add to pasta with rest of tomatoes.
Toss and serve.

title: pear pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla, flour and margarine until creamy. Put pear halves in unbaked pie shell.
Pour mixture over pears. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: vanilla fruit trifle
directions: Place 1/2 cake (cut up) in bottom of large bowl.
Sprinkle 1/2 Kahlua over cake.
Pour on 1/2 pudding; layer 1/2 fruit.
Add 1 container Cool Whip.
Repeat layers all over again.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chinese friday
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with Chinese noodles.
Saute celery, onion, green pepper, mushrooms, pimientos and water chestnuts. Place on noodles.
Mix together rest of ingredients and pour on top of vegetables.
Put more Chinese noodles on top with chopped cashews.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 400°.
In large bowl, combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Add apples.
Mix until apples are evenly coated.
Spoon into pie shell.

title: bourbon dogs
directions: Combine ingredients and beat for 25 minutes in saucepan or in 300° oven.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift the flour and sugar in a large bowl. In a saucepan, heat the butter, cocoa and Coca-Cola until they boil. Pour this over the flour and sugar mixture, then mix thoroughly. Mix in buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla and marshmallows, making a thin batter. Marshmallows will float to the top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: jam cake (3 layers)
directions: Sift spices with flour; cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add pineapple; continue beating.
Mix soda with buttermilk; add alternately with flour and first mixture.
Add jam and preserves.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes or until done. Makes 3 large layers; if you prefer, you can make half the recipe. Use any good caramel icing or using following:

title: red beans and rice
directions: Heat and serve over rice.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift dry ingredients and add to cream mixture.
Add bananas and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 275° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: heavenly hot pancake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda and salt together.
Mix beaten eggs with sour cream until combined.
Add to flour mixture.
Blend until slightly lumpy.
Makes 30 sliver dollar pancakes.
Serve with raspberry syrup.
So light you may want to double the recipe!

title: "blender" coconut pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender.
Mix 1 minute at low speed. Pour into greased 9-inch glass pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Chill or freeze.
Serves 8.

title: white chicken chili
directions: In a large saucepan, combine water, lemon pepper and cumin seed.
Bring to a boil.
Add chicken and reduce heat to low and simmer 20 to 30 minutes until chicken is fork-tender.

title: date loaf
directions: Mix dates, nuts and salt with flour and baking powder.
Beat eggs separately.
Add sugar to yolks.
Beat well and add whites. Pour in dry ingredients; work well.
Bake slowly for 1 1/2 hours in greased pan.
Line pan with wax paper.

title: margie's raspberry salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel crust.
Mix together jello, boiling water and raspberries and pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill until set up.

title: greek moussaka
directions: Saute onions in 2 tablespoons oil; add meat and brown.	Pour off fat.
Spoon in tomato paste.
Add water, wine, parsley, salt, pepper and paprika. Cook, covered, for 10 minutes.	Stir in 1/4 cup bread crumbs and mix well.
Slice eggplant, unpeeled, lengthwise and thinly; fry in heated oil until tender and golden. Add oil as required.
Line bottom and sides of 2 quart casserole dish; spread with layers of meat.
Alternate eggplant and meat. Finish with eggplant on top.
Melt 1/2 cup butter and stir in flour.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened.	Season with salt and pepper.
Cool; add eggs and mix well.
Carefully pour into dish to cover the top and to penetrate lower layers. Sprinkle with cheese and remaining 1/4 cup crumbs. Dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1/2 hour. Cool slightly. Serve 6.

title: braised shortribs with carrots
directions: In a large heavy kettle, heat the oil over moderately high heat until it is hot but not smoking and in it brown the shortribs, patted dry, in batches, transferring them with tongs as they are browned to a platter.
In the fat remaining in the kettle, cook the onions over moderately low heat, stirring occasionally, until they are softened.
Stir in the garlic and cook the mixture, stirring, for 1 minute.
Return the shortribs and any juices that have accumulated on the platter to the kettle. Stir in the tomatoes with the juice, the wine, the carrots, the basil, the thyme and salt and pepper to taste.

Bring the liquid to a boil and braise the mixture, covered, in a preheated 350° oven for 2 hours and 30 minutes, or until the meat is tender. Arrange the noodles on a platter, top them with the shortribs and sprinkle the shortribs with the parsley.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: wisconsin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in the hot water and let cool until slightly thickened.
Add the other ingredients and whip until the color of a Wisconsin sunset.

title: pumpkin pie impossible
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in pie plate.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: microwave baked apples
directions: Core apples, leaving small plug in blossom end; peel skin 1-inch from top.
Combine sugar, nuts and cinnamon; fill apples with mixture.
Arrange apples in an 8-inch square microwavable dish.
Dot with margarine and sprinkle with water.
Cook in microwave oven, covered with plastic wrap, at High for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes; serve warm or chilled, spooning sauce over apples.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: bean salad
directions: Cook and drain mixed vegetables.
Combine vegetables and beans.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Shape rounded tablespoonfuls of dough into balls; place on cookie sheet.
Indent centers; fill with preserves or nuts. Dough can also be put in a cookie press and, instead of preserves, can be decorated with sprinkles or large pieces of nuts.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pecan pie muffins
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together with mixer, then add flour and pecans. Mix well. Spoon into well-greased mini-muffin tins. Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes. Makes 24 mini muffins.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Dredge shrimp in flour (slightly).
Melt butter and add garlic and onion.
Cook on low heat.
When onion begins to look transparent, add shrimp.
Cook 3 minutes.
Turn.
Add sherry. Raise heat to medium and cook 3 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook until hairs (or spins a thread). Add peanuts and cook until golden; add 2 teaspoons butter and 1 teaspoon soda.
Stir, then spread out on greased cookie sheet.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together.
Add with 1 cup of water.
Roll into balls. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes between 80 to 90 balls.

title: pineapple cream cheese pie
directions: Prepare pie crust shell (do not prick crust).
Combine crushed pineapple, sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick and clear; cool.
Blend cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and salt; cream well.
Add unbeaten eggs and beat well.
Blend in milk and vanilla.
Spread pineapple mixture in pie shell.
Top with cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Chill before serving.

title: delicious pickles
directions: Dissolve salt in 11 cups water.
Pour over cucumbers (size that will slice).
Let stand in cool place 2 weeks (keeping covered and skimmed).
After 2 weeks, wash off the brine and slice lengthwise, then cover with water and alum.
Let stand 3 hours and drain. Next, pour vinegar to cover.
Add pickling spices.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain; discard solution.
Add 3 cups sugar 3 mornings straight, stirring gently to dissolve the sugar (this makes the syrup).
Put in gallon jugs or jars.
(Don't need to seal.)

title: lemon squares
directions: Beat with a fork.
Fill shell while hot and bake again for 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut while warm.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Steam broccoli and water for 5 minutes.
Saute until tender, celery and onions in oleo.
Add flour to celery and onions. Dissolve chicken cubes in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Slowly add to flour and celery mixture; blend well.
Slowly add milk or cream; mix well.
Add broccoli and mushrooms.
Cook a little more on low heat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Very good.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix the ingredients together in order they are listed.
Whisk the mixture each time you add a new ingredient.
When it becomes too thick to whisk, stir with a spoon.

title: rolled chicken breasts
directions: Wrap 2 layered thin slices of ham around chicken breast.
Wrap 1 piece of bacon around ham.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour mixture of soup and sour cream over top.

title: chicken and cheese casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; no salt. Debone and slice when cool. Saute onions in margarine. Add soups, cheese and tomatoes. Add chicken and allow cheese to melt. In large buttered casserole, place layer of tortilla chips, then layer of chicken mixture. Repeat layers until casserole is full. Make sure tortilla chips are covered by mixture to keep from burning. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Jell-O.
Drain fruit well.
Add to cottage cheese and Jell-O.
Fold in whip cream and mix well.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours.
You can experiment with other jello flavors such as orange or peach with mandarin orange wedges and pineapple, etc.

title: best peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat in egg, peanut butter, salt and soda.
Blend in flour.
Add vanilla.
Roll dough into small balls and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350° or until slightly brown on edges.
Makes 60 cookies.

title: orange pineapple sherbet
directions: Combine milk and pineapple in a 4-quart ice cream freezer. Add enough soda to bring to fill line. Stir together; cover and then freeze following your freezer instructions.

title: eldorado beef casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Add onion, garlic and tomato sauce.
Combine sour cream and cottage cheese with chilies and ripe olives.
Crush tortilla chips in bottom of well buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole. Add 1/2 meat mixture.
Cover with 1/2 sour cream mixture. Sprinkle with 1/2 grated cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Garnish with reserved tortilla chips.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients to form dough. Roll out on flat surface. Cut into desired shapes. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375° just until edges turn lightly brown.

title: wonderful popovers
directions: Combine ingredients into bowl. Wisk until smooth. Pour into muffin cups, less than 1\2 full. Bake in Preheated 450° oven for 20 min. Turn down heat to 350° and bake for 20 more min.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light.
Add egg, vanilla and milk; beat thoroughly.
Mix the flour, salt and baking powder; add to the first mixture, blending well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet, 1 inch apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes approximately 40 cookies.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Saute beef in hot shortening until the red color is gone but not brown.
Add the onion, chili powder, salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Cook slowly while making the second part.
Bring 4 cups water to rolling boil.
Add 3/4 tsp. salt.
Add cornmeal to 1 cup cold water and add to boiling water.
Cook to a soft mush.
Spread half of mush in large deep greased baking dish.
Add meat mixture and cover with remaining mush.
Bake at 375° 1-1/2 hours and serve hot.

title: company steak
directions: Cut steak into 4 serving size pieces.
Pound steak 1/4-inch thick.
Dredge in flour.
Brown steaks in 2 tablespoons of butter in large frying pan for 2 minutes on each side. Remove to platter and keep warm.
Spread both sides of steaks with mustard and sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce.
Cook chives in remaining butter for 1 minute.
Stir in brandy and broth.
Stir over high heat until reduced by half.
Return steaks to frying pan and heat through, about 1 to 2 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix
the first 7 ingredients well.
Add pumpkin, water and flour and mix.
Pour into greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Cream sugar into butter.
Add egg.
Dissolve yeast in 2 cups very warm water (105° to 115°).
Add flour.
Mix well. Refrigerate at least 2 hours (can do up to 4 days) in airtight container.
Spoon into greased muffin tins (2-inch diameter). Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Bring to boil and boil 6 minutes stirring constantly.
Remove from fire.
Put remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Pour sugar and milk mixture over the ingredients and mix well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Best if not served for 2 to 3 days.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: pete's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add enough vinegar to fill a gallon jar. The longer it sets the more mellow it gets.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in large greased casserole.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: corn pudding
directions: Cut corn from cob until you have 2 cups of corn.
Mix with cream and salt. Beat for about 3 minutes.
Pour into baking dish. Bake at 350° until firm (45 minutes).
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana walnut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, then add bananas.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 20 to 30 slices.

title: golden punch
directions: Combine fruit juices, sugar and water in a large punch bowl. Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour ginger ale into bowl.
Garnish with lemon and orange slices, mint leaves, and cherries.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
In separate bowl combine eggs, oil, sugar, molasses and vanilla. Add dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Stir in zucchini until blended.

title: refrigerated pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onion and salt in a bowl; cover with water and leave overnight.
Drain off water - do not rinse. Dissolve sugar in vinegar; add celery seed and pour over cucumbers. Keeps a long time in a large jar, or plastic container, covered, in refrigerator.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Mix until creamy.
Add egg and mix with first mixture.
Combine next 3 ingredients; mix well, then mix with first mixture.
Stir in chips and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 8 to 10 minutes; do not overbake.
This makes chewy cookies.

title: puffy paint
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Put in old mustard, catsup or glue bottles with a needle nose.
Squeeze paint out on heavy paper for a puffy design.

title: golden cream of potato soup
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in large pot and bring to boil. Cover; reduce heat and simmer until vegetables are tender. Gradually stir 1/4 cup milk into flour, making a paste.
Stir this into soup.
Add 2 3/4 cups milk and cheese.
Cook over medium heat until soup thickens.

title: congealed ambrosia
directions: Mix jello, sugar and boiling water together.
Dissolve the jello, then add other ingredients until mixed well. Chill.

title: split pea soup
directions: Soak peas, then simmer all until done.

title: baked fillets or steaks
directions: Cut fish into serving size portions.
Sprinkle both sides with salt and pepper.
Add the lemon juice and onion to the melted butter.
Dip each piece of fish into this mixture and place in a greased baking pan.
Pour the rest of the fat over the fish.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Sprinkle with paprika. Serve immediately on a hot platter.
Serves 6.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix ingredients to make 40 walnut-size balls.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all except cheese.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese; return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vegetables, onion and soup.
Mix dressing and butter; put on top of vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet 'n sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
In large skillet, heat corn oil on medium heat.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Stir-fry until tender-crisp.
Remove.
Stir-fry pork 1/2 at a time 3 minutes. Return pork to skillet.
In bowl, stir together pineapple juice and remaining 5 ingredients.
Stir into skillet.
Add green pepper mixture and pineapple.
Stir constantly.
Bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Serve over rice.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine and bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or casserole dish for 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: dumpling pies
directions: To make the juice, boil the fruit until tender or falling apart. Then use a cloth to squeeze out the juice so no seeds are left in the juice.
Heat juice and sugar to a boil. Roll out dumplings. Pinch off into the slow boiling juice. Leave enough dough to roll out a top for the pie. Put in the oven on 450° until brown.

title: orzo salad
directions: Cook orzo pasta in water with bouillon for approximately 8 minutes or until tender, but firm.
Drain well.
Whisk together vinegar, mustard and oil, adding the oil a few drops at a time. Toss orzo with the dressing.
Add diced peppers and currants.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Combine brown sugar, margarine, water, cinnamon and nutmeg. Microwave at High until margarine is melted (1.5 minutes).
Stir in carrots until coated.
Cover the dish and microwave at High until carrots are tender (5 to 8 minutes), stirring once.

title: orange-mandarin salad
directions: Use 9 x 9-inch pan.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add other ingredients, including juice of fruits.
Chill until firm.

title: pizza dip
directions: Beat together first 5 ingredients.
Spread in bottom of pan. Top with rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with baked pita triangles.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Layer rice, then chicken in baking dish.
Pour water over chicken.
Combine soups, mayonnaise, lemon juice and small amount of water.
Pour over chicken.
Layer broccoli, then broken pieces of cheese over sauce.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter; spread across top.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Good.

title: golden puffed potatoes
directions: Slice tops from baked potatoes. Scoop out insides. For each potato, add 1 tablespoon margarine, 1 tablespoon milk and seasonings.
Beat until fluffy. Stir in process cheese spread. Fill shell. Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: andrea's sour cream dressing
directions: To taste, mix the above and serve over mixed fruits.

title: calamondo cake
directions: Mix together.
Put eggs on last (beating in one at a time). Pour in greased pan, tube or layer.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in tube pan or 25 minutes for layer.

title: nutty cinnamon breakfast bread
directions: Melt butter in one cup of the milk and yeast in the other. Beat eggs and sugar; stir in the two cups of milk.
Mix flour, salt and cinnamon and gradually blend into egg-milk mixture.
Beat well.
Sprinkle in nuts.
Let dough rise to double in size in mixing bowl covered with warm, damp cloth.
Divide dough into two equal parts and press each into a well-greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle tops with cinnamon-sugar mixture and a little melted butter.
Let rise to double in size in pans.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: hot corn casserole
directions: Melt butter and cream cheese with milk.
Add drained corn and peppers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: forgotten cookie
directions: Take oven rack out of the oven and cover with aluminum foil and set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix egg whites, sugar, vanilla and vinegar.
Beat until it forms peaks.
Add chocolate chips and nuts, if desired.
Spoon on foil.
Place rack in oven and turn oven off.
Leave overnight.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in saucepan; bring to a full rolling boil.
Slowly pour one-third of mixture over stiffly beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Continue boiling remaining syrup mixture until it forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Add remaining syrup gradually to egg mixture, beating constantly until cool and thickened.
Add vanilla flavoring and nuts; beat until mixture holds its shape.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool thoroughly.
Yield:
Approximately 36 pieces.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Remove skin and fat from meat. Cut meat across grain in narrow strips about 2-inches long. Heat butter in large heavy skillet; add meat and cook, stirring with fork until nicely brown. Add onions. Continue cooking 2 or 3 minutes. Sprinkle flour over meat and stir well. Add consomm and tomato soup. Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce boils and thickens. Add drained mushrooms and seasonings. Cover and simmer gently, stirring occasionally for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until meat is meltingly tender. Stir in sour cream and paprika. Serve over wild rice.

title: brisket
directions: Cover brisket with celery salt, onion powder and liquid smoke and marinate 12 hours or overnight.
Salt and pepper and add Worcestershire sauce.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with crushed cracker crumbs.
Put half of the cracker mixture in bottom casserole dish, saving the remainder for the top.
Add half the pecans and cheese.
Layer on all the asparagus.	Mix liquid from the asparagus with mushroom soup and pour over the asparagus layer.
Add remaining pecans and cheese. Top with rest of cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until bubbly.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk; bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate pieces or peanut butter until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla (and nuts).
Beat until blended well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: lemon puff pudding(an oldie)
directions: Cream margarine, flour and 1/2 cup sugar in mixing bowl.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Stir in lemon juice and milk.
Add salt to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Gradually beat in remaining 1/2 cup of sugar.
Fold into first mixture.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart buttered baking dish.
Set in a shallow pan containing boiling water 1-inch deep.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool and serve with whipped cream or plain.

title: e-z pie crust
directions: Stir flour and salt together; add oil and water together.
Mix and combine.
Roll between 2 sheets of waxed paper; pull off one center crust in pan and pull off other sheet.
Makes one shell in less than 5 minutes.
Prick well; bake at 350° to 375° for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: opossum
directions: Clean and boil to tender, drain water off and place in baking container.
Bake at 500° for one hour with sweet potatoes placed around the opossum.
Salt and pepper to taste and serve while hot.

title: dog biscuit recipe
directions: Mix ingredients with about 1/2 cup cold water.
Knead for 3 minutes.
Roll to 1/2-inch thick and cut into dog bones.
Bake on a lightly greased cookie sheet for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, zucchini and nuts. Mix well.
Pour into loaf pans (greased and floured).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Shred cabbage.
Cook cabbage, onion and bouillon cubes (which have been dissolved in 2 cups of hot water) until cabbage begins to be tender.
Add sugar and salt.

title: squash bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in large loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until it tests done in the middle.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Wash, peel and cut up fresh sweet potatoes.
Cook until soft. Drain and mash.
(May freeze extra potatoes to be used later.)

title: strawberry pretzel surprise
directions: Combine pretzels, 2 tablespoons of sugar and margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes and then cool.

title: dad's cheese ball
directions: Mix 1/2 of nuts and parsley and reserve for later use.
Mix all other ingredients to a smooth consistency and chill so the cheese mixture can be rolled into a ball.
Roll ball into nut/parsley reserve.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: my pita pizza
directions: Cut pita bread in half; open up bread to form pocket.
Put 2 tablespoons of pizza sauce in each pocket.
Put 1/4 mushrooms in pocket.
Put 1/4 cup of cheese in each pocket.
Put pizza in microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: easy, delicious, nutritious "lemon chicken"
directions: Marinate chicken breasts in the juice of 1 lemon.
Dissolve chicken bouillon granules in 3 1/4 cups boiling water.

title: momma's apple pie with graham cracker top
directions: Put apple slices in unbaked pie crust.
Mix the next 6 ingredients together and sprinkle over apples.
Pour melted butter over the top.
Bake 1 hour at 350° (or until apples are tender).

title: fruit and nut cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Beat eggs, Crisco and vanilla.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Bake in muffin tins in baking cups.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Leave in baking cups.

title: fairway mist
directions: Chill soda pop before using.
Garnish with lime slices. Yields 1/2 gallon.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix 1 cup milk with topping; mix until fluffy.
Add both packages of chocolate pudding and remaining milk.
Beat until fluffy.
Spoon into pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill 3 hours.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake mix
in
an
11 x 13-inch pan.
Mix condensed milk with equal	amount	of
pina
colada mix.
Pour over cake while still hot.	Spread	pineapple
with juice over the cake. Let cake stand for
hours.
Spread
Cool
Whip
on top and sprinkle with fresh or frozen coconut.

title: onion casserole
directions: Slice onions thin.
Add to pan with butter and saute.
Stir. Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Add flour.
Add packet of broth seasoning. Stir.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Put in casserole dish.

title: spicy pasta dish
directions: Thoroughly cook sausage links; set aside.
Boil spaghetti as directed; drain.
In a large skillet put spaghetti, diced tomatoes and onions.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on low heat for 5 minutes.
Cut sausage links in halves; add to spaghetti mixture for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix together; cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie crust. Top with egg white frosting and brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together and pour into 2 quart casserole. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 - 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Mix ingredients together, adding rhubarb and raisins last and stir them in.
Put in 2 greased loaf pans.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread.
Cut out top of bread; fill with dip.

title: barbecue pork and beef sandwiches
directions: About 8 1/2 hours before serving time, combine all ingredients in a 3 1/2 to 5-quart slow cooker.
Cook on high setting for 8 hours.
When done, stir with wire whisk or large fork until meat is shredded.
Serve on buns with chopped tomato.
Makes 12 large sandwiches.

title: crab bisque
directions: Mix all ingredients (except crabmeat) together over low heat. Add crabmeat just before serving.

title: western dressing dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Good with vegetables or chips.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble 1/2 of cake into bottom of punch bowl.
Mix 1 package of pudding and pour over hot cake.
Layer Cool Whip over pudding. Take Heath bars and crush with a rolling pin.
Sprinkle over Cool Whip.
Repeat the above process to make a second layer.
Serve.

title: bojangles muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter.
Drop by tablespoon into muffin tins that have been greased (1/2 full).
Spoon melted butter on top of each.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: salmon rabbit pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix salmon and peas; spread in 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Blend cheese and 1/2 cup milk; pour over salmon.
Mix mayonnaise, 1/3 cup milk and Bisquick with fork. Drop with spoon on salmon mixture.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes, until browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beverly's nacho dip
directions: Brown meat and dry taco mix.
Simmer according to package. Pour in casserole and let cool.
Spread sour cream on meat mixture. Melt Velveeta cheese in saucepan and add Ro-Tel tomatoes (chopped and drained).
Pour this over sour cream.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles.
Serve hot with nacho chips.
May be made ahead.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix the sugar, flour and meal together.
Mix the eggs into flour mixture, then add the melted butter, milk and lemon juice. Blend this together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350°.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Blend cake mix, flour, dry jello, oil, water, eggs and berries. Bake in greased pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken scallop
directions: Cook noodles according to package; rinse and drain.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion and green pepper and saute.
Add flour, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Mix well.
Add milk gradually and continue to cook, stirring constantly until sauce is smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat and add cottage cheese. Combine noodles, white sauce and chopped chicken, mixing well. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: artichoke pizza
directions: Unroll dough and press onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until cooked through.
Combine remaining ingredients, saving 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese to sprinkle on top.
Spread on crust.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: best yet raisin pie
directions: Mix together and bake in double crust at 350° until brown. (Very good.)

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Clean out peppers.
Cook peppers in boiling salt water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water).
Cook 5 minutes and drain.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in 9 x 13 pan. Layer ingredients alternately. Drizzle 1 can Eagle Brand over all and bake 30 minutes at 350°. Leave in pan at least 30 minutes before cutting.

title: quick and easy rolls
directions: Melt
margarine and add sour cream.
Mix with Bisquick. Spoon mixture into greased or sprayed muffin tins (the smaller the cups, the better).
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded level measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: mini cream puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat water and margarine to rolling boil.
Stir in flour vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball (about 1 minute).
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs thoroughly one at a time until smooth.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonful onto slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown and dry.
Makes 18 to 35 puffs. Cool.
Cut off tops and scoop out filaments.
Make pudding according to package directions.
Fill puffs.
Top each cream puff with dop of Cool Whip and 1/2 a cherry.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Put skim milk and pudding mix in mixing bowl and beat with wire whisk for 1 minute.
(Mixture will be very thick.) Set aside and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: tennessee pumpkin bread
directions: Cream the shortening, gradually beating in sugar. Add eggs, pumpkin, water, nuts and vanilla. Blend in dry ingredients. Turn batter into 2 loaf pans and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until done. Cool.

title: lo-cal orange salad
directions: Mix all and refrigerate.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Using a pastry blender or knives, cut the butter into the flour mixture. In another medium bowl, mix the boiling water and baking soda until the soda dissolves. Add the molasses and blend. Cool the molasses mixture slightly and pour into the pie shell. Sprinkle the crumb mixture over the top.

title: good rich pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, oleo, eggs and vanilla in bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Empty can of pineapple (juice included) in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix on top and drizzle melted butter over.
Put coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot tea warmer
directions: Bring first four ingredients to boil in large, heavy saucepan over high heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Boil 6 minutes. Remove from heat and add tea bags.
Cover and let steep 10 minutes.
Discard tea bags.
Add orange and lemon juices to beverage.
Cover and refrigerate for up to one day ahead or serve immediately.
Using slotted spoon, remove whole spices before pouring into cups.
Serve hot.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well; serve chilled.

title: grandma's rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients except cinnamon.
Pour into a 10 x 10 x 13-inch buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until custard forms on top.

title: kielbasa bean casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
In a separate pan, brown kielbasa and drain.
Mix together kielbasa with onion and celery. Drain beans, all except for baked and chili beans; use their liquid.
Mix together all beans with kielbasa, onion and celery. Stir well.
Pour into a large casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves a crowd.

title: chicken el paso(makes 4 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to broil.
Tenderize the chicken with a tenderizing mallet and season to taste.
Put the chicken on a broiling pan and broil for 10 minutes on each side.
While the chicken is broiling, put the rice and water into a medium size saucepan.
Bring the rice and water to a boil, cover and reduce heat to a simmer for 15 minutes.
Once the rice and chicken are cooked, place a bed of rice on each serving plate.
Place a broiled chicken breast on each bed of rice and pour a generous amount of salsa (or barbecue sauce) over the chicken and rice.
Finally, top each serving with 1/4 of the shredded cheese and place into the microwave oven for 1 minute (or until the cheese melts).
Serve while hot and enjoy!

title: raisin bran muffins(makes 12 dozen)
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix cereal, flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add nuts.
Add eggs, Crisco and sour milk.
Mix completely; store in a cool place overnight.
Do not stir when putting in muffin tins.
Fill 3/4 full; use ice cream scoop.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hard candy
directions: Boil to hard crack stage (300°).
Flavoring can be peppermint, cinnamon, lemon, etc.
Food coloring can be added, if desired. Pour into pan sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Let cool, break into pieces.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Blend sugar, vanilla and oil into eggs.
Stir in zucchini. Blend in other dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts and bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: homemade pickles
directions: Drain juice from
pickles
and discard.
If pickles are large, slice into quarters.
Re-pack pickles into jar, placing garlic pieces
well throughout.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan,
then
heat to boiling.
Pour hot mixture over pickles; cover
jar	loosely.
Let jar rest on counter top for 24 hours, then chill.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: makes its own crust egg custard
directions: Blend in blender for 30 seconds.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pie pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: drop hermits
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients together.
Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add milk to beaten eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with liquid to cream mixture.
Add nuts and raisins. Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven until browned.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: spiced cider
directions: Mix together and let simmer for about 1 hour.

title: fettucine
directions: In small saucepan, combine cream and cheese.
Whisk until thick.
To thicken quicker, add more cheese.
Whisk until cheese melts, about 30 minutes.
Add egg yolks and blend until smooth. (Add meat now if using as a main dish.)
Add cooked noodles.

title: snowcap cheese mold
directions: Mash cheese together until well blended. Soften gelatin in cold water. Dissolve over boiling water. Stir gelatin into cheese mixture. Add grapes, nuts and chives.
Fold in whipped cream. Spoon into 1-quart mold or individual molds.
Chill 6 hours or overnight.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix milk, coconut and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on well-greased baking sheet, about 1-inch apart.
Bake at 350° until a delicate brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan at once.
Makes about 30 (1/2-inch) cookies.

title: spinach and strawberry salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss together the spinach and strawberries. In a medium bowl, whisk together the oil, vinegar, sugar, paprika, sesame seeds and poppy seeds. Pour over spinach and strawberries and toss to coat.

title: hominy supreme casserole
directions: Mix cheese, pepper and sour cream.
Stir in hominy.
Bake at 325 for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and casserole is hot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat all together and shape in ball.
Roll in nuts.

title: janie's southern style okra
directions: In skillet fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
To drippings add pepper, salt, celery and onions.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes until okra is tender, stirring occasionally.

title: caramel filled brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt caramels and 1/2 cup evaporated milk over low heat.
Mix together the cake mix, oleo and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Pat 1/2 of chocolate mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 or 7 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour melted caramel over chocolate mixture.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over caramel.
Pat remaining chocolate mixture over caramel and chips. Bake 15 to 20 minutes more.
Refrigerate after cooling before cutting.

title: english wedding fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Mix liquid ingredients and add to creamed mixture, alternating with dry ingredients.
Add beaten eggs; mix well. Combine all chopped fruit and nuts; add to batter.
Mix well! Cook at 250° for 4 hours, in pans lined with brown paper, well-greased.
Makes a 10-pound wedding cake.

title: lemon cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Combine graham cracker crumbs, nuts, sugar and melted butter in a mixing bowl. Reserve 1/3 cup. Press remaining mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake 6 minutes. Remove and cool on wire rack.

title: triple vegetable bake(low calorie)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly spray an 8 x 8-inch baking dish with vegetable oil.
Wipe mushrooms with a clean, damp cloth.
Cut into quarters and set aside.
Peel potatoes and cut into cubes, set aside.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Lay walnuts and coconut in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured baking dish.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over coconut and nuts.
Mix cream cheese and 1 stick of butter with sugar.
Spoon on cake and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tante hanni's sauerbraten
directions: Marinate roast in remaining ingredients in refrigerator 1 1/2 to 2 days. Braise roast.
Sear on both sides in Dutch oven. Add 2 cups water and 1/2 cup marinade (with all onions) to roast. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Simmer 2 hours.
Serve with boiled new potatoes and red cabbage.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then light mix in buttermilk. Pour into 9 x 12-inch ungreased pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: monterey chicken fajitas
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add chicken, onion and green pepper, stirring until chicken is done.
Add salsa and heat thoroughly. Spoon about 1/2 cup onto each tortilla; top with cheese and additional salsa.
Fold around filling.

title: super bean dip
directions: Spread refried beans thin on a platter.
Mix sour cream, paprika, peppers and avocado.
Spread over refried beans; layer tomatoes, olives and cheese on top.
Serve with corn chips.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients first, except nuts.
Add oil, eggs, vanilla and pineapple.
Mix well for two minutes and add nuts. Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: killer wings
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Place chicken is single layer in lg. shallow baking pan.
Bake 1-1/2 hours, turning midway.
