Remove from oven draining excess fat from pan and let wings thoroughly cool (hot wings will not allow sauce to cling to them).
Combine sauces in lg. bowl and mix well, placing cooled wings in sauce thoroughly coating each wing with sauce.
Let wings soak in sauce for 30 mins.
Replace wings in baking pan and bake for at least 1-1/2 hours at 200 degrees.
Serves 1-4 (depending on how big a wing fan you are!).

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well.
In a cup, mix into a paste the coloring and cocoa; add to ingredients and add vanilla.
Pour buttermilk into cup used to make paste, stirring to get all the coloring.
Sift flour and salt, and alternating with buttermilk, add to batter.
Beat well and fold in soda, then vinegar.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 20 to 30 minutes or until done. Makes 2 layers.

title: mexican cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage, onion and pepper.
Cook meat.
Add taco seasoning.
In a pan, put meat on bottom, then put green pepper and onion on top of meat.
Put rice on top of onion, then put cabbage.
Cover with Rol-Tel, tomato sauce and water.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Halfway through, stir real good.
Cover and finish cooking.
When done, put shredded cheese on top.

title: beans and franks tuscan style
directions: Cook sausage in covered skillet over medium heat with 1/4 cup water until sausage is cooked through, about 8 minutes; uncover and continue cooking until sausage is browned, 3 to 5 minutes.
Cool slightly; cut into 1/2 inch slices.

Cook bell peppers, onion and garlic in oil in covered large skillet over medium heat until vegetables are tender and soft, but not browned, about 10 minutes. Combine sausage, peppers and remaining ingredients in two quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350 degrees for 30 minutes; uncover and bake to desired thickness, abut 1 hour.
(This recipes can be used by diabetics.)

title: rice hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan or baking dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: zesty bacon dip
directions: Mix ingredients together except pretzel chips; cover and chill 2 hours.
Serve with pretzel chips.

title: pickled green tomatoes
directions: Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Pour hot brine into jars, filling to 1/2 inch from the top.
Have jar lids in boiling water and seal immediately as each jar is filled with brine.
Date lids and use in 6 weeks.

title: soup bean pie
directions: Using spoon, mix together sugar, beans and stir in melted butter.
Add eggs, coconut and vanilla; stir very well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick stuck in comes out clean.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops, then grease casserole dish.
Put potatoes on bottom, them place pork chops over potatoes; season with salt and pepper.
Mix soup and milk and pour over potatoes and meat.
Bake in a covered casserole dish for 2 hours at 350°.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Press into 1/2 to 3/4-inch thickness on tray.
Chill overnight.
Cut into 4-inch squares. Coat with flour and brown in skillet.
Place in a baking dish. Pour 1 can mushroom soup and 1/2 cup milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Lightly form into loaf and put in Pyrex dish.

title: butterfinger pie
directions: Mix in large bowl, ice cream, vanilla and 10 of the candy bars, until mixed well.
Pour into pie crust and sprinkle with remaining candy and freeze overnight.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown the ground beef, drain and add the taco mix.
In a large bowl, mix together the lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Add the beef and mix.
Just before serving, add the crushed chips and the Western dressing.
Enjoy!

title: zucchini, pumpkin or banana bread
directions: Mix and pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil; remove immediately from heat. Mix in peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Press into a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips over low heat. Spread as icing over top.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Freezes well.

title: irma brown's white fruitcake
directions: Cream butter well. Add sugar and cream until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Chop fruits and nuts and mix with a small amount of flour.
Sift remaining flour and stir into creamed mixture with salt. Add flavorings.
Bake in tube pan or two loaf pans.
Put in a cold oven and bake at 250° for 3 hours.
This recipe will make a 5 pound cake.

title: tuna delight
directions: Place noodles in casserole.
Add tuna, soup and cheese. Season to taste; cover with crushed potato chips if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.
May be heated in a microwave for approximately 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat all ingredients together and cook, stirring constantly until just boiling. Cool.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Add 1 quart or 1 pint of whipping cream and finish filling to top of sections with milk.
Add vanilla, maple, or cinnamon for flavor and more sugar to taste.
If using cherries, add before last filling of milk and add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter and pour in oblong pan.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients in following order:
crumbs, coconut, butterscotch morsels, chocolate morsels, condensed milk and pecans.

title: first down drumsticks
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Combine ingredients; simmer for 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn; brush with more sauce.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes longer.

title: croutons
directions: In large bowl place bread cubes.
In small saucepan melt butter with Italian seasoning.
Pour butter mixture over bread cubes, toss to coat.
Spread cubes in 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake in 250° oven 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Spread on paper towel to cool.
Old freezer bread is excellent for croutons.

title: chittlings
directions: Pick fat off of chittlings; wash thoroughly several times. Put in pot and boil in salted water.
Cook until tender.
Drain. Cut in pieces.
To fry, dip each piece in beaten egg and then in cracker crumbs.
Fry in deep fat until brown.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels with margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes in 400° oven.
Cool.
Cream together the cream cheese and sugar and spread over pretzels.
Whip the Dream Whip and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Dissolve strawberry jello in boiling pineapple juice.
After mixed, stir in frozen strawberries.
Set in refrigerator.
When it starts to jell, pour over Dream Whip.

title: corn pie
directions: Combine the creamed corn, Niblets corn and milk.
Put in a 10-inch pie pan lined with crust.
Slice hard-boiled eggs on top and dot with butter.
Put on top crust and bake at 350° until crust is lightly browned.
Serve sliced pie with warm milk and butter.
Sausage tastes good with this.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix cake mix, puddings, oil, eggs and water until well blended.
Stir in chips and pecans. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: beef fajita marinade
directions: Sprinkle both sides of the skirt steak with ample amounts of seasoning salt and black pepper. Add the oil, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and minced garlic to a large ziploc bag. Close the bag and shake to thoroughly mix all the ingredients. Add the skirt steak to the bag of marinade. Let meat marinate 8 hours or overnight. Remove meat from marinade and allow excess marinade to drain off the meat. Grill meat over medium coals until it reaches desired doneness. Serve with tortillas and appropriate condiments.

title: cottage grove potato soup
directions: Using a 3 to 4-quart saucepan, bring to a boil 2 cups of water, containing the 2 cups of peeled, diced potatoes and the 1 teaspoon of salt.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 minutes until potatoes are tender.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli as directed.
Saute onion in butter; add flour mixed with water.
Cook until thickened and add cheese. Stir until smooth.
Add broccoli and eggs.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Cover with Parmesan cheese or cracker meal. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: lumpia shanghai(small egg rolls)
directions: In a big bowl, combine first 5 ingredients, then season with salt and black pepper and blend in eggs and soy sauce.
Mix thoroughly well.
To wrap, one end of the wrapper, spoon about 1 tablespoon of the mixture and roll tightly.
Seal the edge of the wrapper by brushing with water.
Cut rolls into 2 pieces and deep fry at 370° in vegetable oil.
Let the egg rolls brown and drain well the oil in a strainer.

title: hershey's cocoa fudge
directions: Thoroughly combine cocoa, sugar and salt in a 4-quart saucepan; gradually add milk.
Bring to a bubbly boil on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Continue to boil without stirring to 234° or until a small amount of mixture forms a soft ball when dropped into cold water.
(Be sure that bulb of candy thermometer is not resting on bottom of saucepan.)
Remove saucepan from heat; add margarine and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cool at room temperature to 110°.
Beat by hand until fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss.
Quickly spread fudge in a lightly buttered 8-inch or 9-inch square pan.
Cool.

title: casserole
directions: Beat eggs,
milk
and
mustard.
Add bread in pan, pour sausage over
top
of bread, add cheese, then pour egg mixture over.
Cook uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Dissolve baking soda in sour cream; add alternately with flour.
Add flavorings.
Fold in egg whites, beaten with salt.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: low-fat oat bran muffins
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Make sure raisins are not stuck together.
Add egg whites and crushed pineapple.
Add water if needed to make a batter.
Fill 12 metal muffin pans that have been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 17 minutes.
Muffin pans can be filled as these do not raise very much.

title: microwave bread pudding
directions: Spread bread cubes in 8-inch round dish.
Sprinkle evenly with brown sugar, salt and raisins.
Put milk into 1-quart measuring cup.
Add butter.
Microwave on High 4 minutes until butter is melted and milk is warm.
Rapidly stir in eggs with a fork and mix well.
Pour over bread cubes.
Microwave at Medium-high for 9 to 12 minutes.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix meal, eggs, corn and oil.
Fold in sour cream and mix well. Pour into a greased preheated skillet.
Bake until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: For 6 to 8 chops, use about 3 cups of cooked rice and one 8 ounce tomato sauce.

title: grilled steak strips
directions: Cut meat into 3/4-inch strips.
Soak meat for at least 2 hours.
Light grill to high heat.
Cook meat, turning constantly, dipping meat in marinade every turn to keep it moist.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Cook chicken and onion in saucepan with 2 tablespoons cooking oil until done.
Add seasoned salt.
Divide mixture between tortillas.
Warm beans; divide them and cream between tortillas. Place salsa on top of other ingredients; roll up.
They are ready to eat.
Makes 4.

title: twinkie delight cake
directions: Slice Twinkies lengthwise and place into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Add pineapple, 7-Up and ice cream in bowl; stir until ice cream melts.
Pour over Twinkies. Chill in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: fish bake
directions: Place fillets in baking dish.
Combine green pepper, tomato and scallions and spread over fish.
Sprinkle with dill and salt; drizzle with lemon juice.
Top with Jarlsberg cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork and cheese is golden.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix together oil, vinegar, sugar and soup seasoning mix.
Pour this over rest of ingredients, about 10 or 15 minutes before serving.
(Noodles of soup mix have been broken up and added also.)

title: gala party mix
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Divide evenly between roasting pans; set aside.
Combine butter and remaining ingredients in a saucepan; cook over medium heat until butter melts, stirring often.
Pour evenly over cereal mixture, tossing gently until all pieces are evenly coated.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Yields 6 quarts.

title: do-ahead iced tea
directions: Use 2 teaspoons loose tea or 2 tea bags for each cup of cold water.
Place tea in glass container.
Add water.
Cover and refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Serve over crushed ice.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits according to directions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered oblong Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut top off peppers.
Wash and scoop out peppers; set aside. Meanwhile, place ground meat in bowl.
Add chopped onion, salt, pepper, stewed tomatoes and chop up half of peppers.
Add rice and mix well.
Stuff peppers with mixture, then place in pan.
Pour tomato sauce over peppers and bake at 350° until meat is cooked. You can also stuff tomatoes the same way or put 1/2 of pan with peppers and 1/2 with tomatoes.

title: heavenly seven layered salad
directions: In a 2-quart serving bowl, layer lettuce, tomatoes, mushrooms, peas, cheese and onions.
Spread mayonnaise over onions, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover; chill several hours or overnight. Garnish with bacon or shredded cheese, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan. While hot, poke many holes with toothpick or ice pick. Mix condensed milk, caramel and butterscotch topping. Pour over cake. Let cake cool completely. Top with 3/4 of a large container of Cool Whip. Sprinkle 4 crushed Heath bars or 1 package Heath bar brittle. Refrigerate until serving.

title: tante neelkjen's cookies(aunt nellie's cookies)
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add milk.
Add sifted flour and soda, pecans and vanilla.
Mix well and shape into rolls.
Roll in waxed paper and chill several hours or overnight.
Slice in thin slices and bake on greased cookie sheet in 350°
oven for about 10 minutes.

title: potato skins
directions: Cut potatoes in half and spoon out the inside of the potato Deep-fry the skin part of the potato until crispy. Place on paper towel to drain the grease. Put skins on a foil lined cookie sheet. Sprinkle with cheese and bacon. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted. Serve with Ranch dressing or sour cream.

title: cream pie
directions: Note:
For chocolate pie, add 3 heaping tablespoons cocoa to sugar and cornstarch.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, juice, vanilla and eggs. Beat well. Add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and beat again. Fold in apples.
Do not beat after apples are added. Bake in preheated oven 1 1/2 hours at 325°. Greasing and lightly flouring the Bundt pan will make a prettier cake.

title: rhubarb crunch(from cottage grove's special education department)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients like pie crust.
Pat in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat eggs; add sugar. Continue beating.
Add dry ingredients and beat again.
Stir in rhubarb.
Spoon evenly over crust in pan.
Return to oven and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve when still warm.
Top with Cool Whip or ice cream if you wish.

title: sugar-free chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa and Sweet 'N Low together.
In saucepan, mix all ingredients together.
Cook on medium heat until thickened.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into prebaked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: carrot-pineapple cake
directions: Blend oil, honey and eggs.
Stir together dry ingredients; set aside.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and combine everything together.
Bake in greased oblong cake pan (9 x 13-inches) in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: apple nut muffins
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add the next 3 ingredients. Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins. Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: tuna pasta supper
directions: Drain oil from tuna into a skillet; add butter and onions. Saute 1 minute.
Stir in flour and seasoning.
Add milk and then cook until slightly thickened.
Stir in tuna to heat and combine with spaghetti.
Serve with cheese, if desired.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix and make crust in baking dish.
Bake at 350° until crisp. Cool.

title: vanilla pie filling
directions: For Chocolate Filling, add 4 tablespoons cocoa (level) to dry ingredients.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate overnight or several hours.

title: sweet-sour beans
directions: Mix all beans.
Fry bacon and drain.
Saute onions.
Mix vinegar, sugar and mustard.
Stir well and add to onions and simmer.
Chop bacon into beans and pour onion mixture on beans. Bake in 3-quart casserole for 30 minutes at 350°.
This freezes well.
Serves 12.
Easy and quick.

title: crunchy crust french toast
directions: Blend egg, milk, sugar and cinnamon.
Mix coconut and corn flakes.
Dip bread slices in egg mixture; then coat with coconut and corn flakes.

title: maiale tornabuoni(marinated pork chops)
directions: Combine all ingredients except pork chops.
Pour over pork chops in deep dish.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Remove pork chops, reserving marinade.
Broil on rack about 4 inches from source of heat 10 minutes, or until cooked throughout.
Turn once during broiling.
Spoon 2 tablespoons marinade over each pork chop. Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour batter into greased and floured bread pans (2) or soup can (only fill up 1/2 way).
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour. If using cans, cool completely before removing.

title: hot ham and cauliflower dish
directions: Cook cauliflower and/or broccoli in a small amount of boiling salted water, covered, until crisp and tender.
Drain well; remove from pan.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix muffin mix, eggs, onion, cottage cheese, margarine and broccoli lightly. Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan 45 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Drain blueberries and pineapple.
Add juice (should be about 1 cup) to Jell-O along with fruit.
Chill until formed.
Beat cream cheese and sour cream, sugar and vanilla until stiff.
Spread over gelatin.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla on low speed.
Add dry ingredients, fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan for 1 hour.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: soft chicken tacos
directions: Heat oil in skillet; add tomatoes, onion and peppers.
Heat for 3 minutes.
Stir in chicken, thyme, cumin and broth.
Add salt and pepper to taste; simmer for 15 minutes.
Before stirring, stir in cilantro, if desired.
Heat tortillas according to package directions; keep warm.
Fill tortillas and serve.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions until almost tender.
Place in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over the vegetables. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put onion rings over top of casserole the last 15 minutes.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add Rice Krispies.
Roll into marble sized balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Mash with a fork and sprinkle lightly with red pepper. Cook at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: christmas cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in water.
Let jello thicken.
Add cranberries, orange, celery and nuts to thickened jello.
Let chill until firm.

title: spice pudding
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour into greased shallow cake pan.
Combine brown sugar and water in saucepan and stir until sugar is fully dissolved.
Bring to rolling boil.
Boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour hot mixture over cake batter and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: ozark fudge
directions: Melt butter in iron skillet.
Add cocoa and salt.
Add sugar and milk, stirring constantly.
Let mixture come to a rolling boil after each addition of milk.
Stir until soft ball stage.
Remove from fire.
Add vanilla extract and beat until creamy.
Add nuts; turn it into a buttered pan and set aside to cool.

title: mom's delicious filling
directions: Mix all together well.
This should be a very moist, wet mixture.
Form into fist sized balls.
Bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours if stuffed into a chicken or 1/2 hour if laid into a baking dish and covered with foil.

title: vienna slices
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut butter in same as for pie crust. Mix egg yolks, milk and flavoring.
Add to dry ingredients and mix thoroughly; press in bottom and up sides (about 1/2-inch) of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread jam on top, then gradually beat sugar into egg whites.
Fold in nuts and pile lightly on top of jam.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into diamond shapes.

title: salmon-rice dish
directions: Flake salmon into buttered casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over salmon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Melt 1/4 cup more Cheddar cheese over top.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Boil chicken until tender; add salt, pepper, onion, Accent, garlic and bell pepper.
When tender add noodles, cream cheese, French onion dip and milk.
Cook noodles until tender.
Serve with biscuits and vegetables.

title: orange cranberry salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello and cranberry sauce and dissolve. Add orange and lemon juices and mix.
Place in mold and chill until firm.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender, peel and slice.
Dice onion and celery; add to potatoes.
Cut bacon into small pieces and brown; drain all but 3 tablespoons of bacon drippings.

title: rocky mountain apple pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cinnamon, flour and cream well; pour over apples. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: peanut butter blitz
directions: In a bowl stir first 4 ingredients.
Spread peanut butter mixture on four slices of bread.
Put the rest of the bread on top.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Save some black olives and onions for garnish. Mix all ingredients except the flour tortillas, enchilada sauce, Cheddar cheese and sour cream. Lay out the tortillas and evenly fill and roll up each tortilla and place in greased baking dish. Pour the enchilada sauce over the top; sprinkle with the Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave until bubbly and heated through. When serving, add the sour cream, onions and black olives for garnish.

title: banana cream pie(weight watchers pie)
directions: Melt peanut butter and honey together.
Add Rice Krispies and mix together to make pie crust; pat mixture in pie pan.
Make pudding (mix for only 1 minute).
Slice bananas onto crust.
Pour pudding into crust.
Add bananas on to the top for decoration. Chill.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Line 9-inch
pie
pan with crust.
Fill pastry 3/4 full with sliced
peaches.
Beat
eggs
and
sugar
and
pour
over peaches. Sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with butter.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 minutes.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except whipping cream, together well. Beat whipping cream and fold into mixture.
Pour into cooled pie crust.
Makes 2 (8-inch) pies or 1 (10-inch) pie.

title: crusty baked potatoes
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Brush potatoes with mixture. Place, cut side down, on baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: hot mint chocolate
directions: Combine chocolate and Schnapps in warm mug and top with whipped cream.

title: crab fettuccine
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions.
Drain.
Heat butter and garlic in skillet on medium heat until garlic is lightly browned.
Add half and half, crab and pepper.
Heat about 3 minutes or until mixture just begins to bubble.
Stir occasionally.
Add Parmesan cheese; stir for one minute.
Remove from heat.
Toss sauce with fettuccine.
Serve immediately.
Makes four servings.

title: louise kelley's blueberry cake or washington pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan well.
Rinse blueberries and dust with flour.
Cream the butter; add sugar and then eggs.
Sift flour and baking powder; add alternately with milk to the first mixture.
Beat well and add vanilla.
Add floured blueberries.
Bake in loaf pan for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: egg rolls
directions: Mix up real well, then put in egg roll wrappers and deep fry.

title: cream-cranberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk and Dream Whip together. Add salad dressing and sugar.
Fold in cranberry sauce, nuts and pineapple.
Pour into mold or loaf pans and freeze at least 6 hours.
Should be thawed a little before serving.

title: shrimp sauteed in herb butter
directions: Shell and devein shrimp.
Melt butter or margarine in skillet; add lemon juice and seasonings.
Saute shrimp in hot herb butter over medium heat 8 minutes or until pink, turning once.
Serve hot.
You will find this excellent when served on a bed of rice. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until smooth. Set aside.

title: cranberry apple dish
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pour into buttered dish. Mix the rest of the ingredients and spread on top.
Drizzle margarine over top and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, water and salt in 2-quart casserole.

Cook in microwave for 20 minutes on High, stirring every 5 minutes. While syrup cooks, beat egg whites until stiff in large bowl. Gradually pour hot syrup over egg whites; continue beating at high speed until mixture thickens and starts to lose its gloss. Beating may require about 12 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts. Drop teaspoonful on waxed paper.

title: baked brie spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Set cheese in ovenproof serving dish; spread butter over top.
Arrange sliced almonds on butter; bake until softened and heated through, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve with bread and fruit.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: "elephant stew"
directions: Cut elephant in 1-inch cubes.
Cook over kerosene fire (465°), frequently adding pinches of salt and pepper for 4 weeks.
If more than 3,800 guests are expected for dinner, 2 rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary, as most people do not like hares in their stew.

title: the world's greatest cookie
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter. Gradually add sugars and cream until blended. Add eggs, 1 at a time. Beat until smooth. Add sifted flour to creamed mixture. Stir in chocolate chips. Drop from tablespoon onto a greased baking sheet. Slightly flatten cookie dough with back of spoon. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream softened cream cheese and peanut butter together.
Add Cool Whip and powdered sugar alternately.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour into crust and freeze!

title: nestle's crunch tart cake
directions: Bake 3 layers about 25 minutes at 300°.
Cool.

title: better than sex brownies
directions: Unwrap caramels.
Melt in saucepan on low with one can of condensed milk.

title: pineapple sour cream nut bread
directions: Combine flour, salt and soda; set aside.
Beat egg; beat in sugar.
Stir in sour cream, pineapple and juice.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Add nuts and coconut.
Turn into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Place in cold oven; turn heat to 350° and bake about 75 minutes or until done.
Let stand in pan 5 minutes, then turn out on rack to cool.
Freeze, if desired.

title: chicken elegante
directions: Take chicken breast and wrap each one with one slice of bacon. Grease baking dish and cover with chipped beef (dried beef).
Lay chicken breasts over dried beef.
Mix sour cream and cream of mushroom soup and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 275° for 3 hours.
This also works well with all pieces of chicken.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream the shortening and 1/2 cup sugar together.
Add the eggs (well beaten). Sift dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture. When well blended, chill and shape into walnut size balls. Roll in 2 tablespoons cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar mixture.
Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet and bake for 12 minutes at 400°.

title: good chocolate pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese, powdered sugar and small carton of Cool Whip.
Prepare vanilla and chocolate pudding with milk.
Add pudding mixture to cream cheese mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into crusts and top with large carton Cool Whip, chopped nuts and grated chocolate.

title: pronto pralines
directions: Combine pudding and sugars together.
Stir in evaporated milk. Bring to a boil. Stir constantly. Boil for 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Beat 3 minutes.
Don't overbeat. (Mix should be shiny when dropped, not dull and thick.)
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Let stand for 1 hour to harden. Makes 24 pralines.

title: california cole slaw
directions: Mix together and pu on a chopped mixture of:
cabbage, green pepper, onion and carrot.
Good enough to be a meal all by itself.

title: herbed mushrooms and artichokes
directions: Microwave mushrooms on high for 5 minutes with small amount of water. Save for later (be sure to drain). Combine onion and butter in casserole dish. Cook, covered on high for 2 minutes. Stir in flour, bouillon, thyme, nutmeg. Stir in 2/3 c. water. Cook uncovered on high for 2 to 3 minutes until bubbly and thickened, stirring every minute. Stir in cheese until melted. Stir in sour cream. Fold in artichokes and mushrooms. Cook uncovered on high for 2 minutes or until heated through. Top with pecans if desired.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Combine ingredients in an oven-proof casserole, sprinkling potato chips over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Let thicken.
Add Cool Whip and sour cream.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding.
Sprinkle wafer crumbs on top.
Chill for about an hour.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Let yeast rise in 1/2 cup warm water (little of sugar also). Combine sugar, oleo, egg and salt together.
Add yeast and rest of water.
Add enough flour to knead.
Let rise for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Divide into 24 equal rolls.
Let rise 35 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Brush tops with oleo, then turn on racks to cool.
I also use this for cinnamon rolls.

title: naomi's veggie squares
directions: Use 2 pans, about 12 to 18-inches. Spread rolls on pans and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°. Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and dressing together. Spread on top of cooled rolls. Put layers of vegetables on top; press veggies. Sprinkle 1 cup of love on top. Chill overnight. Enjoy!

title: mocha fudge pie
directions: Combine hot water & 2 tsp. coffee granules in medium bowl; stir well. Add brownie mix, 1 tsp. vanilla, & egg whites; stir until well blended. Pour mixture into 9 inch pieplate coated with cooking spray. Bake at 325° for 22 minutes. Let crust cool completely. Combine milk, 2 Tbsp. Kahlua, 1tsp.

coffee granules, remaining tsp. vanilla, and pudding mix in bowl; beat at medium speed 1 minute. Gently fold in 1 1/2 c. whipped topping. Spread pudding mixture over brownie crust. Combine remaining Kahlua and coffee granules in bowl; stir well. Gently fold in remaining whipped topping.
Spread over pudding mixture.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear clean lettuce into small bite-size pieces into large casserole dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Layer the rest of the ingredients in order given.
In small bowl, add sugar to mayonnaise and spread over the top of salad as you would frost a cake.
Top with cheese. Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown and season ground beef and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer while cooking noodles.
Layer noodles, beef, cottage cheese and 1/3 of cheeses.
Repeat twice more and top with last of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: leftover ham or turkey
directions: Cook noodles and set aside.
Mix together all remaining ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour noodles and 1/2 cup of cheese into mixture.
Sprinkle top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese and bake, covered, at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: mandel bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then mix in sifted flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Drop into 3 or 4 rolls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and cut with sharp knife into small pieces.
Return to oven at 325° and bake until golden brown.

title: ham ball
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Form into ball.
It may be necessary to refrigerate mixture before making ball (easier to handle).
Keep refrigerated. Very good with favorite crackers.

title: chicken breast in cream sauce
directions: Take boneless and skinless chicken breasts and dip in beaten eggs and then roll in bread crumbs.
Place in hot skillet with equal parts butter and oil.
Brown on all sides and then place in single layer in casserole dish.
Pour over whipping cream .
Cream until half covered.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: old pecan street special
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into deep dish crust and bake at 375° until done (center of pie will be firm when touched).

title: carrot-coconut bread
directions: Beat eggs until light in color.
Stir in oil and vanilla. Blend in carrots, coconut, raisins and nuts.
Stir in flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and sugar.
Blend well. Spoon batter into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Remove loaf from pan.
Cool.

title: tomato cabbage soup
directions: Mix all together.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Dash of hot sauce or salsa may be added, if desired.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: flour tortilla rolls
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except flour tortillas.
Spread mixture over tortillas, roll up and refrigerate overnight.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch rolls.
Serve as an appetizer.

title: spinach balls
directions: Do not add water to stuffing mix.

title: peanut butter drop cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat.
Add milk and flour sifted with salt and baking powder.
Add peanut butter. Stir in nuts.
Drop on greased baking sheet and bake 15 minutes in 400° oven.

title: dutch sytle beef and cabbage
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
Cut into cubes.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat with flour mixture.
In skillet, quickly brown meat on all sides in hot oil.
Drain off fat. Transfer meat to crock-pot.
Add onions.
In same skillet, combine water, vinegar and beef cubes.
Stir together.
Pour into cooker. Cover and cook on low for 8 hours.
15 minutes before serving, cut cabbage into wedges.
Cook in saucepan until tender.
Drain well. Serve beef over cooked cabbage.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Combine in pot.
Stir over medium heat.
Cook to 235°, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 Tbsp. butter.
Cool to lukewarm without stirring.
Add 1 tsp. vanilla.
Beat until thick and no longer glossy.
Pour into 8 x 8 inch square pan.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Add oleo to spaghetti, stir until melted.
Beat eggs, add cheese and add to the spaghetti mixture.
Place in 9 x 13
pan.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and flour.
Beat until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: hot crabmeat appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients except the almonds.
Mix well and place in an 8-inch greased pie plate. Sprinkle with almonds (optional).
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: creamy egg nog
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla pudding mix.
Beat until smooth.
Add ice cream.
Beat to blend.
Add nutmeg (add as much or as little as your taste deems appropriate).

title: yummy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook onion and broccoli in margarine. Add soup, milk and Cheez Whiz. Blend mixture with rice in large casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread out in a 9 x 13-inch pan in order given, adding each layer on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add buttermilk and beat well.
Combine flour and soda; gradually stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla; chill dough several hours or overnight. Roll dough to 1/4 inch thick on floured board.
Place 1-inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° until light brown. Sprinkle sugar over them.

title: potatoes and onions
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Place peeled and quartered potatoes and sliced onions in dish.
Melt margarine; stir in flour. Combine cream and water; add to flour mixture in saucepan.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Add salt and pepper.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli according to directions; drain broccoli.
Add Cheez Whiz, mushroom soup, rice and broccoli.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven or 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all together.
Let set 1 to 2 hours in refrigerator.

title: windy chili
directions: Brown meat.
Blend onion soup and put with meat; simmer.
Add chili powder, cumin, black pepper and a few drops of Tabasco sauce.
Add kidney beans, tomato paste and tomato sauce.

title: warm coconut icing
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter in sugar, then pour in milk, stirring slowly until mixed well. Bring to boil and maintain a rolling boil, stirring constantly for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in coconut, then cool to desired consistency. Then pour over cake.

title: green tomato parmigiana
directions: Heat oil in saucepan.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute, stirring until tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in tomato sauce, parsley and pepper. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Beat egg, milk and oil.
Coat tomato slices in flour, then egg mixture.
Flour again. Heat 1/4 cup oil in skillet.
Fry tomatoes until golden brown on both sides, adding oil as needed. Arrange in alternate layers or one layer in 8 x 10-inch pan with tomato sauce, shredded cheese and grated cheese.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix together as you do for pie crust.
Chill until able to use as pie crust.

title: cocoa oatmeal cookies(no-bake cookies)
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa on medium heat.
Let reach a full rolling boil and boil for 2 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and beat mixture until well blended.
Drop a spoonful on wax paper and let set.

title: three layer pie
directions: Cream oleo and flour.
Add pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tea cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Slowly mix in flour.
Divide dough into teaspoon size balls.
Make imprint in the center of each ball with thumb.
Fill with jam or jelly.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes 96 cookies.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In skillet, combine beef, onion and green pepper.
Cook over medium heat, breaking up meat with a fork until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Add catsup, undiluted soup and water.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole (oblong works best).
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 35 minutes.
Also good made with ground turkey.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer in a large container in order given.
Mix 2 cups of mayonnaise with 1/2 to 1 cup of sugar.
Pour over salad.
Let sit in refrigerator 24 hours.
Toss and serve.

title: stuffed mushrooms-romania(ciuperci umplute)
directions: Preheat oven to 300. Boil livers in dry wine. Grind liver, add onion, parsley, egg, salt and pepper (to taste), mix well. Clean and stem mushrooms. Stuff with mixture. Lightly butter each mushroom and place in baking dish. Bake for 30-60 minutes depending on size of mushroom. Serve hot.

title: cheeseburger bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Generously grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook beef and onion in a 10-inch skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in soup, vegetables and milk.

title: brown rice with mushrooms
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add rice and mushrooms. Add beef broth.
Bring to a boil.
Put into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is tender.

title: festive cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon. Stir in almonds. Beat eggs slightly. Combine oil, almond extract, bananas and undrained pineapple. Add dry ingredients. Mix; do not beat. Spoon into Bundt pan, greased. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Let stand 10 to 15 minutes. Invert on plate and cool.

title: chicken delight
directions: Layer Stove Top, broccoli and add soup.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: raisin-date cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, orange and lemon peel.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg. Beat into margarine mixture until blended.
Stir in raisins, dates and almonds.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Spread slightly with back of spoon or fork.
Bake 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: broccoli puffs
directions: Trim broccoli; pare stems.
Cut flowerets into 1-inch pieces and stems into 1/4-inch slices.
(You should have about 2 cups.) Cook, covered, in boiling water until tender.
Mash or chop finely.

title: cranberry-blueberry pie
directions: Put cranberries through food chopper.
Combine with frozen blueberries, sugar, flour and salt.
Place in pastry-lined 9-inch pie pan.
Dot with butter.
Adjust top crust and flute edges; cut vents.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 45 to 50 minutes, or until crust is golden.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Cook until thick eggs, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Then add mayonnaise and milk.
When cooking potatoes, add salt.
Add to cooled potatoes, celery, onion, pimento and celery seed.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix together with mixer.
Pour mixture over crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool; pour filling over mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: vermicelli (greek) salad
directions: Prepare vermicelli according to package directions except boil in unsalted water.
Mix olive oil, lemon juice and seasoning together.
Combine olives, pimento and green onions; mix with vermicelli.
Pour olive oil mixture over pasta and toss.
Make the day before or at least 4 hours before serving.
Keeps for at least 1 week.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, green onion and peas in 9 X 13-inch dish. Cover with thin layer of mayonnaise.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Shortly before serving, add bacon, eggs and tomatoes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in large bowl and mix well with fork. Add shortening and mix well with a fork.
In small bowl, beat together with a fork 1/2 water, the vinegar and egg.
Combine the two mixtures, stirring with a fork until all ingredients are moistened.
Divide dough into the size portions you want to use and roll out on floured board.
Or freeze in balls and take out of freezer a couple hours before using.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown the sausage.
Pour in casserole dish and add all the other ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and jello.
Add water.
Cook until thickened.
Mix in peaches.
Pour in pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Cool in fridge.
Overnight is best.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour and salt well.
Add milk and eggs. Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring almost constantly. When thickened, remove from stove and add 2 to 3 tablespoons of butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Crumble graham crackers and stir into pudding. You can put Cool Whip on top if desired.

title: strawberry rhubarb jam
directions: Clean jars.
Keep lids hot until ready to use.
Thoroughly crush cleaned berries, one cup at a time.
Measure 2 cups berries into 6-quart saucepot.
Chop rhubarb finely.
Measure 2 1/2 cups into saucepot.
Measure sugar into separate bowl.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar from measured amount and fruit pectin in small bowl.
Stir fruit pectin mixture into fruit in saucepot.
Add butter.
Bring mixture to full, rolling boil on high heat, stirring constantly. Quickly stir in remaining sugar.
Return to full, rolling boil and boil exactly 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Skim off any foam with metal spoon.

title: ted's favorite pizza dip
directions: In 9 inch pie plate; layer cream cheese pizza sauce, pepperoni, black olives and onions.
Top with cheese.	Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Serve with large tortilla chips.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine cooked, cooled pasta and mixed salad dressing with remaining ingredients.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: chicken and rice au gratin
directions: Place chicken pieces in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Combine soup, water, rice, cheese, onion and pepper.
Pour over chicken. Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french toast souffl(serves 12)
directions: Butter 1 (9 x 13) or 2 (7 x 11) glass baking dish(es) well. Fill dishes 1/2 to 3/4 full with bread cubes. In a small bowl, mix butter, cream cheese and syrup together. It is okay to leave a little lumpy. Spoon this mixture over bread crumbs distributing evenly to the edges. In a large bowl, beat eggs, half and half and vanilla. Pour this egg mixture over bread. Fill to 1/2-inch of the top of the dish(es) so that it does not overflow in cooking. Your breadcrumbs will be floating at this point. Dust with cinnamon, cover and store overnight in the refrigerator. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. The souffl is done when the center is raised and firm.

title: pineapple wonder cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package in 8 1/2 x 13-inch pan. Combine pineapple and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over cake while it is still hot.
Cool.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown onion, green pepper and meat in melted shortening.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper. Put layer of rice in greased casserole.
Add a layer of the meat mixture, then a layer of cheese.
Repeat and end with cheese.
Brown in 375° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: death by chocolate cake
directions: Cook brownies according to directions and let cool.
Prepare pudding mix according to directions.
Break candy bars into small pieces in a food processor or gently tap them in a bag with a hammer.
Break half the brownies into small pieces and place in bottom of a trifle dish or large glass bowl.
Cover with half of the pudding, half the candy and half the whipped topping.
Repeat layers of remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle second layer of whipped topping with the reserved crushed candy.
Serves up to 24.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix strawberry gelatin by package directions.
Put in large glass cake pan.
Let cool until partially set.
Drain pineapple, saving juice.
Put half of pineapple and half of nuts in red gelatin and let set.
Bring reserved juice to a boil and add plain gelatin which has been softened in cold water.
Add cream cheese and mix well.
Cool, don't let it harden.
Whip cream; add sugar and vanilla and add to juice and gelatin mixture.
Spread on top of red gelatin.
Let set.
Prepare lime gelatin by package directions and cool until syrupy.
Add remainder of pineapple and nuts, then pour on top of cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until green layer is completely set.

title: heath bars
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with foil.
Spread saltine crackers in single layer in pan.
Melt butter and sugar, boil for 3 minutes. Pour over crackers and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and spread chocolate chips over crackers and when melted spread and let cool.

title: pecan brownies
directions: If doubling recipe, still use only 2 eggs.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sugar; let stand.
Mix first 5 ingredients; top with dressing.

title: mexican artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; spoon into lightly greased 1-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serve immediately with tortilla chips.
Yields 3 cups.

title: upside-down pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter, nuts and cake mix.
Pour into a large 13 x 9 x 2-inch buttered pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pumpkin; then sprinkle nuts on top.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hershey chocolate cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Alternate flour and syrup.
Beat until all ingredients are mixed well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Do not open oven door before the 25 minutes or cake may fall.

title: old fashioned banana pudding
directions: Layer vanilla wafers and slices from bananas in a 1-quart Pyrex dish.
In a saucepan combine sugar, flour, milk, margarine, egg yolks and vanilla.
Heat this mixture slowly, stirring constantly until it thickens.
Then pour hot mixture over layers of wafers and bananas.

title: crescent bake italian
directions: Brown hamburger and onion and drain.
Add salt, pepper, tomato sauce and mushrooms.
Place in 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Open and unroll crescent rolls.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread 1 tablespoon on each triangle.
Roll up, starting at wide end.
Turn into crescent shape.
Arrange on top of casserole.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: nacho cheese sauce
directions: Melt together in crock-pot.
Great on nacho chips!

title: reese's cups
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chocolate pieces and paraffin wax.
Shape into small balls.
Melt chocolate pieces and paraffin wax in top of double boiler.
Dip balls in this mixture and lay on waxed paper to cool.

title: congealed cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups hot water and 1 cup cold water.
Add cranberry sauce.
Beat cranberry sauce into Jell-O with eggbeater or mixer.
Add grated orange and 1/2 cup sugar.
Congeal.
Good for Christmas.

title: cheddar muffin puffs(the favorite hors d'oeuvres of the steinkamp family)
directions: In a small bowl, combine the first four ingredients.
Lightly spread margarine or butter on the muffin quarters.
After spreading margarine on the muffins, spread on combined ingredients.
Sprinkle top lightly with paprika for color.
Bake on a cookie sheet in preheated 400° oven for 6 to 8 minutes. Serve warm.
Makes 48 appetizers.

title: sausage stuff mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; drain.
Remove stem from mushrooms.
In a small skillet cook sausage until no pink remains; break up large pieces.
Drain off fat.
Stir in together sausage and cheese. Fill mushroom caps with 1 teaspoon of mixture.
Place mushroom caps in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan and bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes or until heated.

title: pecan pie
directions: Break up 1 cup of pecans and sprinkle on bottom of unbaked deep dish pie crust.
Melt butter.
Mix eggs, butter, sugars, syrups, vanilla and salt together well.
Then pour into pie shell. Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour, until almost set.

title: orange balls
directions: Crumble wafers.
Add butter and orange juice.
Mix well.
Make small balls.
Roll in coconut.
Keep covered in refrigerator until ready for use.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: cloud nine
directions: Drain pineapple; save 1/4 cup of juice.
Mix cream cheese in bowl; add the juice and beat until light.
Fold in Cool Whip, sugar, nuts, pineapple and cherries.
Chill 2 hours and serve.

title: creamy cheese soup
directions: Saute onion and butter.
Add vegetables when tender.
Add flour and milk mixture; heat, but do not boil.
Add cheese.
Let melt, stirring.
Serve in bread bowls.

title: yellow slush punch
directions: Dissolve the sugar in the water in a large freezer container. Add pineapple juice, orange juice, limeade and almond extract and mix well.
Freeze, covered, until needed. Let stand until slushy. Combine with the ginger ale in a punch bowl and mix gently.
Makes 50 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas to a thin batter.
Add sugar and well beaten eggs.
Then add butter, salt and baking soda which has been sifted with flour.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: candied apples
directions: Wash and dry apples.
Mix sugar, syrup and water;
cook until it
forms a hard ball in water.
Add coloring.
Dip and cool. Makes 8 apples.

title: michigan chilies rellenos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 individual 2-cup casseroles. Combine yogurt, egg and flour; mix until smooth.
Combine cheese in another bowl.
Into each casserole place 1 ounce of cheese mixture. Top with 1/2 of chilies.
Sprinkle 1 ounce of cheese mix in each. Pour 1/2 yogurt mix in.
Add 1/2 tomato sauce.
Top with remaining cheese mix.
Bake at 350° until puffed and edges lightly browned, about 40 minutes.
Turn out on plate.
Circle with shredded lettuce and taco chips.
Serves 2.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Cool slightly. Add rest of ingredients and refrigerate.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; boil eggs and cool.
Combine mayonnaise and sour cream.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and chill.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by tablespoon into deep fat until brown.
Very good with fish or whatever!

title: filet mignon with sautéed onions
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a small bowl; rub both sides of beef with pepper mixture. Place beef on a broiler pan coated with cooking spray; broil 5 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness. Set aside; keep warm.

title: paper cup frozen salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients with enough red food coloring to give a pink tint.
Lightly fold in nuts and Bing cherries. Spoon into fluted paper muffin cups (large size) which have been placed in 3-inch muffin cup pans. Freeze.
Cover with plastic wrap and store in freezer.
Remove from freezer about 15 minutes before serving to loosen paper cups from pan.
Peel off paper cups and place on salad greens.
Serves 12.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together in 2 large bowls, then sift to make uniform.
One third cup mix to coffee cup; add hot water.

title: 3 cheese lasagne(st. rose student recipe)
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Spread 1 1/2 cups spaghetti sauce over bottom of a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange 4 noodles over sauce.
Cover with 1 cup Ricotta cheese mixture, 1 cup shredded Mozzarella cheese and 1 1/3 cups spaghetti sauce. Repeat another layer.
Sprinkle over top 1 cup Mozzarella cheese. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dr. pepper shrimp dip
directions: Combine 1/2 the shrimp and the remaining ingredients in the blender or electric mixer.
Blend until fluffy and smooth. Coarsely chop remaining shrimp.
Fold into mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: egg and potato casserole
directions: Arrange potatoes, peas and eggs in layers in greased 2 quart casserole.
Simmer onion in 2 tablespoons butter in double boiler top.
Add flour and blend.
Add milk to vegetable liquid to make 2 cups.
Add liquid gradually to flour mixture, stirring sauce until it thickens.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into casserole. Top with crumbs mixed with remaining butter (melted).
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: empanadas
directions: Flatten and roll biscuits out real thin.
Cook hamburger with garlic, salt, pepper and onions to taste.
Mix tomato sauce, corn, cheese and sugar and add cooked hamburger.
Place large spoon of this mixture in center of biscuit.
Fold over (like fried pie) and mash edges with fork.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: christmas pickles
directions: *See step 2 for the rest of the ingredients.

title: pop pop yocom's cocktail sauce
directions: Mix all thoroughly.
Keep refrigerated.
Use with shrimp, ring bologna or cheese.

title: german potato salad
directions: Blend dry ingredients; make a paste by adding the vinegar. Take the skillet that fried the bacon and add the water.
Boil and add the paste.
Cook until smooth.
Combine the potatoes and gravy.
Heat only until the chunks of potatoes are warm.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Blend flour, sugar, soda and salt in a large bowl.
Stir in cereal.
Add buttermilk, oil and eggs and blend just until moistened.
(May be stored in fridge in nonmetal bowl for 6 weeks.)
As needed, fill lightly greased muffin pans 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
May brush top with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar before baking.
Makes about 5 dozen muffins.
Recipe may be halved.

title: party pizzas
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Melt cheese, catsup, oregano, garlic and Worcestershire in a pan.
Mix in meat.
Spread on bread and brown in oven 5 minutes at 375°.
May be frozen and heated at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Put chips into blender and turn to high speed for 8 to 10 seconds, until chips are powdered.
Do not overblend.
Push chocolate down with a wooden spoon.
Add boiling water and blend at high speed for 6 to 8 seconds to melt chocolate.
Add rum, coffee and egg yolks.
Blend for 10 to 15 seconds, pushing chocolate down as necessary.
Beat egg whites to stiff peaks with a bit of cream of tartar.
Fold chocolate mixture into whites, gently with a large whisk.
Chill 2 to 4 hours.
Serves 12.

title: microwave salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon reserving liquid in measuring cup.
Add milk to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Bone, clean and flake salmon.
Combine all ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Place in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Microwave at High 7 to 11 minutes or until center is set.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Pour boiling water over All-Bran (set aside).
Cream together sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beat well, blend in buttermilk, Bran Buds and soaked All-Bran.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Can be refrigerated up to 6 weeks.
When needed, fill greased muffin tin 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients very well.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sesame snow peas
directions: Wash snow peas; trim ends and remove strings.
Combine snow peas and remaining ingredients in a 1-quart casserole, stirring gently.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap and microwave at High for 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir after 2 minutes.
Snow peas should be slightly crispy.

title: rosa lea's eggplant pyramids
directions: Peel eggplant.
Slice eggplant 1/2 to 5/8 inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt and let sit a few minutes.
Wipe salt and moisture off.
Brown in heavy skillet on one side.
In baking dish sprayed with Pam, place eggplant, browned side up in one layer on bottom of dish. Top with 1 slice of onion and 1 slice of tomato.
Top with 1 thin slice of Swiss or Mozzarella cheese.
Melt a little margarine and stir in a spoon of bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle on top of tomato.
Bake about 10 minutes in 350° oven until cheese is melted and crumbs are brown.

title: orange salad
directions: Sprinkle dry orange Jell-O over cottage cheese.
Add drained pineapple.	Fold in Cool Whip.
Add miniature marshmallows, nuts, coconut and orange segments as desired.
Chill.
Other flavors of Jell-O may be used.

title: canned green beans that taste like fresh
directions: Add all ingredients and cook as long as possible over low heat.
Delicious.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Peel eggs and divide sausage meat into 4 equal portions.
Wrap sausage around each boiled egg.
Roll in beaten egg and then bread crumbs.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes or until sausage is cooked.
May be eaten hot or cold.
Slice in half to serve or slice into eighths for appetizers.

title: date nut cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder twice. Sift over dates and nuts. Add sugar, butter, yolks and vanilla. Mix with hands. Fold in beaten egg whites. Pour in greased angel food pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cut up raw rhubarb and pour boiling water over it.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Then drain off the water and add sugar, 3 tablespoons water, flour and egg yolks.
Pour into unbaked pie shell, dot with butter and bake at 350° until done.
Then whip egg whites and put on top and brown.

title: chili cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first five ingredients together. Add eggs.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares (70).
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: green stuffed peppers
directions: Steam peppers for 5 minutes.
Brown ground beef and onion. Add tomato sauce.
Cook rice, then add to sauce.
When done, stuff the peppers.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake peppers for 45 minutes, covered, then uncover and bake for 15 minutes.
Take out and add cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable beef stew
directions: Combine meat and potatoes in large pot and add enough water to cover well. Add onion soup mix and onion.
Bring to a boil and let cook for 20 minutes.
Now add carrots, corn, pinto beans, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Let cook about 30 minutes or until all vegetables are tender.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and mix in salt, onion, carrots and parsley and toss well.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Let stand in a cool place at least 1 hour before serving.

title: veggie biscuit bites
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients until soft dough forms.
Turn onto a surface generously dusted with baking mix. Gently roll in baking mix to coat.
Shape into ball.
Knead 3 or 4 times.
Roll dough 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with 1-inch round cutter dipped in baking mix.
Place with edges touching on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 2 dozen 1-inch biscuits.

title: greek butter crescents
directions: With electric mixer, cream together butter and Crisco.
Add 10x sugar and eggs.
Gradually add flour.
Form into crescents. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Sift 10x sugar over cookies. Makes approximately 10 dozen cookies.

title: almond bark treats
directions: Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix taco seasoning, sour cream and softened cream cheese together in separate bowl.
Layer in bottom of pan.
Layer salsa dip next.
Shredded lettuce next, enough to cover pan.
Tomatoes are next, cut into squares (may wish to drain on paper towel before adding).
Final step is the cheese.
Add taco and mild or sharp cheese together.
If done overnight, do first 3 steps first and let chill.
Do following steps before serving or couple hours before.

title: grilled mullet
directions: Scale fish; remove head and clean well.
Cut on either side of the dorsal fin, as filleting and remove back bone.
Leave fish whole.
Salt generously.
Rub with peppers.
Place in Ziploc bag and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to grill, rinse and pat dry.
Cook on charcoal grill over white coals.
You need to use a fish griller or a closely spaced rack that has been sprayed with Pam.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together oil, sugar and eggs; add apples, coconut, raisins, nuts, soda, salt, cinnamon and vanilla and mix well. Stir in flour.
Pour into an oblong baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Test for doneness.

title: dave's hot chili
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add onions and peppers.
Saute until almost tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together into 3-quart casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 1 hour, stirring after 30 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook the macaroni as directed on box; drain macaroni and rinse in cool water.
Dice onion, celery and pickle.
Blend all ingredients together, then add the mayonnaise, mustard and milk. Add salt to taste.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 2 hours. Serves 5 or more.

title: trellis irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In mixer bowl combine 4 cups flour, herbs, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Mix on low speed 2 minutes.
Place buttermilk and oil in stainless steel bowl and whisk gently to combine.
Gradually add buttermilk mixture to dry ingredients, while mixing on low speed and continue to mix until dough forms a ball (20 to 30 seconds).
Scrape dough from hooks. Turn dough over and mix on low speed another 30 seconds.
Flour dry surface with remaining 1 tablespoon of flour.
Knead until smooth with heels of hands.
Form dough into round loaf.
Pinch small handful of dough on top and gently twist, being careful not to tear dough from loaf.
Place loaf, pinched side down, on baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
Whisk egg yolk with 1 tablespoon water and lightly brush over top.
Score by cutting 1/4 inch deep X on top.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Bread is done when hollow sound is heard when bottom is tapped with finger.
Allow to cool to room temperature before serving.

title: chewy bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Spread mixture in greased 13 X 9 rectangle pan.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes or
until done,
Let cool before cutting.

title: hankey panks
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage.
Drain.
Use same skillet to add meat, cubed cheese, garlic salt and oregano.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Spread on slices of party rye bread.
Freeze on cookie sheets.
Store in Ziploc bag and freeze.
To Serve:
Bake in a 300° oven for 10 minutes on cookie sheet.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients except Hershey Kisses in large bowl. Mix on lowest speed until dough forms.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top each with kiss, press firmly so cookie cracks around edge.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all wet ingredients.
Add apples and nuts, then add dry ingredients.
Bake in Bundt pan (greased and floured) for about 1 hour.
Can be cooked in 2 loaf pans.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Combine buttermilk, sugar, soda and Karo in a large pan (at least 4 quart size) and cook over low fire until soft ball forms in small amount of cold water.
Stir often.
Remove from heat, add vanilla and butter. Cool and beat.
Add pecans.
Pour into greased pan.

title: coffee caramel sauce
directions: Cook sugar and water in heavy medium saucepan over low heat, swirling pan occasionally, until sugar dissolves.

Increase heat and boil until mixture begins to color, brushing down any sugar crystals on sides of pan with a wet pastry brush, about 4 minutes. Continue cooking, swirling pan gently, just until mixture turns a rich caramel color.
Remove from heat and add cream (mixture will bubble vigorously).
Stir until caramel dissolves.
Add Espresso and boil 1 minute.
Add vanilla.
Cool to lukewarm.
Can be prepared 3 days in advance and kept covered and refrigerated. Reheat to lukewarm over low heat to serve.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Heat
milk
to	warm temperature.
Dissolve yeast.
Let set a few minutes.
Add sugar and salt while warm.
Gradually add 2 cups flour and egg.
Beat at slow speed for 1/2 minute. Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
Stir in as much of the remaining flour as you can mix with a spoon.
Knead in enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
Knead until smooth, 6 to
8 minutes. Shape into ball.
Place in a greased bowl.	Turn
once.
Cover. Let
rise
until
double, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef; drain grease.
Add all of ingredients in large saucepan.
Bring to hard boil.
Reduce heat; cover and let simmer 20 minutes.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and Karo syrup together and add to the Rice Krispies.
Mold mixture into pie plates and spoon softened ice cream into shell; place in freezer until ready to serve.
Makes 2 pies.

title: spicy chicken wings
directions: Flour the chicken drumettes. Salt and pepper and brown chicken. Put in baking dish. Pour spicy honey barbecue sauce over the chicken wings. Bake at 350 degrees for one hour. Pour sauce over white and brown rice.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In large skillet saute onion and pepper in margarine until tender.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, olives and oregano, then add browned meat.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Place 1/2 of cooked spaghetti in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Top with 1/2 of meat mixture.
Sprinkle with 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers.
Mix the soup with the water until smooth.
Pour over casserole. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes until heated through.
Serves 12.

title: sweet rice
directions: Put rice, milk, sugar and/or cinnamon/vanilla into pan and cook on medium heat for approximately 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: trash
directions: Mix cereals and next 4 ingredients.
Blend liquids and spices. Sprinkle over cereals.
Bake at 200°, uncovered, for 2 hours. Stir every 30 minutes.
(This liquid is enough for 93 ounces of dry mix.)

title: ham and broccoli quiche
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare crust as directed on package for one-crust filled pie, using a 9 inch glass pie pan.
Layer ham. cheese and broccoli in crust-lined pan.
In medium bowl combine remaining ingredients, beat well.
Pour over broccoli.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
6 servings.

title: mock crab cakes
directions: Drain zucchini well, pressing between layers of paper towels. Combine zucchini and next 5 ingredients in a large bowl. Divide mixture into 8 portions, shaping each into a patty (mixture will be soft). Pour approximately 1/2-inch of oil

into a large heavy skillet. Fry patties in hot oil over medium-high heat for 2 minutes on each side. Drain on paper towels. Serve with tartar sauce. Makes about 8 cakes. This is great way to use those extra summer zucchini.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over very low heat.
Remove and gradually stir in the sugar.
Add salt.
Return to heat and stir in milk.
Cook 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Do not let this boil.
Makes a quart or so and stores well in the fridge.
Reheat by placing jar in pan of hot water.
Velvety and delicious!

title: bonnie's apple cake
directions: Mix the sugar, eggs and oil together.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add sliced apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Scrape chocolate squares fine; mix with water, milk and sugar. Stir until dissolved.
Whip with eggbeater until light and fluffy.
Serve with marshmallows or cream.

title: mike's peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water in big kettle until it reaches crack stage, 275° on a candy thermometer.
Add peanuts, stirring until it reaches 300°.
Remove from fire and add vanilla, soda and butter. Stir until butter melts.
Pour out on 2 1/2 feet of foil that has been buttered thoroughly, stretching candy to desired thickness as it cools.
When cool, break in pieces and store in airtight container.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add well beaten eggs.
Add soda to buttermilk; mix well.
Add salt to flour and sift 2 times.
Add flour and buttermilk gradually to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake 1 hour at 325° in tube pan.

title: sweet potato apple bake
directions: In a large bowl, combine sweet potatoes, apples, raisins and almonds.
Spoon into a shallow baking dish.
In a small bowl, combine butter, brown sugar, oats and lemon peel; sprinkle over sweet potato mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage and drain grease.
Steam celery, onions and bell peppers, until tender in butter.
Prepare soup mix by directions, using 2 1/2 cups water.
Combine all ingredients.
Put 1/2 almonds in casserole dish.
Sprinkle other half package of almonds on top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Clean and wash berries.
Simmer 1 cup berries, 1 cup sugar and 1 cup water for 15 minutes.
Add red food coloring.
Mix 1/3 cup water with the cornstarch; add to cooked mixture.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool and add to remaining berries. Whip the cream.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked shell.
When cool, add whipped topping.
Chill before serving.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add melted oleo.
Mix all well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: beef cubes sauerbraten style
directions: Brown meat and onion in oleo.
Add salt, vinegar, water, bay leaves and cloves.
Simmer 2 hours.
Add gingersnaps and boil. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: apple cake(serves 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 9-inch pan.
Place the apples in a large bowl and stir in the egg.
Pour in oil over the apples.
Mix in sugar and cinnamon.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Pour into the prepared pan.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until a tester inserted in the center comes out clean. Preparation time:
20 minutes.

title: holiday potato casserole
directions: Cook
potatoes 15 minutes.
Mash.
Add butter and cream cheese.
Beat.
Stir in 1/2 of Cheddar and next 5 ingredients. Put in	greased
baking
dish.	Bake
at
350° for 40 minutes. Sprinkle 1/2 cup Cheddar over and bake 5 minutes more.

title: grandma lyla's norwegian fattigmand
directions: Mix in order as written.
The batter should be prepared the evening before.
A while cloth should be fastened to the rolling board; sprinkle with flour.
Roll out thin; cut out in diamond shapes.
Make a slit in center and draw one corner through, making a knot.
Fry in deep fat at 370° for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Makes 100 fattigmand.
A Christmas tradition.

title: oriental salad
directions: Chop cabbage and onions, set aside.
Saute seed, almonds and noodles in margarine, set aside.
Boil soy sauce, sugar, oil and vinegar 1 minute and cool.
Mix all just before serving.

title: favorite broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Thaw broccoli. Then combine all ingredients except butter and crumbs. Pour into casserole. Blend butter and crumbs. Sprinkle on top. Bake 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: coconut icing
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Add coconut and mix well. Beat egg whites until stiff. Add to rest of ingredients and cook until mixture starts popping. It will be watery, but put on cake anyway.
It's delicious when cool.

title: little gracies shower dessert
directions: In mixing bowl, cream the sugar and egg yolks until fluffy. Gradually add the milk and place in heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil on medium heat and cook until slightly thickened approximately 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in jello. Cool.
When cool, add pineapple.
Whip the cream.
Fold in the beaten egg whites and whipped cream.
Cut cake into thin slices. Place half of slices in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour half of creamed mixture over cake.
Sprinkle half cherries over. Repeat with second layer.
Freeze at least 8 hours.
Remove 30 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.
This is excellent to have in the freezer.

title: spring flower cake
directions: Toss coconut with food coloring until evenly tinted; set aside.
Place angel food cake on large serving plate; frost top and sides with whipped topping.
then sprinkle with coconut.
Cut cake in 8 slices, leaving all slices in place.
Then carefully pull out cake slices and separate slightly to resemble the petals of an open flower.
Spoon halved strawberries into center of flower.
Store leftover
cake in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: herbed salmon ball
directions: Drain salmon.
Remove skin if desired.
Mash bones.
Combine cream cheese, garlic, cottage cheese, onion, fines herbes and thyme until well blended.
Stir in salmon to blend.
Chill 3 hours.
Mixture will be soft.
Roll in parsley and walnuts.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 4 servings.

title: 4-fold delight
directions: Melt butter; add flour and nuts.
Pat mixture smooth in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients, then add hot water and butter.
Boil 5 minutes.
After sugar dissolves, add cream and vanilla.
Cook a few minutes longer, until thick.
Stir constantly.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix until crumbly, then add enough milk (about 1/4 cup) to make a dough ball that can be rolled out thin.

title: colonial gingerbread
directions: Measure all ingredients into bowl and beat at low speed until blended.
Increase speed to medium and continue beating for 3 minutes.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 16 servings.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs and vanilla and beat.
Add the flour, salt and cocoa; beat 1 or 2 minutes.
Add the coconut and nuts last.
Bake in a greased and floured pan (use a 9 x 13-inch pan) for 30 or 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove from the oven.
Immediately spread marshmallow cream on hot cake and then top with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: pickle relish
directions: Soak cucumbers, onions and mangos in salt for 45 minutes. Squeeze water out of cucumbers, onions and mangos after soaking.

title: skillet corn and chicken
directions: In a large skillet cook chicken in hot margarine 10 minutes or until brown.
Remove chicken from skillet and set aside.
Drain fat from skillet and combine remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling and return chicken to skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat about 10 minutes or until chicken is done and broccoli is tender.
Garnish with tomato wedges and fresh thyme.

title: 2-flavor fudge
directions: Combine sugars, milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to full boil over moderate heat, stirring frequently.
Boil for 15 minutes, over moderate heat, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow cream and butterscotch and chocolate morsels.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Blend in chopped walnuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Yield: about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all vegetables with 1 cup of Hellmann's mayonnaise. Chill.
Even better the next day.

title: dunken weenies
directions: Place all ingredients in a slow cooker on low heat for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve piping hot with party crackers.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Combine sugar and vinegar.
Mix cabbage, celery, onion, pepper, carrot and salt.
