Stir in sugar and vinegar mixture. Chill for 8 hours.

title: pickled cucumbers
directions: Peel cucumbers and run the tines of a fork lengthwise down to give it serrated edges when sliced.
Slice paper thin.
Place in a small deep bowl alternating with layers of onion.

title: low cholesterol rock cornish hens
directions: Wash hens and pat dry.
Split hens lengthwise.
Sprinkle green onions in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Place hens over onions.
Combine vermouth, lemon juice and soy sauce; pour over hens, then sprinkle lightly with paprika and pepper.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 25 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Wash vegetables and cut into medium slices.
Place into a medium saucepan and cover with 1/2 cup of water. Bring to a boil for 10 minutes.

title: rich white cake with strawberry frosting
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Combine water and milk; set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in flavorings.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form.
Gently fold into batter. Pour batter into three greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans and let cool completely on wire racks.
Spread Strawberry Frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.
Garnish with whole strawberries, if desired.

title: coconut-pecan coffee cake
directions: Mix ingredients well (about 2 minutes). Bake in greased and floured or greased and sugared Bundt pan about 1 hour at 350°. A glaze is nice on this cake. Put on after cake has cooled or just warm. Let cake cool about 10 minutes in pan before putting it on plate.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line desired number of muffin cups with paper baking cups.
In large bowl, combine buttermilk, oil and eggs; beat well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.

Add remaining ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Spoon batter into paper-lined muffin cups, filling 2/3 full. (Store remaining batter in tightly covered container in refrigerator for up to 4 weeks.)
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: meeshies (iced brownies)(yields 6 servings)
directions: Butter 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until set.

title: zucchini squash with sour cream
directions: Melt butter.
Add salt and paprika.
Add squash, washed and grated in long strips.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add sugar.
Cover and cook 2 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Heat and serve.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 1 hour to set.
Keep refrigerated and covered.

title: crab cakes
directions: Beat egg and add ingredients together.
Make into 6 cakes. Deep-fry in vegetable oil.

title: frosty fudge pie
directions: *After flakes are crushed, you will have 1 cup.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken and broth 20 minutes in large pot. Add noodles. Cook according to directions on package. Add more water if needed. Add salt and pepper to taste. Remove from heat. Stir in soup and thyme. Cook on low if too thin. Serve with bran muffins. Will freeze well if needed.

title: spaghetti and cheese
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Mix together with cheeses, milk, eggs and seasonings.
Pour into a 10-inch baking dish.
Top with crushed crackers and margarine.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, cream cheese and garlic.
Add chopped artichokes.
Put in 4 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and mix well.
Store in an airtight container.

title: ice cream pumpkin pie
directions: Bake pie shells and cool.
Mix by hand pumpkin and spice.
Add ice cream and mix well.
Add dry instant vanilla pudding and mix well.
Pour into cooled pie shells and spread with whipped topping.
Chill and serve.

title: carrot halva
directions: Mix carrots, sugar, milk and water in heavy pan.
Boil until almost dry, stirring constantly.
Add butter and cook again until almost dry.
Add raisins and coconut. Spread in a shallow greased pan and refrigerate.
Cut into squares when cold.

title: marg's diet cake
directions: You will also need a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: easy holiday squares
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time.
Add vanilla.
Spread into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Divide into 24 squares and drop 1 tablespoon of cherries in each square.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small skillet, melt butter.
Add onion, celery, green pepper, 1/2 teaspoon Italian seasoning and garlic powder.
Cook and stir over medium heat until tender.
In medium mixing bowl, crumble beef.
Add onion mixture, bread pieces, milk, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well and press into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour. Add baking powder, salt and shortening; mix. Add milk and mix well. Let rise for 15 minutes. Shape into biscuits and place in greased pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: strawberry angel food cake dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch dish, tear cake into pieces.
Mix the cream cheese, Cool Whip, sugar and milk together; spread over cake.
Mix berries and Glaze together and spread over cream mixture.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: cranberry percolator punch for 30
directions: Place
the juices, water and sugar in a pot.
Place the cloves, cinnamon and salt in percolator basket.

title: allegro chicken
directions: Place chicken in a Ziploc bag.
Add enough Allegro to flavor chicken, about 1 tablespoon per chicken breast.
Marinate several hours.
Grill or broil.

title: cheerios treats
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch rectangular pan.
Microwave margarine in large microwavable bowl on High for 45 seconds, or until melted. Add marshmallows; toss until coated.
Microwave 1 minute and 30 seconds on High, or until smooth when stirred, stirring after 45 seconds.
Stir in peanut butter.
Immediately stir in cereal; mix lightly until well coated.
Press mixture into pan, using greased spatula or waxed paper.
Let cool; cut into squares.
Yields about 24 squares.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; add to mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan; sprinkle butterscotch chips on top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: recipe for a happy marriage
directions: Flavor with frequent portions of prayer, recreation and a dash of happy memories.
Stir well and remove any specks of jealousy, temper or criticism.
Sweeten well with generous portions of love and keep warm with a steady flame of devotion.
Never serve with a cold shoulder or hot tongue.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Day 1:
Fill gallon glass jar with medium cucumbers.
Cover with boiling water and press down.

title: grandma's waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl; add well beaten yolks and milk. Blend thoroughly; stir in oil. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into batter. Bake in hot waffle iron until golden brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream together.
Add the green pepper, onion and pimento.
Fold in the frozen Tater Tots.
Bake in a covered casserole for 2 hours at 325°.

title: chocolate chip cream cheese squares
directions: Slice 1 roll of cookies 1/8 inch thick and lay over bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: fruit saled
directions: First you get a bowl and cut it all up.
Next you put it in the fridge for 19 minutes and then
you get to eat it!

title: honey pumpkin pie
directions: For filling, in a mixing bowl combine eggs, honey, evaporated milk, salt, pumpkin pie spice and pumpkin.
Beat well.
Pour filling into pastry lined 9 inch pie plate.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400 degrees.
Reduce heat to 350 and bake for 45 minutes more or until knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool on a wire rack.
Serve with whipped cream if desired.
Cover and chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: salsa
directions: Saute onions, peppers and garlic in olive oil. Add other ingredients and simmer until texture of salsa. Put in jars. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: yellow pound cake
directions: Mix well; bake in tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Very good!

title: eclair cake
directions: Boil the butter and water and add the flour.
Cool slightly. Add the eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition. Spread the mixture on a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 3 minutes.
(It will look lumpy.) Cool thoroughly, then put on filling.

title: barbecue chicken marinade
directions: Marinate chicken legs with all the ingredients in shallow dish for 3 to 4 hours.
Stir occasionally with marinade.
Grill on barbecue.

title: custard pie
directions: Thoroughly mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Stir in hot milk at once.
Pour in unbaked shell.
Dot with nutmeg.
Bake at 475° for 5 minutes; reduce heat to 425° for 10 minutes longer or until done.

title: barbecued frankfurters
directions: Put vegetable oil on small plate.
Put chop in each side, then put in bread crumbs.
Sprinkle with small amount of oil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Place rhubarb in ungreased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with salt.
Put sugar, flour and cinnamon into bowl. Add butter and mix until crumbly. Sprinkle over rhubarb.
Bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, saute bacon until crisp. Add onions, potatoes and green pepper. Add clam juice or water. Simmer 15 minutes, covered,
until potatoes are done. Add salt, pepper, clams and liquid and cream. Heat to simmering.
Do not boil or clams will toughen.
Preparation time:
20 minutes. Cooking time: 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli per box instructions.
Melt cheese and 1/2 oleo over low heat.
Drain broccoli and add cheese mixture.
Stir well.
Crush crackers finely.
Melt 1/2 oleo and stir in crackers. Put broccoli/cheese mixture in baking dish and add topping.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Stir shortening to soften.
Gradually add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and molasses, beat thoroughly. Sift together dry ingredients, add to molasses mixture alternately with boiling water, beating after each addition.
Bake in well-greased pan; in moderate oven (350°) about 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Serve warm.

title: avocado canapes
directions: Peel, then chop avocado, eggs and onion.
Add oil, lemon juice and salt.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve on crackers.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Put all ingredients in order, unmixed, in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw
and
break up the hash browns.
Mix with soup and sour cream.
Put into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook sliced carrots in salted water until crunchy.
Drain carrots while hot.
Mix together the balance of the ingredients and mix into the carrots.
Add 1/2 sliced onion and sliced green pepper rings, adding to mixture.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 24 hours before serving.
Makes about 3 pints.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: In pan, bring to boil just around the edges the corn syrup and sugar.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, then cornflakes. Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and slice.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, cocoa and salt.
Add margarine, milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs and beat 2 more minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter together 7 minutes after it starts to boil.
Stir well.
Put marshmallow mix and chocolate chips in a large bowl.
Pour hot mixture over ingredients in bowl.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered platter or a cookie sheet with sides.

title: quick salad
directions: Combine all ingredients with mixer, except crackers.
Crumble crackers and put half in the bottom of your dish.
Pour salad mixture over crackers. Add remaining crackers on top of salad. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Delicious.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water. Add pineapple and oranges (do not drain); pour into 9 x 13 dish. Top with marshmallows. Jell in refrigerator.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans during the day.
Put in crock-pot, turn on low and go to bed.
Wake up at 5 a.m. and check if they need more cooking. Turn on high for 1 hour.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Make pastry and roll very thin.
Cut with biscuit cutter and line muffin tins.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Remove outer wrapping and put unopened package of broccoli in microwave on a paper towel, microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes, just until thawed.
Put butter and onion in a 2 or 3 quart microwave-safe bowl or deep casserole and microwave on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes until onion is tender, stirring once.

Stir in flour, salt and pepper; then the milk and chicken broth until smooth. Cover with a lid or vented plastic wrap and microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times, until slightly thickened.
Open package and gently press broccoli to squeeze out excess moisture. Cover and microwave 3 to 4 minutes, stirring once, until broccoli is tender and soup bubbly.
Let stand 3 minutes.

title: escalloped eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant, cut into 2-inch cubes.
Boil in salted water 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.
Add cheese, mustard, pepper and paprika to white sauce.
Cook over hot water until cheese melts.
In small amount of shortening, fry ground meat until brown.
Add onion and green pepper, cooking until tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll very thin.
Cut in squares. Cook in any kind of broth.

title: pop's hush puppies(ottis bounds)
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour and seasonings.
Add eggs, apple and onion.
Stir in milk.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot grease.

title: jamaican cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat egg, melt margarine and mix both with milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat mix until well blended. Pour into greased tin.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: kraut-meat casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onion until browned.
Drain off fat.
Stir altogether and put in crock-pot on low 4 to 5 hours or in oven 1 hour at 350°.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Place broken pieces of lettuce in a large salad bowl.
Layer onion, carrots, peas (still frozen), a good layer of mayonnaise and cheese and sprinkle bacon bits on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Do not toss.
When serving, dig down to combine all of the layers.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water until jello dissolves. Add drained pineapple, bananas and strawberries. Pour half into mold and chill until firm. Add a layer of sour cream and add remaining jello and chill.

title: gran ray's baked beans
directions: Mix sugars, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add to mixed beans, crumbled fried bacon, onion and pimentos.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick and easy pork chops
directions: Fry pork chops.
Slice potatoes lengthwise and place on the bottom of a casserole dish.
Place pork chops on top.
Slice onion and place on top of pork chops.
Open can of soup.
Mix the soup with either 1/2 can of water or milk.
Pour on top of onion. Cover and cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Put in punch bowl everything.
On top of everything pour 3 quarts of grapefruit soda or 3 quarts 50/50 soda.

title: meatball soup
directions: Combine above ingredients in large pot. Bring to boil and add meatballs. Simmer for 45 minutes. Add 1 to 2 cups egg noodles. Simmer 15 minutes and serve.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese and horseradish together.
Spread evenly over tortilla.
Put 1 slice of beef on tortilla.
Add onion and tomatoes.
Roll tightly and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Serve with additional horseradish sauce or salsa to dip in.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix milk, egg, corn and shortening.
Add flour, blending well. Drop by spoonfuls into deep hot fat or oil. Fry until golden brown; drain on paper towels.

title: diet ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well, add Sweet 'N Low, milk, pudding and flavoring. Beat well again.
Ready to put in ice cream freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.
(About 2,000 calories per gallon.)

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados with onion and seasonings.
Add tomato and mayonnaise and mix until smooth.
Sprinkle top of dip with lemon juice to prevent discoloring.

title: pasties
directions: Make pie crust; roll out and cut into circles using medium size plate.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix with the next 5 ingredients, then add the nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven temperature to 350° and continue baking for 30 to 35 minutes.
Filling should be slightly less set in the center than at the edges.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble, reserving 1/4 cup fat.
Cook onion in reserved fat until tender.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and dash of pepper.
Add vinegar and 1 cup water; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add bacon and potatoes.
Heat thoroughly, tossing lightly.
Garnish with parsley and bacon curls.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Bake in 13 x 9-inch dish in 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: sugar-free fruit bars
directions: Boil together dates, raisins, prunes and 1 cup water.
When done, add margarine and vanilla; cool.
Beat the eggs.
Add cooled fruit mixture and the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. (Real good for diabetics.)

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift together flour, ginger, soda, cinnamon and allspice. Cream together sugar and butter.
Add molasses and egg (beaten). Mix all and add hot water.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until done.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water until dissolved. Add sherbet and mix well. Add Cool Whip and mix well. Add oranges. Spread into 9 x 13 inch pan. Refrigerate overnight.

title: candied carrots
directions: Parboil carrots in salted water; drain.
Add margarine, sugar, honey, pepper and orange juice.
Return to fire on low heat and simmer until cooked to desired doneness.

title: chocolate peanut butter covered crispix
directions: In microwave, melt 16 ounces milk chocolate morsels.
Melt 1 stick margarine.
Mix together and add 1 cup peanut butter.
Pour 1 large box Crispix cereal in large container.
Add mixture and stir.
Pour 1/2 box powdered sugar over cereal.
Mix and toss. Pour mixture in large paper bag and add remaining sugar (10x) and shake.
Store in container.
Eat and enjoy!

title: crustless chocolate pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour and cocoa in mixing bowl.
Stir in melted butter, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into well-greased pie plate. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Can be topped with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: banana split salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in an 8 x 11 x 2-inch pan.
Freeze overnight.

title: feather scones
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt, then rub in the shortening.
Beat eggs and milk together, then stir in.
Use a bit more milk, if necessary, to make a rather soft, yet easily handled dough.
Knead slightly on floured board.
Roll out, to about 1/2-inch.
Cut in triangles or cut out with round biscuit cutter. Bake on ungreased pan in a 425° oven for about 15 minutes, or until high and brown.
Serve at once with butter.

title: guacamole
directions: Combine all ingredients. Refrigerate in a non-metal bowl. Serve within 6 hours with chips.

title: hershey cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add the rest of the cake ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.
In last 5 minutes of baking time, start frosting.

title: dump cake
directions: "Dump" ingredients in order listed into a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve cold or warm with ice cream.

title: mashed potato stuffing casserole
directions: Prepare instant potatoes for 12.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water and add Croutettes, egg, onion, parsley, celery, salt and pepper.
Fold into mashed potatoes and put in greased casserole. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, drop by teaspoon on Teflon pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Substitute coconut flavoring for the vanilla and 1 ounce shredded wheat for oatmeal for variation.

title: grape tea
directions: Steep tea bags in boiling water five minutes; remove bags. Add sugar, Kool-Aid and grape juice.
Cool.

title: festive chicken
directions: Wrap two bacon strips around each chicken breast; place in a shallow glass baking dish and set aside.
In a small mixing bowl combine soy sauce and sugar; add remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken, turning to coat evenly.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until chicken tests done, basting occasionally with marinade.
Yields 2 servings.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch square pan.
Press 1 package of crescent rolls into bottom of pan, pressing seams together.

title: cream of carrot and tomato soup
directions: Put tomatoes in saucepan and cook, uncovered, 30 minutes. Trim the carrots and scrape; cut into 1/4-inch rounds.
Heat 1/2 butter in a heavy saucepan and add carrots.
Cook briefly, stirring, and add salt and pepper to taste and water.
Cover closely and cook 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Slice bananas into mixing bowl; beat until mashed.
Add all ingredients.
Blend well.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and sprinkle with confectioners sugar or frost cake.
If a 13 x 9-inch pan is used, bake about 50 to 55 minutes.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Grease Bundt or tube pan with shortening (not oil).
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon; put in pan (like flour) to coat sides.
Save remainder of mixture.
Mix all the other ingredients together. Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour half of batter in pan. Sprinkle remainder of brown sugar and cinnamon mixture over batter; add remainder of batter.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from oven.
Let stand about 4 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Do not frost.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together in a greased casserole; dot with butter.
Stir once or twice while baking at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: easy banana cream pie
directions: Slice bananas in pie shell.
Prepare pie filling as directed on package for pie, using 2 1/2 cup milk.
Fold in 1/2 cup whipped topping and pour over bananas in shell.
Chill 1 to 3 hours.
Add remaining topping; garnish with bananas and mint.

title: baked brie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
On floured surface, roll pastry into a 12-inch square.
Cut 2 circles from it:
one 4 1/2-inches in diameter, the other 8 1/2-inches in diameter.
Spread mustard over each circle, leaving a 1/4-inch border.
Center Brie on large pastry circle; place small pastry circle on top and brush with egg. Fold bottom circle's sides up and press them onto the top circle to seal.
Invert onto greased cookie sheet; brush with egg.
Press almonds onto sides.
Using cookie cutters, cut leaves from scraps; arrange on top.
Bake 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oriental salad
directions: Take seasoning packet out of noodle package.
Mix with the vegetable oil, vinegar and sugar.
Set aside.

title: old fashioned chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, salt and milk in a 3-quart saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring until it starts boiling.
Cook until 237° (use candy thermometer in pot).
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cool to 110°.
Beat with spoon until it starts to lose its gloss and spread in buttered platter.

title: no bake chocolate, oatmeal, peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except oats and peanut butter in a large saucepan; bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Last, stir in oats.
Drop onto wax paper.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, butter and water.
Cook over hot water until smooth and thick.
Season to taste.
Add beets.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve at once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour 3/4 cup sugar over peaches (or cherries) and let stand. Melt margarine in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Make a batter of sugar, flour, baking powder, milk and salt. Pour batter into dish. Then pour peaches over batter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and dry jello together. Add pineapple, oranges, and Cool Whip. Mix all together and chill.

title: cucumber nut rolls
directions: Cream together cheese, onion and cucumber.
Form into tiny balls and roll in nuts or spread on finger sandwiches after adding nuts.

title: mom's popcorn balls
directions: Cook Karo syrup, sugar and cream of tartar to soft ball stage (234°-240° degrees). Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla and mix well. Then add baking soda and stir well. Pour over popcorn and shape into balls.

title: date bars
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to egg yolks and mix thoroughly.
Fold in stiffly beaten whites.
Milk may be added; this facilitates mixing.
Spread 1/2-inch thick in a greased and floured baking pan, 9 x 9-inch.
Bake in a slow to moderate oven (325°) for 25 minutes.
When cold, cut in strips and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 30 bars, 3 x 3/4 x 3/4-inch.

title: chocolate mayo cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, except baking soda.
Add 2 teaspoons baking soda to the hot water.
Mix remaining ingredients and beat. Bake at 350°.

title: rice pudding(microwave recipe)
directions: In a deep 1-quart bowl combine all ingredients.
Heat on Medium uncovered for 10 minutes, stirring several times.

title: rice dish
directions: Boil 10 to 12 medium size sweet potatoes until tender.
Cool, then peel.
Cut into thin slices or chunks.
Layer in large casserole (buttered) alternately:
sweet potatoes, butter chunks (small), miniature marshmallows, ending with marshmallows.
Bake in 350° oven (covered) for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
If marshmallows have melted, add more for topping.

title: double-cheese chicken casserole
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil over high heat. Add onion, celery and bell pepper. Boil until tender, about 10 minutes. Add pasta to pot. Cook until tender, about 10 minutes; drain.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix ingredients with mixer on low speed.
Grease and flour cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream butter, egg and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients all together.
Add egg mixture, then hot water.
Beat until smooth. Batter is soft but makes fine cake.
Bake in greased shallow 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: guacamole
directions: Put all ingredients in a food processor and blend for 10 seconds.

title: orange party punch
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in 2 cups cold water and fruit juices.
Chill until ready to serve. Spoon sherbet into punch bowl.
Pour gelatin mix and ginger ale over sherbet.
Yields 40 servings.

title: herb-marinated chicken on the grill
directions: Skin chicken.
Place in Ziploc bag.
For marinade, in a bowl, combine cooking wine, oil, vinegar, basil, oregano, onion powder and garlic.
Pour over chicken to coat well.
Marinate 5 to 24 hours in the refrigerator, turning bag occasionally.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Grill on an uncovered grill over medium coals for 20 minutes, brushing occasionally with marinade.
Turn chicken and grill for 15 to 25 minutes more or until tender and no longer pink, brushing often with marinade.

title: oire's cornbread
directions: Mix together and pour into a heated and greased iron skillet. Bake at 450° for about 10 or 15 minutes.

title: nutty apple pie cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until smooth.
Add egg; beat until fluffy.
Stir flour with cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Mix baking soda with warm water.
Add flour mixture along with baking soda and water to creamed mixture.
Beat until smooth and fluffy. Fold in apples and nuts.
Spread into a well-buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until cake tests done. Serve each wedge while still warm.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pan and simmer on the stove for 1 hour.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Season to taste.
Mix well.
Heat on top of stove or put in large baking dish in 350° oven until bubbly.
Serves 12.

title: cauliflower polonaise
directions: Cook whole cauliflower in small amount of boiling, salted water, covered, until tender, about 20 minutes.
Finely chop egg. Heat butter until lightly browned; stir in crumbs, parsley and egg.
Spoon mixture over cooked cauliflower.

title: unusual frozen banana split fruit salad
directions: Mix together.
Place into container and freeze.

title: brown bread
directions: Beat oil and sugars together.
Add eggs.
Alternating with dry ingredients, add sour milk.
Pour into greased bread tins.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange balls
directions: Combine wafers, sugar, pecans and coconut.
Add juice and margarine.
Mix well and form into balls.

title: red peanut patties
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and water to a boil.
Add peanuts and food coloring.
Start boiling.
Continue boiling for 20 minutes to hard-ball stage.
Add margarine and a dash of salt.
Beat until gloss disappears and pour on buttered cookie sheet.

title: orange cream salad dressing
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, mustard, salt and paprika in a saucepan.
Add juices and butter.
Cook, stirring constantly until clear and thickened.
Chill.
Fold in whipped cream.
Serve as a dressing over salads made with pear halves, pineapple, peaches or other fruits.
Makes 2 cups.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their skin until tender; drain, peel and slice or cube.
Keep warm.
Fry bacon until crisp; add onion and cook until soft.
Stir in green pepper, celery and parsley; cook about 1 hour.

title: sour pickles
directions: Pack washed and dried cukes in sterilized quart jar.
Add 2 tablespoons dry mustard, 2 tablespoons salt and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cover securely and shake jar so ingredients are well mixed.
Shake occasionally.
Ready to eat in 2 weeks.

title: garlic ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and garlic powder.
Roll on wax paper sprinkled with sugar and pecans.
Excellent with crackers.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and soda.
Mix and melt over low heat the margarine, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil and pour slowly in the dry ingredients and mix until smooth only.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix together and pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix flour, sugar and mayonnaise.
Add milk and stir until smooth.
Spoon into greased and floured muffin tins.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Makes 16 to 18 muffins.

title: swedish meatballs my way
directions: Put in large pot or crock-pot.
Cook until hot.

title: quick chicken or tuna casserole
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar. Add eggs. Beat well. Add flour which has been sifted with salt and soda. Add nuts. Drop from spoon. Bake at 350°.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Put all the ingredients, except the last 5, into a large pot and bring to a boil.
Garnish with cheese, sour cream, lettuce, tomatoes, and Fritos.

title: monkey bread
directions: Coat biscuits in cinnamon and sugar; drop in greased Bundt pan. Melt together margarine, sugar and cinnamon; pour over biscuits. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday strada
directions: Arrange bread in overlapping rows in bottom of 3-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle ham (or sausage), cheese, pepper and onions over bread.
Beat eggs in large bowl; add milk, mustard, pepper and paprika.
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serve with white or cheese sauce if desired.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: cider baked onions
directions: Cut
the onions in half across.
Melt butter in skillet. Put cut
side down and fry until brown.
Turn upward in baking dish. Sprinkle with herbs; pour in cider.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375°.

title: reese's peanut butter balls
directions: Cream together whipped butter, peanut butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Roll in balls the size of a big marble.
Melt paraffin and chocolate in double boiler.
Dip balls and let stand on wax paper until hard.

title: baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dip chicken pieces in dressing and then roll in cornflakes.
Place in a baking dish; bake approximately 50 to 70 minutes.
